<HEAD>

<TITLE>Planning Circle Financial Group: Trimark Regular Investment Plan</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="images/pcfgbkgd.jpg">

<A HREF="../pcfg/"><IMG SRC="images/pcfgsm.gif" ALT="Return to the Planning Circle Financial Group Home Page" WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=71 BORDER=0 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Trimark Fund</H1>
<P>


<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Trimark</I> Regular Investment Plan</H2>

<HR>

<H4>
<UL>
<LI>$100 Purchase
<LI>for the period ending December 31, 1995
</UL>
</H4>
<HR>

<P>
Below is an example of a <I><B>Trimark</B></I><B>
Regular Investment <I>Plan.</I></B> The purchaser of the plan
invested $100 a month beginning at <B>Trimark Fund</B>'s inception,
September 1, 1981.<BR>

<P>
The <B>Trimark Fund</B> plan value reflects the deduction
of a 5% commission rate as well as changes in unit value and assumes
income and capital gains distributions are reinvested. It does
not take into account administrative fees, payable by unitholders,
which would have reduced returns.<BR>

<P>
For comparative purposes, we have shown the same
schedule of deposits invested at a 10% annual compounded total
rate of return with no fees deducted.<BR>

<P>
Latest 1-year, 3-year, 5-year and 10-year historical
annual compounded total rates of return for <B>Trimark Fund</B>
to December 31, 1995 were 16.7%, 20.8%, 23.9% and 15.0% respectively.
Since its inception, investors in <B>Trimark Fund</B> earned 18.3%.
While all results are based on the past performance of the fund,
these are not necessarily indicative of future results. Your unit
value and investment returns will fluctuate.<BR>
<BR>


