<HEAD>

<TITLE>Planning Circle Financial Group: An Introduction to Mackenzie</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="images/pcfgbkgd.jpg">

<A HREF="../pcfg/"><IMG SRC="images/pcfgsm.gif" ALT="Return to the Planning Circle Financial Group Home Page" WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=71 BORDER=0 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>

<P>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>An Introduction to Mackenzie</H1>
<P>
At Mackenzie, we're committed to building financial independence
for investors in our Industrial, Ivy and Universal Fund groups.
For more than 25 years, we've assisted investors to achieve both
specific financial goals and the sense of financial well-being
which comes from knowing that their savings are being professionally
managed to grow and earn income.
<P>
Our approach is based on several fundamental investment principles:
<UL>
<LI>Investors should be able to take advantage of the benefits
of diversification by choosing from a wide range of mutual fund
options based an types of assets held, geographic scope and management
style.
<LI>Only proven professionals with an outstanding record of performance
may direct fund portfolios.
<LI>Fund managers and their styles should remain consistent through
the years. Those responsible fop international funds should be
located close to their investments. 
<LI>Independent, knowledgeable financial planning advice is essential
to meeting personal objectives.
<LI>True professional management must include a dedicated, ongoing
investor service and information program. 
<LI>Mutual funds should be interchangeable at the option of the
investor. 
</UL>

<P>
By sticking with the principles that have guided us over the past
27-years and with investment approaches that have generated superior
long-term performance we plan to continue to be investment managers
of choice for Canadians into the next century and beyond.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
