<HEAD>

<TITLE>Planning Circle Financial Group: Mackenzie: Diversification: The Importance of Choice</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="images/pcfgbkgd.jpg">

<A HREF="../pcfg/"><IMG SRC="images/pcfgsm.gif" ALT="Return to the Planning Circle Financial Group Home Page" WIDTH=75 HEIGHT=71 BORDER=0 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>

<P>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Diversification:</H1>
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Importance of Choice</H1>
<P>
In today's complex economic
environment, it's only natural for investors to be cautious. 
But to build a successful investment portfolio, even the most
cautious investor must realize that there is no such thing as
a risk-free investment ... that potential returns frequently increase
with volatility ... and that the most important challenge is to
build a diversified investment portfolio that offers the right
balance between risk and reward.
<P>
As professional money managers,
we recognize that each investor has different risk and return
preferences.  To satisfy these preferences, our goal is to offer
the broadest range of mutual fund choices in Canada.  By investing
in a portfolio of different Mackenzie-managed funds, investors
can strike a balance that best suits their own investment goals.
<P>
We offer a full range of investment
choices. Our equity funds typically produce better long-term returns
than income or balanced funds - although, inevitably, greater
risk is assumed over the short term.
<P>
For many Canadians, Mackenzie's
domestic equity funds represent the ideal balance between risk
and reward.  They are prepared to experience occasional volatility
in short-term performance - including lower or even negative returns.
 In exchange, the longer term rewards can be substantial, as the
performance record of our equity funds indicates.
<P>
To decide which Mackenzie
fund - or funds - are right for you, and to establish your investment
objectives and risk tolerance level, consult an investment fund
dealer or stockbroker.  These independent professionals can help
you to diversity your portfolio ... and make the most of these
important fund choices.<BR>

<P>
<HR>
