<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 11/25/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER><img src="../../../images/evng_arch.gif" width=400 height=56 border=0 alt="The Evening News On-Line Archive"></CENTER>


<CENTER>
<H1>Monday, November 25, 1996</H1>
</CENTER>

<ul>
    <li>Foster Newser       
    <li>Drunk Jumper        
    <li>Rent Study          
    <li>Developement Charge 
    <li>Red Cross - Team     
    <li>NFL - Border Bars     
    <li>Simpson             
    <li>Fergie Book Bash    
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Foster Newser</b><p>
York Regional Police are denying accusations of browbeating a rape suspect into confessing.<br>   23 year old Jeremy Foster, claims after he was arrested he got nothing to eat and was denied sleep until he confessed to the crimes.<br>   The 23 three year old says he believed the confession was the only way he would get to see a lawyer.<br>   Foster was accused of two knifepoint sexual assaults and held in custody for almost a week after the rapes.<br>   DNA tests he demanded, proved he was not the rapist.
<hr>
<b>Drunk Jumper</b><p>
A night of drinking has turned to tragedy for a third-year University of Waterloo student.<br>   The 21-year-old is in critical condition in a Hamilton hospital after falling from a ninth-floor balcony early this morning.<br>   Police say they are treating the incident as an accident.<br>   The man's name has not been released.
<hr>
<b>Rent Study</b><p>
A private research study suggests that a growing number of people who rent rather than own their own home, may be forced on the streets, because of the Harris government's loosening of rent controls.<br>   
<hr>
<b>Developement Charge</b><p>
Municipalities will soon be paying more for building parks, roads and other services.<br>   Since 1991 development charges for everthing from water and sewer- hookups to the construction of new roads, libraries or parks, have been paid by new home buyers.<br>   But today, municipal affairs minister Al Leach introduced legislation to spread these costs to the entire muncipality.
<hr>
<b>Red Cross - Team</b><p>
A group of Canadian doctors is being given some free medical advice.<br>  15 doctors are in Ottawa for a two day training session at the Red Cross before they head to Central Africa to help victims of the conflict in Zaire.<br>  A large part of the preparation is learnign how to cope emotionally in a war zone.
<hr>
<b>NFL - Border Bars</b><p>
On the heels of what is being billed as a hugely successful Grey Cup weekend ... to the Bills and the NFL's battle with Canadian bar owners.<br>  Once again the league is threatening to sue Canadian bar owners who show this weekends blacked out Buffalo Bills game.<br>  13 bars have already been sued, most of which have paid an out of court settlement.<br>  But a handful of bar owners vow they're not going to be bullied by the deep pocketed NFL.
<hr>
<b>Simpson</b><p>
OJ Simpson says he doesn't know how blood got inside his Bronco.<br>   Simpson is being grilled again at his wrongful death trial.<br>   Plaintiff lawyer Daniel Petrocelli asked Simpson if he knew about the discovery of blood matching his own -- in the Bronco, the morning after the murders of his ex-wife and her friend.<br>   Simpson said he did, but that he had no explanation.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Fergie Book Bash</b><p>
England's Duchess of York is back on her old stomping grounds.<br>   Fergie recently wound up a successful tour of the United States to promote her autobiography.<br>  But back on her home soil, the reaction has been less than favorable.<br>  







<P>
