<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 11/18/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER><img src="../../../images/evng_arch.gif" width=400 height=56 border=0 alt="The Evening News On-Line Archive"></CENTER>


<CENTER>
<H1>Monday, November 18, 1996</H1>
</CENTER>

<ul>
    <li>Zaire Extra         
    <li>Home Sweet Home     
    <li>Child Poverty       
    <li>Rape Suspect - Court  
    <li>Ontario Sale        
    <li>Grey Cup Day One    
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Zaire extra</b><p>
Prime minister Chretien says Canada is determined to press ahead with the international rescue mission for central Africa, despite the mass return of refugees to Rwanda.<br>   Chretien says: "we have to go there and we have to go for humanitarian purposes."<br>    About 500-thousand Rwandan refugees have returned home in recent days, but Chretien says the government is still worried about the half-million still in Zaire.
<hr>
<b>Home Sweet Home</b><p>
CNN's Christiane Amanpour is in Rwanda and reports now on the journey of the nearly one million refugees who are back home ... how they got there and what they found when they arrived.
<hr>
<b>Child Poverty</b><p>
Groups fighting child poverty are sugesting a child's equivalent to the Canada Pension Plan.<br>  Campaign Two Thousand says its proposed social investment fund would lift eight hundred thousand children out of poverty.<br>  That would put Canada on track to keeping a promise to eliminate child poverty made to the United Nations in 1989.<br>  Since then, child poverty in Canada has almost doubled.
<hr>
<b>Rape Suspect - Court</b><p>
A Thornhill man faces six charges in connection with two sexual assaults last week in Vaughan, just north of Toronto.<br>  A woman was grabbed last Sunday while walking near a park.<br>  On Thursday, a woman fought off an attacker in the same area.<br>  Police say 23-year-old Jeremy Foster has been charged with two counts of sexual assault, and one count each of threatening death, wearing a disguise, robbery and forcible confinement.       <br> Toronto police have not laid charges against Foster in connection with two recent sexual assaults in suburban North York.
<hr>
<b>Ontario sale</b><p>
Premier Mike Harris says he hopes a 17-million dollar advertising blitz will help create jobs by increasing direct foreign investment in Ontario.<br>   Harris held a worldwide TV teleconference today -- to sell Ontario to the world as a great place to do business.<br>   The premier says just a two per cent increase in foreign investment should create thousands of new jobs for Ontario.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Grey Cup Day One</b><p>
Its the Argos and Eskimos in the CFL Final this Sunday in Hamilton. With the Grey Cup challengers ready to play, Matt Hayes reports that the only challenge left is to sellout the stadium.
<i><br>  There's no doubt about it. Grey Cup organizers were thrilled by Toronto's victory in yesterdays CFL Eastern Final.<br>  By the weekend ticket sales had just past the 30 thousand mark. The impact of the Toronto-Edmonton matchup is just starting to be felt at the roar store ticket office.<br>  That means about 7 thousand tickets are still available. Its hoped those seats will be purchased by anxious Argo and Eskimo fans.<br>  Surprisingly I found many Argo fans on the streets of Hamilton today.<br>  </i>






<P>
