<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 11/15/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<CENTER><img src="../../../images/evng_arch.gif" width=400 height=56 border=0 alt="The Evening News On-Line Archive"></CENTER>


<CENTER>
<H1>Friday, November 15, 1996</H1>
</CENTER>

<ul>
    <li>Docs Update         
    <li>Serial Rapist       
    <li>Bernardo Cell       
    <li>McCoy - Rescue       
    <li>Martin Zaire        
    <li>Hong Kong #5        
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Docs Update</b><p>
The first crack has appeared in the doctors job action against the Harris govenrment.<br>     Baby doctors in Sudbury have temporarily ended their job action against the protest.<br>   Obstetricians have not accepted new patients in Sudbury since June 1st.<br>   But they now say they will stop turning away new patients over concerns for the health of pregnant women.<br>
<hr>
<b>Serial Rapist</b><p>
Police say a serial rapist is on the loose in the Toronto area.<br>   In the most recent incident, a woman fought off a knife-wielding man last night in Vaughan, just north of Toronto. She was thrown to the ground and suffered a cut hand but was not sexually assaulted.<br>  Investigators believe the same man is responsible for three other attacks this week.
<hr>
<b>Bernardo Cell</b><p>
The plexiglass shield protecting Paul Bernardo from attacks by inmates has been removed from his cell door.<br>   The shield was installed on the cell door at the Kingston Penitentiary after inmates pelted Bernardo with human waste.<br>   But prison officials say they took the shield down so Bernardo could benefit from heating and ventilation during the winter.
<hr>
<b>McCoy - Rescue</b><p>
Four crewmen from a downed Canadian Forces helicopter are recovering in hospital today.<br>  The four were on a rescue mission at the northern tip of Labrador when the chopper went down in bad weather.<br>  One of those crewmen was 37 year old Scott McCoy from St. Catharines.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Martin Zaire</b><p>
Finance minister Paul Martin says the relief operation in Central Africa is something Canada must do despite the expense.<br>  Defence minister Doug Young has said the mission to Zaire and Rwanda could cost as much as one hundred million dollars...<br>  Martin says that's money well spent.
<hr>
<b>Hong Kong #5</b><p>
On July first 1997, Hong Kong will be transferred from British to Chinese rule.<br>   In 1999, another near-by colony will also be handed back to China.<br>  But unlike Hong Kong, this colony is not about to put up a fight.<br>  Tonight in part five of the series "Countdown in Hong Kong" we take you to a place that has chosen cooperation over confrontation in dealing with the transfer of power.






<P>
