<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 11/01/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, November 1, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>






<ul>
    <li>More Cuts           
    <li>Education Report    
    <li>Zaire               
    <li>Diana Australia     
    <li>Space Station       
    <li>Oscar Peterson      
</ul>
<hr>
<b>More Cuts</b><p>
Premier Mike Harris  is working on plans to cut yet another three billion dollars from provincial government spending.<br>  But the premier says he is still going ahead with his promised income tax cut to Ontarians.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Education Report</b><p>
A controversial new report on Ontario's education system was released in Toronto today.<br>  More than two months after education minister John Snoeblen appointed him to the task, Windsor lawyer Leon Paroian ... came forth with his recommendations to make major changes to the way that teachers bargain in this province.<br>   The most controversial of those recommendations, is a call for a total ban on strikes by teachers.<br>   The recommendation has enraged teachers' unions, but Paroian, was defiant in his defence of the proposal.            Whether the recommendation makes sense or not... premier Mike Harris is already hinting that his government will not impose a ban on strikes by teachers.
<hr>
<b>Zaire</b><p>
The situation on the border between Zaire and Rwanda continues to deteriorate as hundreds of thousands of refugees are caught between two rival armies.<br>  Nobody has food or clean water, but many have rifles and rockets.<br>  Zaire's transitional parliament has voted to cut diplomatic ties with Rwanda, Burundi and Uganda.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Diana Australia</b><p>
The princess Di magic seems to be fading in Australia.<br>   During a four-day charity visit, crowds turning out to see the former wife of prince Charles have been disappointing.<br>   And in Sydney, American actress Priscilla Presley snapped up the best hotel suite in town.<br>   When Diana came to Australia in the 1980's, tens of thousands of admirers and royal watchers lined the streets for a glimpse of her.
<hr>
<b>Space Station</b><p>
NASA is planning to launch Space Shuttle Columbia next week to test new equipment for building the international space station.<br>   But the oldest and longest serving astronaut is worried the space agency wont be ready to build an orbiting outpost by the time the first piece is launched a year from now.
<hr>
<b>Oscar Peterson</b><p>
Jazz pianist Oscar Peterson has received many awards and honors during his legendary career, but the honor which undoubtedly means the most to him, is one he recently received from a few friends.<br>  



