<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 10/31/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, October 31, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>






<ul>
    <li>Doctors Vote        
    <li>GM Oshawa           
    <li>Overcrowded Jails   
    <li>Niagara Growth      
    <li>Ginseng Bar         
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Doctors Vote</b><p>
The council of the Ontario Medical Association has rejected a tentative deal with the Harris government. The OMA's 250 council members followed the advice of the province's doctors in turning thumbs down on the agreement. About three-quarters of doctors who voted in a province- wide referendum rejected the deal. 
<hr>
<b>GM Oshawa</b><p>
General Motors says a U.S. strike isn't hampering production at its truck plant in Oshawa... yet. The truck plant is running all three shifts today. But things will be re-evaluated tomorrow. Spokesman Stew Low says GM will do what it can to keep the plant stocked with parts. About 75-hundred American GM workers are out at plants in Wisconsin and Indianapolis. 
<hr>
<b>Overcrowded Jails</b><p>
Jails throughout the golden horseshoe are busting at the seams... triple bunking in cells has now become commonplace... and as Ian Dovey reports tonight ... guards are worried not only about their own safety...but that of inmates.                       
<I><br>  Another inmate arrives at the Hamilton Wentworth Detention Centre adding to what the guards say is an dangerous overcrowded situation inside.<br>  There are more than 400 inmates inside the facility, many of them are being double or triple bunked in a cell no wider than four feet. <br>    Quincy Morgan says the additional inmates are coming from correctional facilities in Toronto because they're filled to capacity. <br>     In the legislature, Liberal leader Lyn Mcleod has accused solicitor general Bob Runciman of ignoring the volatile situation, saying the Hamilton facility is a powder keg ready to blow.<br>   According to guards it came close to that a week ago Sunday when some inmates throw their food trays to the ground and refused to go back in their cells. <br>     A Ministry of Corrections offical says bed space is limited at all institutions in southern Ontario, but acknowledged the Hamilton Wentworth Detention Centre is a pressure point adding the situation is being constantly monitored in a reasonable and responsible way.<br>  </I>
<hr>
<b>Niagara Growth</b><p>
A senior official of the Royal Bank is forecasting boom times for the Niagara Region. Royal vice- president Gord Feeny says the region could post the highest economic growth in the province over the next five years. A similar forecast was made last month by the Business Development Bank of Canada.
<hr>
<b>Ginseng Bar</b><p>
An ancient Chinese secret is the root of the latest trend in healthy, Canadian snack foods. A new, low fat snack bar rolled off the production line at Sunny Crunch Foods in Markham this afternoon.



<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

