<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 10/23/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, October 23, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>






<ul>
    <li>Estey Report        
    <li>G.M. Vote           
    <li>Ovide - Newser      
    <li>Cabinet Caucus      
    <li>Simpson Trial       
    <li>Wildfires           
    <li>Queen Visit         
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Estey Report</b><p>
A judicial report released today blames poor police planning and improper action by the Ontario Public Service Employees Union, for a violent clash outside the Ontario Legislature last spring.<br>   The report comes just two days before organized labor plans a massive protest against the Harris government.<br>  
<hr>
<b>G.M. Vote</b><p>
The votes cast by 26 thousand striking General Motors workers in Ontario and Quebec are still being counted at this hour.<br>  The employees were voting on a tentative deal that was struck yesterday.<br>  It's a deal the Canadian Auto Workers union says is the best it could deliver to its membership.
<hr>
<b>Ovide - Newser</b><p>
Canada's native representatives say the Liberals deserve a failing grade for their red book promises on aboriginal issues.<br>  Assembly of First Nations chief, Ovide Mercredi, says the Liberals have ensured that natives have suffered because of the government's emphasis on defeicit reduction.
<hr>
<b>Cabinet Caucus</b><p>
The federal government says it has found room for an additional ten thousand job cuts in the public service.<br>  The government had originally estimated budget cuts would eliminate about 45 thousand jobs.<br>  But Treasury Board president Marcel Masse, says the extension of the governemnt's "program review", found more positions could be cut.
<hr>
<b>Simpson Trial</b><p>
Opening arguments have begun in the O.J. Simpson civil trial with a lawyer branding the former football star a "vengeful killer."<br>   Daniel Petrocelli, a lawyer for the family of murder victim Ronald Goldman, opened his case by declaring that all the evidence points to Simpson as the murderer.<br>   He vowed to prove Goldman and Nicole Simpson died at the hands of the former football star.<br> 
<hr>
<b>Wildfires</b><p>
The air attack has resumed against southern California wildfires and mother nature is now helping in the battle.<br>   Strong Santa Ana winds have died down, making it easier to fight the Malibu fire.<br>   It and other blazes have destroyed more than 100 homes.
<hr>
<b>Queen Visit</b><p>
And finally in news, the Queen plans a summer visit to Canada.<br>   She made the announcement at the opening of the British Parliament today, saying she'll visit Canada between June 24th and July 2nd.<br>   The Queen also plans to visit India and Pakistan next October to mark the 50th anniversary of their independence from Britain.




