<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 10/04/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, October 4, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>










<ul>
    <li>Collenette Quits    
    <li>CAW Presser      
    <li>Amateur Sport       
    <li>Drowning            
    <li>Gaza Tension        
    <li>Father Goose        
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Collenette Quits</b><p>
Defence minister David Collenette has quit the federal cabinet.  Under seige for months over the Somalia scandal it was a letter written for a constituent in an immigration case which Collenette says forced him to do the honourable thing and resign.<br>  
<hr>
<b>CAW Presser</b><p>
The federal government is worried about the bad news from the General Motors bargaining table.<br>   Labor minister Alfonso Gagliano wants talks to get moving.<br>   In the Commons, Gagliano said Ottawa is worried about the economic damage the GM strike may cause -- but can't intervene because it has no jurisdiction.<br>   Union president Buzz Hargrove says the two sides met briefly today but made no progress, and no talks are scheduled for the weekend.<br>   However, he says he'll be on call in case "GM decides to get into serious negotiations."
<hr>
<b>Amateur Sport</b><p>
Ontario's minister responsible for amateur sports, today unveiled the government's new strategy for funding sports and recreation in the province.<br>  In essence what it means is less money, and funding for fewer sports organizations.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Drowning</b><p>
A man implicated in the smuggling of illegal immigrants into the U.S. faces a manslaughter charge in Cornwall, Ontario.<br>  A 63-year-old woman died in hospital yesterday after a small, overloaded boat sank Wednesday in the St. Lawrence River.<br>   Eight others survived, and one man is still missing.<br>  The dead woman is believed to have been from India.
<hr>
<b>Gaza Tension</b><p>
One week ago, three palestinians died and many more were injured in clashes with Israeli troops in Jerusalem.<br>  The confrontation followed prayers at a holy muslim site.<br>   Since then, a middle-east summit in Washington brought the promise of new Israeli -Palestinian peace talks, scheduled to begin on Sunday.<br>  But the U.U. says the situation in the region  remains dangerous.
<hr>
<b>Father Goose</b><p>
Finally tonight, Canada's father goose is taking to the skies in search of "Igor" a goose who has strayed from the flock.<br>  Bill Lishman a Canadian inventor who taught a flock of geese to change migration patterns by following an aircraft, was the subject of the movie "Fly Away Home."<br>  Lishman's project was dubbed "operation migration."<br>  All of Lishman's geese wear gray neck bands with yellow vertical stripes.<br>  Today Lishman started out in Niagara Falls New York in search of the stray Igor.<br>  Two sightings of Igor have been made in the Buffalo area.<br>  Lishman will retrace the geese's migration route down south to Virginia.







<P>
