<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 09/27/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, September 27, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>







<ul>
    <li>GM-C.A.W.           
    <li>Mahaffy - Rock        
    <li>RCMP Women          
    <li>Bhaduria Suit       
    <li>Israel Update       
    <li>Hope Diamond        
</ul>
<hr>
<b>GM-C.A.W.</b><p>
Just days before a contract deadline, General Motors appears to be heading towards a strike with its union.<br>   A letter by the president of GM to employees, warning of the need to contract out jobs, has sparked a furor among GM workers.<br>  The Canadian Autoworkers Union may walk away from the bargaining table this week-end.
<hr>
<b>Mahaffy - Rock</b><p>
Debbie Mahaffy, the mother of slain teenager Leslie Mahaffy, is going to deliver a message to the federal justice minister that will be difficult for him to ignore.<br>   Since Leslie was killed by Paul Bernardo five years ago, Debbie Mahaffy has been fighting to keep killers behind bars... for life.<br>  And Mahaffy believes that talking to the justice minister is just like talking to a rock.
<hr>
<b>RCMP Women</b><p>
A staggering number of female RCMP officers say they have been sexually harrassed on the job.  In fact, more than half said so in an internal inquiry conducted in 1993.<br>  Since 1994, RCMP employees have had mandatory harrassment training courses. So far eight thousand have taken them.<br>  Sargaent Donna Brownlee says the numbers come as no surprise.  She adds a number of assistance programs are available for women who need them.  <br>  Sgt. Brownless advises women who have been harrassed not to leave the force.
<hr>
<b>Bhaduria Suit</b><p>
Independent MP Jag Bhaduria has launched a multi-million dollar lawsuit against the Toronto Board of Eduction.<br>   The board fired Bhaduria in 1990 because of threatening letters he sent to board officials.<br>   At that time the Markham MP, who was a teacher, was angry because he was not promoted to vice-principal.
<hr>
<b>Israel Update</b><p>
Palestinians and Israelis are still exchanging gunfire in their worst clashes in decades.<br>   Sources close to Yasser Arafat say he has ordered police to stop any attacks on Israelis, but the fighting continues.<br>   In one of today's fiercest battles, Israeli helicopter gunships fired at Palestinian gunmen in the southern Gaza Strip, and tanks surrounded the area.<br>   Scores of people have been killed in the fighting over the past four days.
<hr>
<b>Hope Diamond</b><p>
Legend has it the Hope Diamond was owned by kings and queens, caused premature deaths and beheadings and even carries a curse.<br>   But even a diamond with so much weighty history needs to be cleaned now and then.<br>  So the largest known blue diamond was escorted to New York under heavy security this week...for a bath.<br>   







