<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 09/23/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, September 23, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>






<ul>
    <li>McLean Report       
    <li>OPSEU
    <li>Labour Protest      
    <li>Toronto Fatal       
    <li>Cable            
    <li>Korea Infiltrators  
    <li>IRA Arrest          
    <li>JFK Jr. Wedding     
</ul>
<hr>
<b>McLean Report</b><p>
 While the speaker of the legislature, Al McLean is on three months' sick leave, his lawyer is threatening legal action if provincial politicians are given access to a report dealing with sexual harrassment charges against mclean. 
<hr>
<b>OPSEU</b><p>
A deal has been reached in a strike that pitted the staff of the Ontario Public Service Employees Union against their bosses.<br>   Randy Robinson, a spokesman for the 239-member ontario public service staff union, says a verbal agreement was reached last night.<br>   Staff union members walked off the job September 3rd to fight a plan by OPSEU to cut staff and costs, following an expensive strike against the Harris government.
<hr>
<b>Labour Protest</b><p>
Ontario's top labor leader is warning Toronto to expect a crippling shutdown next month.<br>   Gord Wilson of the Ontario Federation of Labor, says Toronto is where the boss lives and "the way to challenge him is to put him out of work."<br>   One-day protests against the Tory government, have drawn thousands of people, and stopped public transit, in London, Hamilton, Kitchener and Peterborough.
<hr>
<b>Toronto Fatal</b><p>
Police have more questions than answers following the death of an Ajax limousine driver in downtown Toronto.<br>   An autopsy on the body of 30-year-old Michael Hajj has failed to provide any clues as to why he plunged more than 30 metres off the Gardiner Expressway.<br>   Police say Hajj either jumped or was pushed over the railing.<br>   His body was found after his limo was involved in an accident with two other cars -- one of them a stolen Honda.
<hr>
<b>Cable </b><p>
An Ontario MP credits a push by consumers for the passage of a bill to prevent cable companies from negative-option billing.<br>   That's where cable firms charge consumers for specialty channels they haven't requested unless otherwise notified.<br>   Roger Gallaway says a lot of MPs were lobbied over the weekend by constituents who don't want to be forced to buy something they don't want.<br>   Liberal, New Democrat and Reform MPs voted to pass the bill, despite concerns from cabinet that it might stop french-language specialty channels from being shown outside of quebec.
<hr>
<b>Korea Infiltrators</b><p>
Officials in South Korea are saying no to a request by North Korea to get a grounded submarine back.<br>   The south calls the request "unjustified."<br>  The communist north says engine trouble caused the submarine to ground last week off South Korea's coast.<br>    But Seoul says the sub was full of commandos trying to infiltrate into the south.<br>  So far, 20 of the North Koreans have been killed. About 40-thousand South Korean troops are hunting five still believed to be at large.
<hr>
<b>IRA Arrest</b><p>
British police say they've foiled an "imminent" Irish Republican Army attack, that could have caused "grave loss of life."<br>  The plan involved setting off a "large vehicle bomb."<br>  Explosives were seized in early morning raids today in London and south England, and six people were arrested.<br>   One died after a shootout with police.
<hr>
<b>JFK Jr. Wedding</b><p>
One of the world's most eligible bachelors is eligible no more.<br>  John F. Kennedy Junior, the magazine publisher once voted the "sexiest man alive", married Carolyn Bessette in a very private ceremony on Saturday.<br>  Helicopters buzzed the event on an island off the Georgia coast, but only a chosen few got to attend.<br>  Kennedy, who was formerly linked with actress Daryl Hannah, had been dating Bessette for about five years.




<P>
