<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 09/20/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, September 20, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>







<ul>
    <li>Snobelen - Highschool 
    <li>P.M. - Week         
    <li>Body Parts          
    <li>Kevorkian           
    <li>Simpson             
    <li>Anderson Suit       
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Snobelen - Highschool</b><p>
Education minister John snobelen says Ontario's high school system is outdated and irrelevant.<br>   He made those comments today as he announced a massive reform of high school education.<br>   
<hr>
<b>P.M. - Week</b><p>
From haircuts to watergate it's been a somewhat confusing first week for parliament, and some of the confusion came from the prime minister himself.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Body Parts</b><p>
Their suspicions have been confirmed.<br>   Toronto police say dismembered remains found in an east-end apartment are those of 16-year-old Mehdi Amin Moha-mmadi.<br>   The teen, who lived near the building where the body parts were found, was reported missing earlier this week.<br>   A torso and a severed leg were found on Wednesday in a closet in the apartment.<br>   More body parts were later found in a nearby ravine and dumpster.<br>   28 year-old Taghe Savo-ji-pour is charged with first-degree murder and committing an indignity to a body.<br>   Police say the victim and the accused knew each other.
<hr>
<b>kevorkian</b><p>
Police in Southfield, Michigan have arrested a man who is alleged to have said he was going to "stop" the so-called suicide doctor, Jack Kevorkian.<br>  The man was arrested outside the office of Kevorkian's lawyer.<br>   Police say they found an unloaded gun and ammunition in his car.
<hr>
<b>Simpson</b><p>
<br>   OJ Simpson arrived at a Santa Monica, California court today, to chants of "OJ is a murderer" and "DNA tells the story."<br>   This is the first day Simpson is attending his civil trial in a wrongful death suit since jury selection began.<br>  He said nothing as he walked into the courthouse.
<hr>
<b>Anderson Suit</b><p>
A TV infomercial host has won more than half a million dollars in dmages in a verdict against actress Loni Anderson.<br>  A Los Angeles jury today recommended anderson pay 565 thousand dollars in general damage.<br>  The jury found she violated her contract for promoting skin care products.




