<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 08/23/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, August 23, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>



<ul>
    <li>Hwy 24 Fatals       
    <li>Pyramid Scheme         
    <li>Ont. Education Costs      
    <li>Speaker Sex         
    <li>New TWA             
    <li>Slumber Nightmare   
    <li>Mother Teresa       
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Hwy 24 Fatals</b><p>
<br>  Four people are dead and four others, critically injured after a minivan was hit by a transport truck near Guelph early this morning.<br>  The accident occurred at an intersection, residents deemed unsafe years ago .
<hr>
<b>Pyramid Scheme</b><p>
<br> A "get rich quick" scheme has left as many as 10-thousand people wondering what happened to their money.<br>   Toronto police say the investors -- including a few who lost up to two-million dollars each -- poured their cash into an illegal pyramid scheme.<br>   Those stung live mainly in the Toronto area, but some are from British Columbia and Europe.<br>   Police say investors were offered a 10 percent return on their money.<br>   The cash was to be put in highly profitable commodity markets -- but no money ended up in genuine investments.
<hr>
<b>Ont. Education Costs</b><p>
<br>  The Harris government says it is going to review its collective bargaining rules for teachers and school boards.<br>  This comes in the wake of two government reports that state that Ontario teachers make too much money and too many school boards raised taxes this year.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Speaker Sex</b><p>
<br>   Ontario's speaker of the legislature is facing yet another allegation of sexual harassment.<br>  The Toronto Star reports that a woman who worked as a conservative staffer at the legislature back in 1991, complained to her boss about Al McLeans' conduct.<br>   The newspaper states Kareen Kerr spoke to tory member Elizabeth Witmer about McLeans' conduct at a caucus function.<br>   The newspaper quotes unnamed friends and co-workers as saying Kerr complained that McLean caressed her back, put his arm around her and propositioned her.<br>   Kerr quit her job in 1992 and died of a heart attack a year later.<br>   McLean denies any knowledge of the latest complaint.
<hr>
<b>New TWA</b><p>
<br>  The FBI has confirmed that explosive residue has been found on wreckage of TWA flight 800.<br>  However, they are not concluding that the plane was bombed.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Slumber Nightmare</b><p>
<br>     A slumber party in Chesapeake, Virginia turned into a nightmare.<br>  Police say a man broke into a house where teenagers were spending the night.<br>    One girl was stabbed to death and two girls and a boy were injured.<br>   At least two of the girls were raped.<br>   A neighbor has been arrested.
<hr>
<b>Mother Teresa</b><p>
<br>     Doctors in India are stepping up efforts to stabilize Mother Teresa.<br>   They are administering new drugs after she suffered partial heart failure today.<br>    The elderly nun was admitted to hospital Tuesday suffering from Malaria.<br>  Pope John Paul has issued a statement wishing her a speedy recovery.


<P>
