<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 08/22/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thurssday, August 22, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>



<ul>
    <li>UAW Strike Target   
    <li>Premiers            
    <li>Liberal Convention  
    <li>Biker Wars          
    <li>Parolin Follow       
    <li>Raccoon Rabies      
    <li>Iguanas Evicted  
    <li>Computer Virus      
    <li>TWA Update          
    <li>Straw House         
</ul>
<hr>
<b>UAW Strike Target</b><p>
<br> The United Auto Workers Union in the US has delayed deciding which company to target in national contract talks. And that has put a lot of pressure on the Canadian Auto Workers union, who has already given its deadline for targeting one of the big three auto makers. 
<hr>
<b>Premiers</b><p>
 Premier Mike Harris says it's important to get the premiers talking about potential solutions, not just problems.<br> Speaking at the premiers meeting in Jasper, Alberta, Harris said the provinces and territories should be given more control over their own affairs.<br> He adds the premiers agree the status quo is not working.<br> Harris also says the premiers are not as divided on federal-provincial power-sharing as has been reported.
<hr>
<b>Liberal Convention</b><p>
<br> And then there were six...the newest candidate for the Liberal leadership position is MPP Annamarie Castrilli of Toronto.<br> She has not formally declared her candidacy, but her office confirms Castrilli is in the running and her papers have been filed with the party.<br> The other MPP's are Dalton McGuinty, Dwight Duncan, Joe Cordiano, John Gerretsen who announced yesterday and Gerard Kennedy.
<hr>
<b>Biker Wars</b><p>
<br> Police say biker gangs vying for control of the drug trade between Toronto and the US border see Hamilton as a prize ripe for the picking. So far, the battle has been played out among established Ontario gangs -- Satan's Choice, Outlaws and, in Hamilton, the Red Devils. Police believe the Hell's Angels are preparing to launch a major offensive for control. A spokesman for the Hamilton Wentworth Regional Police says the angels "want Ontario." And police say the angels are notorious for violence when moving into new territory.<br> The Hell's Angels is the predominant bike gang in Canada outside Ontario.<br> There are 11 chapters across Canada but only individual members in Ontario, the outlaws are most influential gang in Ontario.<br> There's evidence that established bikers in the Hamilton area are preparing to confront the angels and police believe there may be an alliance or truce between gangs and police worry a new round of violence could follow.
<hr>
<b>Parolin Follow</b><p>
<br> A six year old Princeton, B.C. boy badly mauled by a cougar was told yesterday, that his heroic mother Cindy Parolin died while saving his life. Princeton mayor John Stinson says the interior community is rallying its support around Cindy's husband ...Les Parolin and his four children. Support that includes a memorial fund and a scholarship.
<hr>
<b>Raccoon Rabies</b><p>
The Ministry of Natural Resources is taking its fight against raccoon rabies across the US border into upper New York state.<br> Ministry spokesman Charles McGinnis says Ontario has put-up 125-thousand dollars towards a cross-border program to drop vaccine-laden bait in the state this fall.<br> It's part of a prevention program aimed at keeping raccoon rabies out of Ontario.<br> Ministry planes will also be dropping the vaccine over parts of southeastern Ontario in September.
<hr>
<b>Iguanas Evicted </b><p>
<br> Tenants in a downtown Toronto apartment building have gone to court to have a pair of iguanas evicted.<br> A judge has ruled that Chico and Chocolate, interfered with the comfort and enjoyment of the mainly elderly tenants of the building. Some of the 70 residents, who signed a petition, complained that they were afraid to have their grandchildren visit because of the lizards. However the owner of the pet iguanas, Frank Gonzales says his pets wouldn't hurt a fly. And that the management is out to get him because he won a court case against them. <br>  (clip)
<hr>
<b>Computer Virus</b><p>
<br> Today was a good day to give your home computer a rest. A virus was set to attack PC's when the date read August 22nd. Macintosh users are off the hook, but IBM-compatible PC users be forewarned. Computers that are infected will get a message saying "HD Euthanasia by Demon Emperor." No one knows where the virus came from, but it may have spread from a world wide web site that offers sharewhere. The virus is also set to attack again on September 22nd.
<hr>
<b>TWA Update</b><p>
<br> The recovered body count has now reached 209 in the TWA crash. Most of the missing victims from TWA flight 800 were seated in the middle of the airplane. And that's where investigators think the explosion that brought the plane down occurred. That word comes from Robert Francis of the US National Transportation Safety Board today. He also says investigators continue running tests, trying to determine exactly what destroyed the plane.
<hr>
<b>Straw House</b><p>
<br> You have no doubt heard about the house that Jack built...then there was noted condo construction project of the three little pigs, but its not likely you've heard the story of the house being built by Moira Hepburn.<br> She may have started a brand new trend in construction as we see in this report.


<P>
