<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 08/16/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, August 16, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>




<ul>
    <li>Cabinet Shuffle     
    <li>Harris-Speaker      
    <li>OPP Hero            
    <li>Campus Shooting     
    <li>Dole-Conv.          
    <li>Royal Pain          
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Cabinet Shuffle</b><p>
<br> Premier Mike Harris fired his environment minister today and demoted another in a shakeup that brought two backbenchers into the government's inner circle.<br>  Critics say the moves have sent a clear message to the taxpayers.... privatization is high on the government's agenda.
<hr>
<b>Harris-Speaker</b><p>
 Premier Mike Harris said today he wants to get the controversy surrounding the speaker of the legislation, Al Mclean, delt with as soon as possible. Special assistant to the speaker, Sandi Thompson has made an informal complaint against Mclean of sexual harassment. She is currently on leave with full pay. <br>            Speaker Mclean is in Malaysia for the next two weeks attending a parliamentary commonweath conference. 
<hr>
<b>OPP Hero</b><p>
<br>  An OPP officer received cuts and minor burns while attempting to rescue two men from a flaming crash this morning in Toronto.<br>   Constable Jason Diminie was patroling the 4-0-1 highway when he came across a vehicle engulfed in flames.<br>   Diminie reached through the flames and smashed the passenger door window.           <br>  The 25-year-old driver is in serious condition at North York General Hospital.<br>   His 26-year-old brother was pronounced dead at the scene.
<hr>
<b>Campus Shooting</b><p>
<br>   In international news tonight,  a 36-year-old graduate engineering student is accused of gunning down three professors at a San Diego state university.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Dole-Conv.</b><p>
The campaigning begins anew today for Bob Dole. One day after accepting the Republican presidential nomination, Dole kicks off a four-state campaign sweep. In his speech last night, Dole attacked the Clinton Administration as elitists "who never grew up, never did anything real." Dole maintains the answer to today's social ills lies in a return to the values of his second world war generation.
<hr>
<b>Royal Pain</b><p>
<br>  As if the royal divorce wasn't bad enough.. Princess Diana is contending with another problem.<br>   



