<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 08/07/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, August 7, 1996</H2><BR>

<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>



<ul>
    <li>Health Coalition    
    <li>Smog Shots          
    <li>Mars - Reaction     
    <li>Lakeswim - Update     
    <li>Dog Home            
    <li>Oldest Woman        
    <li>Health - Hidden Fat    
    <li>Jobs            
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Health Coalition</b><p>
 A coalition of some 80 citizen groups across the province, are demanding an immediate moratorium on health care cuts until full public hearings are held. The groups accuse the Harris government of placing profit ahead of people's health needs. 
<hr>
<b>Smog Shots</b><p>
 Meanwhile health officials are continuing to advise people to take precautions in this heat and pollution... even young healthy people.  Cut back on exercising, drink plenty of fluids - and no - alcohol doesn't count...<br>   Stay indoors away from the heat and humidity ... you cannot escape the chemical toxins in the air by retreating indoors, but if you stay out of the heat you are at least relieving one stress factor.<br>   An air-quality advisory is expected to remain in effect for most of southern Ontario today and into tomorrow. Conditions have worsened since this morning...<br>  It is considered to be poor in Niagara Falls, London and Sarnia.. Moderate in St. Catharines, Hamilton and Oshawa. In Toronto it swings from poor to very good.
<hr>
<b>Mars - Reaction</b><p>
<br> Well given what we are doing to our environment here on planet Earth... the latest research involving the planet Mars might be good news... there is evidence today that the red planet did in fact at one time, support life. The evidence comes from a group of NASA funded scientists... but other space scientists say no way...<br>  And as Jamie West tells us.. the issue has some theologians revisiting traditional religious thinking about life's origins...<br> 
<i><br>  We're not talking about little green men...but tiny microfossils dating back 4.5 billion years, found in a rock catapulted from Mars 16 million years ago...<br>  That landed on earth in the antarctic 13-thousand years ago...<br>  Scientists have been probing the meteorite named Allan Hills 84001 since it's discovery in 1984.<br>  Hamilton's McMaster University holds an original piece of that same meteorite.  Weighing about 30 grams it's valued at over 30-thousand dollars, and says Doug Welch it's the real thing, as are NASA's findings...<br>  
Theology professor Dr. Clark Pinnock says god might have had more going on than originally thought and he's not threatened in anyway by the findings...<br>  But even those that took part in the research are quick to point out that more work needs to be done to find a definitive answer.<br>  </i>
<hr>
<b>Lakeswim - Update</b><p>
<br> Back on this planet... an effort to cross Lake Ontario came up a bit short. <br>  So close and yet so far... Toronto police officer John Munro had to abandon his attempt to swim across Lake Ontario because of nausea and a pain in his left shoulder. Munro's swim ended early this morning... after he battled the pain and nausea for more than four hours. He was brought to shore by his wife marathon swimmer Vicki Keith.<br>   Munro has been treated and released from hospital.<br> He says he is disappointed but he gave it his best shot... he went into the water at Niagara on the Lake and swam for twenty two hours.  He was raising money for big chill, a youth anti-violence program.
<hr>
<b>Dog Home</b><p>
 <br>  Holly the Irish Setter has limped home to an emotional reunion with her original owners. Susan Burnett of Markham says Holly, who made national headlines in a dog abuse case, sniffed through the whole house -- making sure everything was where it should be. Meanwhile, 66-year-old Maureen Cook, accused of abusing Holly by dragging her behind a car, appeared in an Orangeville court yesterday. The case was set over until September 3rd. Burnett says they decided to board Holly with Cook several months ago when their home was about to undergo renovations.
<hr>
<b>Oldest Woman</b><p>
<br>     A woman, believed to be the oldest person in the United States, has died. Mary Thompson was 120.  She had a heart attack yesterday in Orlando, Florida. Thompson credited her long life to minding her own business. She outlived two husbands and eight of her 10 children.
<hr>
<b>Health - Hidden Fat</b><p>
 Another warning about fat for you tonight...<br>   A US consumer group says the saturated fat that's listed on nutrition labels tells only part of the story.<br>   The Center For Science in the Public Interest says what the label doesn't show is the amount of so-called "trans fats."<br>   Trans fats are created when vegetable oil is hardened by a process called hydrogenation.<br>   The Centre for Science in the Public Interest claims trans fats or hydrogenated oils raise the levels of bad cholesterol in the blood -- and raise your risk of heart attack.
<hr>
<b>Jobs </b><p>
<br>     Prime minister Chretien says governments -- with their deficits -- can't be expected to bear the brunt of job creating -- but the private sector must.<br>   Chretien made his comment at the start of a two-day Liberal caucus session being held to prepare for the fall sitting of parliament.<br>   Chretien is insisting that his government has the right economic policies, especially with interest rates at a two-year low.<br> He also expects a drop in the unemployment numbers.<br>  



<P>
