<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 08/06/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Tuesday, August 6, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>


<ul>
    <li>Air Quality    
    <li>Olympic Athletes    
    <li>Munro Swim          
    <li>Social Caseload     
    <li>Caribana Shooting   
    <li>Dog Woman           
    <li>Callbeck Resigns    
    <li>Manitoba Abortion   
    <li>UK Abortion         
    <li>Olympic Bomb        
    <li>TWA Crash           
    <li>Bosnia Agreement    
    <li>Russia-Tues.         
    <li>Diana Dishes        
</ul>
<hr>
<b>Air Quality</b><p>
 Hot hazy humid weather has southern Ontario in it's grips for the first time this summer.<br>  There are concerns that those with breathing problems like asthma may suffer at the hands of something called photochemical smog.  The concoction is created from high levels of air pollutants mixing with bright sunshine.<br>  There is now an air quality advisory issued for most of southern Ontario and a humidex warning as temperatures begin to soar into the mid-thirties.. and in some spots in southern Ontario today, as high as forty...<br>  Medical professionals are warning that the best way to deal with the heat and smog is to stay out of it....
<hr>
<b>Olympic Athletes</b><p>
<br>  Hundreds of fans didn't let the heat stand in the way of giving Canada's Olympic rowers a hero's welcome home.<br>  They cheered heartily as gold medalists Marnie Mcbean and Kathleen Heddle, silver medalist Derek Porter and the rest of the team were introduced.<br>  Canada's rowers captured six medals at the olympics....one gold.. four silver and a bronze. It made the canadians the top rowing nation in the world.
<hr>
<b>Munro Swim</b><p>
<br>  A Toronto police officer is setting out to prove he has as much potential for marathon swimming as his wife.<br>  John Munro, the husband of Vicki Keith, is trying to swim across Lake Ontario.<br>  He's now about halfway there.<br>  Conditions are said to be good, and Munro is doing fine so far.<br>  The swim is a fundraiser for chill power, an education program aimed at preventing youth violence.<br>  Lauran Sabourin reports.
<BR>
<i>
John Munro was getting greased up by an expert.<br>  His wife Vicki Keith was helping him prepare to swim across Lake Ontario from Niagara on the Lake to Toronto.<br>  
John Munro wanted to be a marathon runner but knee problems forced him to give up training.<br>  Swimming allows him to attempt that marathon dream. <br>  
John Munro waded into the waters off Niagara on the Lake.<br>  His wife Vicki positioned in a kayak beside him. <br>  Using slow plodding strokes John Munro is heading for Vicki Keith Point near Leslie Street on the Toronto waterfront.<br>  The lake temperature is about 23 degress.<br>  The waters are calm.<br>  Munro is hoping to reach his goal sometime tomorrow morning.<br>  </i>
<hr>
<b>Social Caseload</b><p>
<br>  Another plunge for ontario's social assistance caseload.<br>  Social Services Minister David Tsubouchi has announced more than 11-thousand people received welfare or family benefits cheques last month.<br>  That amounts to a percentage drop of about 1 per cent.<br>  Tsubouchi says the drop reflects seasonal employment changes and the effects of his government's welfare reforms.
<hr>

<b>Caribana Shooting</b><p>
<br>  Police are working on a new lead in last weekend's Caribana shooting.<br>  23 year old Elrick Christian was shot to death during a parade along toronto's waterfront.<br>  Friends of Christian say they know who the killer is, and have given police the name.<br>  No arrests have been made yet.<br>  three other people were injured, two of them seriously.
<hr>
<b>Dog Woman</b><p>
<br>  The Irish setter dragged behind a car on this rural road in Shelburn is back with her original owners in Thornhill tonight.<br>  The family had given the dog up because of allergies, but took her back after 66 year old Maureen Cook was charged with causing unnecessary pain to the animal.<br>  Cook's case has been set over until September 3rd.
<hr>
<b>Callbeck Resigns</b><p>
<br>  The premier of Prince Edward Island is calling it quits.<br>  Catherine Callbeck has also announced she's stepping down as leader of that province's Liberal party.<br>  Callbeck says she has spent the summer soul-searching and decided it was time to leave politics.
<hr>
<b>Manitoba Abortion</b><p>
<br>  A landmark ruling out of Winnipeg this afternoon.<br>  A judge has forced a pregnant woman into a treatment program, because her glue sniffing addiction threatens her unborn child.<br>  The judge says he will give reasons for his decision in a few days.
<hr>
<b>UK Abortion</b><p>
<br>  A shocking twist to the case of a British woman carrying twins who wanted to abort one of the fetuses.<br>  Just as anti abortion groups won a court order preventing her from doing so, a hospital in London confirms the woman has already undergone the procedure.<br>  A fertility specialist says one fetus was aborted about five months ago.
<hr>
<b>Olympic Bomb</b><p>
<br>  More questions surrounding Atlanta security guard Richard Jewell.<br>  While searching his apartment, investigators have found fragments from the Centennial Olympic Park bomb explosion.<br>  Jewell's lawyer says the material was given to him by other security officials as a souvenir, several days after the bombing.<br>  He has not been charged.
<hr>
<b>TWA Crash</b><p>
<br>  Crews searching for debris from TWA flight 800 have found luggage at the bottom of the ocean, closer to New York's Kennedy Airport than the main crash site.<br>  That could add to the theory that there was an explosion in or near the jumbo jet's forward cargo hold.<br>  The plane crashed in a huge fireball July 17th after taking off for Paris.<br>  All 230 people aboard were killed.
<hr>
<b>Bosnia Agreement</b><p>
<br>  After days of tough negotiations, Bosnian Croats and Muslims have agreed to govern the city of Mostar together.<br>  The European union has administered the city since 1994.<br>  The agreement could be an important step in solidifying peace in Bosnia, and could pave the way for the withdrawal of Nato-led peacekeeping forces.
<hr>
<b>Russia-Tues.</b><p>
<br>  The largest rebel attack in months is underway in the breakaway Russian region of Chechnya.<br>  The attack coincides with Russian president Boris Yeltsin's first day back at the kremlin since going into seclusion three weeks ago.<br>  
<hr>
<b>Diana Dishes</b><p>
<br>  Another astounding revelation about Diana, princess of wales, has hit the british tabloids.<br> The rags are spouting about how she washed dishes and helped clean out a cupboard at the home of her former lover, James Hewitt.<br>  Hewitt's mother spilled the beans in a magazine interview, for which she was reportedly paid 95-thousand dollars Canadian.<br>  Mrs. Hewitt says she became aware of the couple's interest in each other when Diana's visits to the home became regular.<br>  Diana's divorce from Prince Charles becomes final on August 28th.



<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

