<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 07/19/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, July 19, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>TWA 
<LI>Suicide Study 
<LI>Olympic Wrap 
<LI>Salmon Fishery 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>TWA </H3>

<P>
Sources are now quoted as saying it was -- in all likelihood --
a bomb. CBS and CNN report the probe of the TWA explosion off
Long Island, New York, will be handed over to criminal investigators
later today. The networks say sources indicate that &quot;any
possible mechanical malfunction or meltdown&quot; has been virtually
eliminated. 
<P>
All 230 people aboard TWA flight-800 were killed when the plane
exploded, sending debris and bodies into the Atlantic Wednesday
night. 
<HR>

<H3>Suicide Study </H3>

<P>
A crown prosecutor says the first Canadian doctor to be charged
with assisting a suicide could go to trial this fall. 
<P>
AIDS specialist Maurice Generics is charged in connection with
the April suicide of a 31-year-old Toronto man. 
<P>
Meanwhile, a Toronto mother has raised one million dollars to
conduct a study of suicide.
<HR>

<H3>Olympic Wrap </H3>

<P>
Security is tight for tonight's opening Olympic ceremonies in
Atlanta. Organizers are using 30-thousand police officers, soldiers
and private security guards. And security measures increased yesterday
at the city's main airport, after the TWA disaster. 
<P>
Prime minister Chretien will have lunch with some of the Canadian
athletes today and attend tonight's gala opening, which is being
televised around the world. 
<HR>

<H3>Salmon Fishery </H3>

<P>
The annual Chinook Classic Salmon Derby gets underway on Lake
Ontario tomorrow. Anglers will compete for over 40-thousand dollars
in prizes over the next two weeks. 
<P>
As Jamie west reports tonight ...the big lunkers are becoming
harder to find, and that's putting the pinch on charter boat operators
who say provincial cutbacks are partially to blame... 
<P>
<I>Mike Dumenil operates his fishing charter business out fifty
point marina.... his competitor Dan Smith is along for the ride.
</I>
<P>
<I>Over the last decade the Ontario government has reduced it's
stocks of Chinook salmon...Lake Ontario's biggest draw for anglers
and of course money maker for charter businesses. Another problem
is the number of lamprey eels depleting fish stocks...again there
have been cutbacks to a plan to get rid of them. </I>
<P>
<I>So now an electronic fish finder is the captain's first mate
in efforts to keep clients happy. These operators admit a slow
spring has set the season back by about three weeks but they're
optimistic the 40-thousand dollar Derby will still be a success.</I>



<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

