<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 07/17/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, July 17, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Hepatitis B 
<LI>Child Rapist 
<LI>Police Lawsuit 
<LI>Homeless Demo 
<LI>Snobelen Panel 
<LI>Canadian Military 
<LI>Saudi U.S. 
<LI>R. Downey Arrest 
<LI>Stallone Shooting 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Hepatitis B </H3>

<P>
Health officials say there is little danger that a Hepatitis-B
outbreak in the Toronto area, will spread to other areas of Ontario.
But to be on the safe side, the Harris government plans to introduce
a province-wide Hepatitis-B vaccination program soon. 
<HR>

<H3>Child Rapist </H3>

<P>
A 13-year-old girl who says she was gang raped by four boys, broke
down on the witness stand at a Toronto trial. 
<P>
Testifying in a barely audible voice, the girl told the court
how the boys held her down during the attack in mid-May. She kept
telling them she wanted to go home. 
<P>
Two boys, aged 13 and 15, are on trial in youth court. Two other
boys, 10 and 11, are too young to be charged. The trial has been
adjourned until August. 
<HR>

<H3>Police Lawsuit </H3>

<P>
Toronto police are being sued by the family of a man who was shot
and killed by officers last month. The parents of Wayne Williams
also want a judge to force officers involved in the shooting,
to co-operate with the special investigations unit. 
<P>
The 24-year-old man was killed after officers responded to complaints
a man was smashing car windows. The officers have not spoken to
investigators and only recently handed over their notes. 
<HR>

<H3>Homeless Demo </H3>

<P>
&quot;We told you so&quot;. That to the larger extent was the
message today from a group that calls itself the &quot;Bread Not
Circuses Coalition&quot;. 
<P>
The group held a news conference outside coroners court in Toronto,
where an inquest into the deaths of three homeless people is being
conducted. Coalition members say they were right in 1990, when
they predicted that homeless people would be mistreated had Toronto
succeeded in its bid to host this year's Olympics... they were
right, because that's what's happening south of the border. 
<P>
Many supporters of Toronto's Olympic bid blame the Bread Not Circuses
Coalition for the bid's failure. 
<HR>

<H3>Snobelen Panel </H3>

<P>
Education minister John Snobelen says Ontario may allow private
universities to grant degrees. Snobelen has set up a five-member
panel to examine the idea, which he says could help solve the
problem of too few spaces for a growing number of students. 
<P>
Other options the panel will consider, linking tuition to potential
earnings and encouraging partnerships between business and post
secondary institutions. 
<P>
The panel plans to hold a series of public hearings into the proposals
in September and October. 
<HR>

<H3>Canadian military </H3>

<P>
There are disturbing allegations tonight that Canadian peacekeepers
in Bosnia beat mental patients, held wild parties with nurses
and sold goods on the black market. 
<P>
Lieutenant-General Maurice (bah-reel) has called a military board
of inquiry into the incidents -- and vows any officers involved
will face disciplinary action. The alleged misconduct occurred
during 1993 and 1994, and involved members of the 12th armored
regiment, based at Valcartier, near Quebec city. 
<HR>

<H3>Saudi U.S. </H3>

<P>
American troops in Saudi Arabia face a &quot;very intense threat&quot;
from terrorists. And defence secretary William Perry says the
threat includes a possible attack with chemical or biological
weapons. The heightened alarm over terrorist threats may force
the U.S. military to move up to four-thousand of the American
troops now stationed in Saudi Arabia. 
<HR>

<H3>R. Downey Arrest </H3>

<P>
Actor Robert Downey Junior is in trouble with the law again. Just
hours after getting slapped with drug charges, he was found passed
out in a stranger's house in California. 
<P>
The 31 year old Downey has been booked for investigation of trespassing
and being under the influence of drugs. 
<HR>

<H3>Stallone Shooting </H3>

<P>
Police call it a case of guard-versus -guard at Sylvester Stallone's
Miami estate. One security guard is in critical condition after
being shot and stabbed in a clash early today. Investigators say
he was hurt when he foiled a break-in by a second guard. 


<P>
