<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 07/08/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, July 8, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>London School Attack 
<LI>Middleton 
<LI>401 Accident 
<LI>Labor Strikes 
<LI>Native 
<LI>Irish Demo 
<LI>Sharon Appointment 
<LI>AIDS Conference 
<LI>Wescam - Olympics 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>London School Attack </H3>

<P>
British police say at least seven people were hurt when a man
armed with a machete or an ax went on a rampage at a school in
England. 
<P>
It happened in Wolverhampton, about 95 kilometres northwest of
London. A witness to the attack says three adults and four children
were taken to hospital with varying degrees of stab wounds. A
hospital official says one adult and one child are seriously wounded.

<HR>

<H3>Middleton </H3>

<P>
Family and friends of Rebecca Middleton, the 17 year old Belleville
student who was brutally raped and murdered in Bermuda last week,
paid their last respects today. 
<P>
Middleton's blood stained body was found by passersby early Wednesday
morning. She had been hitch-hiking with a friend near the tourist
town of St. George, and was last seen accepting a ride from two
men on motorcycles. 
<P>
Rebecca, a grade 11 student, left her home in Belleville June
20th for a six week holiday with a friend. 
<HR>

<H3>401 Accident </H3>

<P>
Thousands of commuters from east of Toronto were late for work
today. A tractor-trailer crash in Ajax blocked the westbound lanes
of the 401 during the peak of this morning's rush hour. 
<P>
One of the trucks burst into flames, however neither driver was
injured. At one point, traffic was backed up about six kilometres
from Ajax to Whitby. 
<HR>

<H3>Labor Strikes </H3>

<P>
And traffic was also re-routed in various cities across the province,
during the series of day-long strikes, organized by Ontario's
labour movement. But those strikes may soon grind to a halt following
a ruling today by the Ontario Labor Relations Board, deeming one
of those strikes illegal. 
<HR>

<H3>Native</H3>

<P>
The grand chief of the Assembly of First Nations, is urging a
more militant stance in relations with Canada's governments. 
<P>
Ovide Mercredi is calling on native leaders to push for sovereignty-
association with Canada. But at the assembly's annual meeting
in Ottawa today, he also cautioned against violence. 
<P>
Mercredi says aboriginal peoples simply don't have the strength
to confront the power, available to national and provincial governments.

<HR>

<H3>Irish Demo </H3>

<P>
There has been a second day of violence in northern Ireland. Protestants
determined to march through a roman catholic enclave, tossed rocks,
bottles and firecrackers at riot police today. 
<P>
Police fired back with plastic bullets when protesters tried to
cut through barbed wire barriers. 
<HR>

<H3>Sharon Appointment </H3>

<P>
One of Israel's biggest hawks is back in political life. Israeli
prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu has appointed Ariel Sharon to
his cabinet -- as minister of national infrastructure. 
<P>
The appointment has caused an uproar in Israel and comes on the
heels of yet another controversy, involving Netanyahu's wife,
and a former nanny. 
<HR>

<H3>AIDS Conference</H3>

<P>
A sobering prediction at the International AIDS Conference in
Vancouver. Projections released today show the number of people
worldwide infected with the aids virus is expected to double in
less than four years. 
<P>
The projections indicate that by the turn of the century, about
44-million people will fall victim to HIV. But not all news coming
out of the conference is bad.
<HR>

<H3>Wescam - Olympics </H3>

<P>
In eleven days the eyes of the world will be focused on the Olympic
games in Atlanta. And as Lauran Sabourin reports a Hamilton area
company will be providing the perspective through which the world
will watch the event. 
<P>
<I>Fifteen thousand athletes and coaches. Two million spectators.
Three billion television viewers. And those viewers will be watching
with the technology of Wescam. </I>
<P>
<I>Wescam technology will allow the world to see the athletes
close up. The physical exertion. The elation. The disappointment.
</I>
<P>
<I>On a much larger scale the Atlanta games represent the most
ambitious civilian telecommunications venture since the space
program. This level and scale of technology have never been attempted
before. </I>
<P>
<I>This is the largest presence Wescam will have at the Olympic
games. This year the company will be operating at 19 different
venues, and will have the bragging rights within their industry
that they were at the 96 Olympics.</I>


<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

