<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 06/10/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, June 10, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Harnick-Victims 
<LI>Patient Threats 
<LI>Another Slaying 
<LI>Stabbing Death 
<LI>Women's March 
<LI>Clark Hamilton 
<LI>Strike-Replacements 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Harnick-Victims</H3>

<P>
Attorney General Charles Harnick announced today, the government
will spend 10.2-million dollars to give more help to victims of
violent crime. It includes a voice mail system which gives instant
up dates on the progress of victims cases.
<HR>

<H3>Patient Threats </H3>

<P>
Doctor-patient confidentiality rules could soon change to protect
the public from people who threaten to seriously harm or kill.

<P>
The Ontario College of Physicians and Surgeons is considering
a recommendation to change the system so doctors told of such
plans would be compelled to notify police and the intended victim.
Right now, doctors who violate patient confidentiality can face
disciplinary action. There are exceptions, such as child abuse
cases. 
<HR>

<H3>Another Slaying </H3>

<P>
A man who was shot Toronto during the weekend died of a gunshot
wound to the chest. Police released the autopsy results today
in the death of 20-year-old Lawrence Hickling. His 30-year-old
friend was also shot and is in serious condition in hospital.

<P>
No suspects have been arrested in the shooting that occurred during
an argument early yesterday. 
<HR>

<H3>Stabbing Death </H3>

<P>
A suspect in the fatal stabbing of a teenager at a Toronto subway
station has had his case put over to next week. 
<P>
Seventeen-year- old Michael Amann-Ewaschuk was stabbed in the
chest during a confrontation with several young people last Friday.
Twenty- one-year-old Chad Little of Toronto is charged with second-degree
murder. He appeared in court today and had his case put over until
Monday. 
<HR>

<H3>Women's March</H3>

<P>
Only days away from their final destination the National Women's
March Against Poverty stopped in the Niagara peninsula today.

<P>
Two bands of women, one from the east coast the other from the
west have been traveling across the country shouting about the
injustice of poverty. And as Lauran Sabourin reports these women
are delivering their message while rocking and rolling towards
the nation's capital. 
<P>
<I>They arrived in Welland this morning looking a little haggard.
Seven women from eastern Canada who've spent weeks on the road
telling people who will listen how women are paying the price
for policies that discriminate against them. </I>
<P>
<I>1996 has been designated by the United Nations as the year
of eradicating poverty. The participants at this rally are only
speaking about poverty. So many people are living it. Monthly
welfare checks may cover the rent, but little else, while the
poor try to stretch what few dollars the have. </I>
<P>
<I>The anti poverty caravan is continuing to roll across the country.</I>

<HR>

<H3>Clark Hamilton </H3>

<P>
Meanwhile, the battle for ballots in Hamilton East is going down
to the wire, and the candidates are playing out their trump cards.

<P>
This morning, the Conservatives' Angie Tomasic brought in former
Tory prime minister Joe Clark to speak on her behalf. Clark returned
to the issue of accountability, and maintained that sending Sheila
Copps back to Ottawa would give the grits the wrong message. 
<HR>

<H3>Strike-Replacements </H3>

<P>
A Toronto hotel is using replacement workers -- the first time
such workers have been brought across picket lines in Ontario
since a law banning them was scrapped by the Harris government.

<P>
The workers are doing the jobs of about 600 unionized employees
of the Westin Harbor Castle Hotel who went on strike over a wage
dispute this morning. A hotel manager notes replacement workers
were routinely used before the NDP legislation. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

<CENTER>| <A HREF="../archive/">Return To The News Archive Page</A> |
<A HREF="/">Return To The CHCH Home Page</A> |</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>| Questions or comments? <A HREF="mailto:news@chch.wic.ca">news@chch.wic.ca</A>
|</CENTER>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER><I>Updated: June 10, 1996</I></CENTER> 

</BODY>

