<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 06/06/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, June 6, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Kid Beatings 
<LI>Ottawa Mom Charged 
<LI>Groin-Kitchener 
<LI>Booze Taxes 
<LI>Martin - Labor 
<LI>Israel Palestinians 
<LI>Diana Chicago 
<LI>Fergie Book 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Kid Beatings </H3>

<P>
Ontario's minister of corrections says a full investigation is
under way into allegations that teenage prisoners were beaten
by guards, following a riot at the Bluewater Youth Centre near
Goderich. 
<HR>

<H3>Ottawa Mom Charged</H3>

<P>
The mother of a newborn boy, who had a lead pellet removed from
his brain, has been charged with attempted murder. 
<P>
Reports tonight state Brenda Drummond, who is in her late 20's,
was taken into police custody this afternoon. Police have said
they were investigating whether the eight-day-old boy was shot
in the head with a pellet while still inside his mother's womb.
The little boy was in critical but stable condition in an Ottawa
hospital. 
<HR>

<H3>Groin-Kitchener </H3>

<P>
A Kitchener woman is in police custody tonight, in a case that
resembles the highly publicized Lorena Bobbitt case. 
<P>
Kitchener Waterloo Regional Police, say they responded to a 9-1-1
call and found a 50 year old man bleeding from his genitals. The
man's 42 year old common-law wife has been charged with aggravated
assault. 
<P>
The man was scheduled for surgery this afternoon. 
<HR>

<H3>Booze Taxes </H3>

<P>
The Ontario Restaurant Association and representatives from Canadian
distilleries, called on the Harris government today to lower provincial
taxes on booze. The delegation delivered a beer-barrel with over
17-thousand coasters signed by restaurant and bar patrons in the
Windsor area, asking the province to reduce the 85 per-cent tax
on liquor. 
<P>
In accepting the petition, Isabel Bassett, parliamentary assistant
to finance minister Ernie Eves, pointed out that Ontario can't
act alone, since liquor taxing is a joint federal- provincial
matter. The delegation indicated that the high taxes have been
partly responsible for some 19 distilleries closing over the past
18-years. 
<HR>

<H3>Martin - Labor </H3>

<P>
Paul Martin says he and his cabinet colleagues went through the
&quot;tortures of the damned&quot; to find a satisfactory alternative
to the GST. 
<P>
The finance minister told the Canadian Federation of Labor meeting
in Ottawa that 20 options were examined while the government still
felt it was possible to bring in a replacement tax. But he said
Canadians just didn't want to have to adjust to a different kind
of tax. 
<HR>

<H3>Israel Palestinians </H3>

<P>
In world news tonight, incoming Israeli prime minister Benjamin
Netanyahu is asking Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat to tone down
the rhetoric over Palestinian independence. 
<HR>

<H3>Diana Chicago </H3>

<P>
It's Princess Diana's last day in Chicago. 
<P>
This morning, the princess visited a hospice at Northwest Memorial
Hospital, where she met with a patient. Next it was on to an awards
luncheon... her royal highness is scheduled to board a flight
back to England, later this afternoon. 
<HR>

<H3>Fergie Book</H3>

<P>
Another estranged royal is visiting the big apple, apparently
in search of a career change. The newly-divorced Sarah Ferguson,
&quot;ex&quot; to prince Andrew, and the ex-duchess of York, is
getting set to tell all in what's being billed as an &quot;adult
book&quot;. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

