<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/30/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, May 30, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Hostage Taking 
<LI>Palma Wanted 
<LI>Baltovich Denies 
<LI>Mcdonough-GST. 
<LI>Israel Elect 
<LI>N. Ireland Elect 
<LI>Royal Divorce 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Hostage Taking </H3>

<P>
It's a waiting game for the mounties in southeastern BC. An armed
couple -- sought in connection with violent crimes in Alberta
-- is holding a pregnant woman hostage in a home outside Cranbrook.

<P>
RCMP sergeant Peter Montague says the main concern is the delicate
condition of hostage Leanne Campbell. Her baby is due in about
a week. 
<P>
The standoff began yesterday after a Mountie wearing a bullet-proof
vest was shot and wounded as he approached the house. 
<HR>

<H3>Palma Wanted </H3>

<P>
A continent wide warrant has been issued for a man wanted in connection
with the slaying of three Toronto prostitutes. 
<P>
Police are seeking 30-year-old Marcello Palma of Toronto. Palma
is married and the father of a 15-month-old child. 
<P>
The three prostitutes were shot to death in downtown Toronto during
the Victoria Day weekend. Police say Palma, who is considered
armed and dangerous, may be heading to Montreal. 
<HR>

<H3>Baltovich Denies </H3>

<P>
A Toronto man who has spent five years in prison for the murder
of his former girlfriend, says he didn't do it and is now pointing
a finger at Paul Bernardo. 
<P>
Papers filed with the Ontario Court of Appeal, include fresh evidence
in the case of Robert Baltovich who was convicted of second-degree
murder in the presumed death of Elizabeth Bain. Bain vanished
in 1990 ... her body was never found. 
<P>
The new evidence submitted last week does not name Bernardo, but
it makes reference to evidence presented at a trial concerning
the Scarborough rapist. Bernardo has admitted to a string of assaults
blamed on the Scarborough rapist -- the last about the time Bain
vanished. 
<HR>

<H3>Mcdonough-GST</H3>

<P>
In the federal by-election in Hamilton east, New Democrats claim
to be in second spot behind Sheila Copps. 
<P>
Today, the federal NDP leader came to Hamilton to help with the
campaign. While here, Alexa Mcdonough unveiled her party's plan
to get rid of the tax that triggered the by-election... the dreaded
GST. 
<P>
<I>Hamilton labour leader Wayne Marston wants to be the federal
member of parliament for Hamilton east. And he thinks the June
17th by-election caused by the sudden resignation of Sheila Copps
is his ticket. </I>
<P>
<I>Marston was joined in the campaign by federal party leader
Alexa Mcdonough. They canvassed the riding saying a vote for Sheila
is a vote for the GST. </I>
<P>
<I>At an earlier news conference, Mcdonough unveiled a four point
NDP program to kill the federal sales tax. Stop the proposed harmonization
which she says favours corporations. Ease the burden immediately
by removing the tax from items such as new homes and kids clothes.
A family of four would save 270 dollars a year. Undertake a national
taxation review. And as a first step, further ease the burden
by dropping the GST to five percent. </I>
<P>
<I>They know that in a field of 13 candidates, being number two
doesn't count.</I> 
<HR>

<H3>Israel Elect </H3>

<P>
Israeli opposition leader Benjamin Netanyahu promises peace talks
won't end if he takes power. He has a slim lead in Israel's election
for prime minister. 
<P>
Netanyahu is expected to slow the pace of negotiations. But he
says he'll honor all signed agreements. 
<HR>

<H3>N. Ireland Elect </H3>

<P>
Protestants and Catholics in northern Ireland took part today
in elections which were meant to find a way to peace. The vote
was held to decide which parties should represent them in northern
Ireland's long-delayed peace negotiations. But there was little
optimism evident as voters battled driving rain and gusting winds
to trudge into polling stations. 
<P>
The vote count won't take place until tomorrow. 
<HR>

<H3>Royal Divorce </H3>

<P>
Andrew and Fergie are officially single again. Following a ten
year, highly publicized marriage, the Duke and Duchess of York
received a final decree of divorce today. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

