<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/29/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, May 29, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Ipperwash-Secret 
<LI>Reform 
<LI>Israeli Elect 
<LI>N. Ireland Elect 
<LI>Shuttle Returns 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Ipperwash-Secret </H3>

<P>
Ontario premier Mike Harris and attorney general Charles Harnick
are denying they ordered police to force native protesters from
a provincial park, one day before a demonstrator was shot dead
by police. 
<HR>

<H3>Reform </H3>

<P>
As we reported earlier... Reform party leader Preston Manning
parachuted into Hamilton east today in support of local by-election
candidate Andy Sweck. 
<P>
He met with polish business leaders at a Barton Street restaurant...
telling them that the campaign is about jobs, crime and political
accountability. 
<P>
Later, he told students at Scott Park Secondary School that the
Young Offenders Act needs a major overhaul... that teen-aged criminals
prey on teen-aged victims. 
<HR>

<H3>Israeli Elect </H3>

<P>
Israel's ruling party and its leader have the early lead in a
crucial election, but it's too close to call. 
<P>
TV exit polls say that in the direct election for prime minister,
incumbent Shimon Peres has a slight advantage over challenger
Benjamin Netanyahu. The exit polls also indicate the Labor party
of Peres could win slightly more seats in parliament than the
opposition liked.
<HR>

<H3>N. Ireland Elect </H3>

<P>
Voters in Northern Ireland meanwhile, head to the polls tomorrow..
to elect candidates who will take part in next month's peace negotiations
for the province. 
<HR>

<H3>Shuttle Returns </H3>

<P>
The Space Shuttle &quot;endeavour&quot; and its six astronauts
had a picture perfect landing in Florida this morning. 
<P>
The 10-day mission which included Canadian mission specialist
Marc Garneau, was highlighted by the release of two test satellites.
Patchy ground fog and clouds over the landing site, had threatened
to delay the landing or send the shuttle to Edwards Air Force
Base in California. But the weather cleared and mission control
in Houston gave the go-ahead for its Florida return. 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

