<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/24/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, May 24, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Kennedy - Liberals 
<LI>Chretien Poll 
<LI>Mulroney - Court 
<LI>CBC 
<LI>Life Expectancy 
<LI>Food Moods 
<LI>Personal Ponds 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Kennedy-Liberals </H3>

<P>
The Ontario Tories received a vote of non-confidence in the first
by-election since they came to power. Instead, the voters in the
Toronto area riding of York South elected a liberal. It's the
riding which used to be held by former NDP leader Bob Rae. 
<P>
Yesterday's winner is Gerard Kennedy. He's a political newcomer,
but his name is already being mentioned as a potential candidate
for leader.
<HR>

<H3>Chretien Poll </H3>

<P>
The prime minister is downplaying a bad-news poll out today. Jean
Chretien says he doesn't work around the polls. 
<P>
The Gallup Survey marks the first time since Chretien became prime
minister in 1993, that fewer than half of Canadians polled approved
of his handling of the job. It suggests that 47 per cent of Canadians
approve of the government's performance, compared with 36 per
cent who disapprove. 
<HR>

<H3>Mulroney - Court </H3>

<P>
Federal lawyers must file their statement of defence as ordered
by the judge in Brian Mulroney's 50-million dollar libel suit.

<P>
A bid by federal authorities for a postponement has been rejected
in the Quebec Court of Appeal. Lawyers representing the federal
government feared outlining their defence, would hinder the RCMP
investigation into the airbus affair. But justice Marie Deschamps
threw out the request, saying the arguments weren't convincing.

<HR>

<H3>CBC </H3>

<P>
The budget-ravaged CBC now turns to fine-tuning a leaner future.
The public broadcaster reached last-minute contract deals with
its three unions early today, narrowly averting a strike by seven-thousand
employees. 
<P>
Terms of the tentative contracts were not disclosed. Job security
was the major issue during negotiations, specifically CBC demands
for more contracting-out. 
<HR>

<H3>Life Expectancy </H3>

<P>
The latest survey from Statistics Canada shows Canadian life expectancy
was at an all time high in 1994. But despite the fact that people
are living longer the cancer rates are soaring. 
<HR>

<H3>Food Moods </H3>

<P>
At one time or another, many of us have turned to a special food
or beverage when we're feeling a little low. Food can affect your
mood, by influencing chemicals in the brain. One of the best snacks
for a good night's sleep is cereal, milk and a banana.
<HR>

<H3>Personal Ponds</H3>

<P>
Aquatic animals are evaporating. Study after study shows fish,
frogs and other creatures are disappearing.. as animals lose habitat
to development. But some people are trying to give a little space
back to wildlife-- right in their own backyards. 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

