<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/23/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, May 23, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Foreman Evng 
<LI>Burloak Evng 
<LI>Hooker Evng 
<LI>York South - Debt 
<LI>CUPE - Ontario Labour 
<LI>CBC - Negotiations 
<LI>Euthanasia Nurses 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Foreman Evng</H3>

<P>
A jury has convicted a former Kitchener nursing student of first-degree
murder in the shotgun slaying of his ex-girlfriend. 
<P>
Joan Heimbecker died of multiple gunshot wounds, in her McMaster
University residence two years ago. Joan's family and friends,
who faithfully attended the month-long trial in Hamilton, wept
as 25-year-old Rory Foreman was pronounced guilty. 
<P>
Before he was sentenced to life in prison, Foreman apologized
in court to Joan's parents and sister, saying Joan's murder was
a selfish, cruel and cowardly act.
<HR>

<H3>Burloak Evng </H3>

<P>
Police say a 14-year-old Burlington boy charged with murdering
another teen knew the victim. The accused was charged after the
body of 14-year-old Lee Doherty was found yesterday in an Oakville
park. 
<P>
Police say Doherty was beaten to death with a blunt object, probably
a crow bar. 
<HR>

<H3>Hooker Evng </H3>

<P>
Hookers working the streets of downtown Toronto say they're living
in fear after the deaths of three prostitutes. 
<P>
Police say a 25 year old woman, a male transvestite and a transsexual
hooker were all shot, with the same gun -- execution-style in
the back of the head. Police say it's too early to say a serial
killer is on the streets, but they won't rule it out. 
<HR>

<H3>York South - Debt </H3>

<P>
Mike Harris and his common sense revolution are facing the first
test at the polls. A provincial by-election is taking place today
in the riding last held by former NDP leader Bob Rae. 
<P>
The candidates for the major parties are Conservative Rob Davis,
Liberal Gerard Kennedy and New Democrat David Miller. The by-election
is seen as a test of the popularity of the Harris cuts in taxes
and spending.
<HR>

<H3>CUPE - Ontario Labour </H3>

<P>
The labor movement meanwhile, isn't going to sit idly by and watch
the government turn back the clock 50 years. That was the message
Canadian Labor Congress president Bob White delivered at the Canadian
Union of Public Employees convention in Niagara Falls today.
<HR>

<H3>CBC - Negotiations</H3>

<P>
It's getting down to the eleventh hour for the CBC and seven-thousand
radio and t-v workers. A strike deadline will hit at one minute
before midnight and there's still no contract agreement. 
<P>
Workers are protesting the broadcaster's plans to contract out
more work in its effort to cut costs.
<HR>

<H3>Euthanasia Nurses </H3>

<P>
A new study says some critical care nurses actively help their
patients die. That in spite of the fact that such activities may
violate professional ethics or the law. But the research is being
angrily disputed.
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

