<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/21/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Tuesday, May 21, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Twister-Niagara 
<LI>Timmins Flood 
<LI>Transvestite Slaying 
<LI>Garneau 
<LI>Debit Cards 
<LI>S.F. Quake 
<LI>Ferry Capsized 
<LI>Mafia Arrests 
<LI>Frozen Mummy 
<LI>Correction 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Twister-Niagara </H3>

<P>
Environment Canada says at least one tornado and possibly more
hit the Niagara- Brantford- Hamilton areas during severe thunderstorms
last night. 
<P>
When it was all over buildings were destroyed, and trees were
toppled. Miraculously no one was seriously injured. 
<HR>

<H3>Timmins Flood </H3>

<P>
The hoped-for good news turned bad today for people in Timmins.
Residents were hoping the worst was over and the swollen Mattagami
River would start subsiding. But officials say the river will
rise further, before the situation gets any better. That means
more families may have to flee their homes. Twenty families have
already had to re-locate. 
<HR>

<H3>Transvestite Slaying </H3>

<P>
Police believe there is a connection in the slayings of two young
men whose bodies were found in the same downtown Toronto neighborhood.

<P>
Both men, who were dressed in women's clothing, were shot to death
overnight. One was found in a stairwell of an apartment building,
while the other was discovered behind another apartment building
on the same street. Police believe the victims were prostitutes.

<HR>

<H3>Garneau </H3>

<P>
A Canadian has pulled off the toughest job of the day today up
in space, retrieving a satellite that had been deployed yesterday.
And Marc Garneau carried out the task flawlessly with the help
of the Canadian built robot known as the &quot;Canadarm&quot;.
<HR>

<H3>Debit Cards </H3>

<P>
A recent survey shows more and more Canadians are using debit
cards to pay for their purchases. 
<P>
New statistics indicate that the number of debit card transactions
has doubled over the past year.
<HR>

<H3>S.F. Quake </H3>

<P>
An earthquake has rattled much of northern California. The quake
jarred an area from Monterey Bay north to San Francisco and east
to Sacramento. 
<P>
The US geological survey puts the magnitude at 4.7 and the epicenter
about 15 kilometres east of San Jose. There is no immediate word
on damage or injuries. 
<HR>

<H3>Ferry Capsized </H3>

<P>
At least 500 people have drowned after a ferry hit a rock and
capsized in Lake Victoria, Africa. And survivors say many of the
victims were teenage students on their way home after the end
of school term. 
<P>
Radio Tanzania says only 40 people lived through the disaster.

<HR>

<H3>Mafia Arrests </H3>

<P>
Police have arrested one of Italy's most-wanted men, a reputed
Mafia terrorist. 
<P>
The man is thought to have killed a famous prosecutor and headed
the teams that planted car bombs that damaged a museum, two churches
and an art gallery in 1993. 
<HR>

<H3>Frozen Mummy </H3>

<P>
A frozen 500-year old mummy discovered in the mountains of Peru
was unveiled at National Geographic headquarters in Washington,
D.C. today. Scientists believe she gives the first look at the
life of Incan nobility...and their deadly rituals. 
<HR>

<H3>Correction </H3>

<P>
A correction tonight. 
<P>
On some of our newscasts yesterday, we incorrectly reported that
a &quot;rumble&quot; between rival motorcycle gangs broke out
at a Queens Park demonstration Sunday. In fact, there was a minor
altercation between two individual bike club members. 
<P>
We regret the mistake. 
<P>
The bikers were at Queens Park to protest what they call unfair
treatment by all levels of government. 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

