<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/16/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, May 16, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>
<UL>
<LI>Unity-Thursday 
<LI>Revolt 
<LI>Cayuga Missing 
<LI>Casino Poll 
<LI>Disabled Legislature 
<LI>Parks Ban 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Unity-Thursday </H3>

<P>
Unity ... has become the wound that will not heal ... here in
Canada ... and once again Quebec, and Ottawa ... are busy pouring
salt. 
<P>
Premier Lucien Bouchard appeared on ABC's &quot;Good Morning America&quot;,
this morning ... to take the offensive against prime minister
Jean Chretien. Bouchard told the audience that Chretien is in
complete disarray when it comes to the unity issue, and is desperately
trying to prevent a sovereigntist victory in Quebec. 
<P>
Chretien has said that Quebec cannot declare independence unilaterally,
and that a simple majority vote, will not be acceptable. Bouchard
says, those statements are simply &quot;awful&quot;. 
<P>
But in Ottawa; unity minister Stephane Dion stuck to the party
line, in reaction to Bouchard's interview. 
<HR>

<H3>Revolt </H3>

<P>
And yet another federal leader has problems of his own: the Toronto
Sun says, there's a move afoot to dump Preston Manning as the
leader of the federal Reform Party. 
<P>
But Manning and his supporters say, that's news to them. They
have dismissed the report saying it comes from disgruntled former
members of the Reform party. 
<HR>

<H3>Cayuga Missing </H3>

<P>
He's been missing for 13 years, but no one thought to notify police
about the disappearance of Robert Asher of Dunnville until February
of this year. As Kathy Renwald reports Cayuga OPP now have the
major crimes unit investigating the 13 year old mystery. 
<P>
<I>Robert Asher left Dunnville 13 years ago in a 1970 gold Pontiac
and there hasn't been a sighting of him since. </I>
<P>
<I>Cayuga OPP say he was estranged from his family ..left home
at 16 ..hung around in crash pads in downtown Dunnville. His parents
never reported him missing ..because he led a vagabond life. </I>
<P>
<I>But in February of this year 13 years after Robert Asher was
last seen police got a tip. Police admit this is the coldest of
trails, but anyone who has information on Robert Asher of Dunnville
is asked to call Cayuga OPP.</I> 
<HR>

<H3>Casino Poll </H3>

<P>
Is a turf war developing in Niagara Falls over the awarding of
a casino? The opposition is being mounted by residents living
near the Maple Leaf Village Casino and businesses on the other
side of town. 
<HR>

<H3>Disabled Legislature </H3>

<P>
Dozens of disabled people jammed the Ontario legislature this
afternoon, in a bid to bring home a message to Mike Harris. 
<P>
Advocates for the disabled say the Tories have failed to keep
an election promise to provide new legislation to protect Ontario
residents with disabilities. They packed the public galleries
to support NDP justice critic Marion Boyd, as she introduced a
private member's resolution for an all-party debate on the proposed
Ontarians with Disabilities Act. The motion was passed unanimously.

<HR>

<H3>Parks Ban </H3>

<P>
And, a warning from the Ontario government for those planning
to spend the holiday weekend, camping in a provincial park. 
<P>
There will be a complete ban on alcohol in all 29 provincial parks
over the Victoria Day weekend. That includes Long Point, Turkey
Point, and the Pinery, in southwestern Ontario. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

