<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/13/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, May 13, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Riot Inquiry 
<LI>Unity 
<LI>Ham. East Enumeration 
<LI>Chemical Fire 
<LI>Plane Follow 
<LI>Simpson England 
<LI>Jackie O Auction 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Riot Inquiry </H3>

<P>
The head of the inquiry into the March riot at Queen's Park says
he's not out to lay blame. Retired judge Willard Estey opened
the probe today into the ugly picket line confrontation during
the public service strike. 
<P>
Surprisingly, organized labour, which pressured for the inquiry,
didn't send a lawyer to the probe. 
<HR>

<H3>Unity </H3>

<P>
Quebec premier Lucien Bouchard has ruled out a snap election and
a possible referendum. But he says he will not be meeting, as
scheduled, with prime minister Chretien this week. 
<P>
Bouchard is incensed after Ottawa announced Friday it intends
to join a court challenge on the legality of separation. Treasury
board president Marcel Masse says the government will argue the
constitution should supersede any referendum on Quebec sovereignty.

<HR>

<H3>Ham. East Enumeration </H3>

<P>
Enumerators from Elections Canada are pounding the pavement in
Hamilton east... knocking on doors gathering information for the
voters' list for the June 17th federal by- election. 
<P>
Janice Turner and Chris Guitard are responsible for a three square
block area. They say that some people have them confused with
census takers. Enumerators will call at each house three times
if necessary. If there's still no one home... they'll leave a
voter registration card in the mailbox.
<HR>

<H3>Chemical Fire </H3>

<P>
Hundreds of people were forced to the chilly streets of downtown
Toronto this morning by chemical fumes. Firefighters were called
to 380 Adelaide Street West, near Spadina after two chemicals
mixed together caused an unexpected reaction. 
<P>
District fire chief Robert Richardson says officials are still
trying to determine what compound was produced by the mixture,
which filled the air with fumes. There were no injuries. 
<HR>

<H3>Plane Follow </H3>

<P>
Officials have confirmed that human remains have been recovered
from the site of the crash of flight 592, and that a full recovery
may take weeks. The very difficult search for bodies and wreckage
goes on in the Florida everglades.
<HR>

<H3>Simpson England </H3>

<P>
OJ. Simpson continued his blitz in Britain today, with an appearance
on a prime time talk show hosted by a husband and wife team. He
was asked some of the same questions Americans continued to ask
about the murders he was acquitted of. 
<HR>

<H3>Jackie O Auction </H3>

<P>
Call it a case of buyer's remorse.. after last month's high-priced
auction of items from the estate of Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis.

<P>
Newsweek reports Sotheby's Auction House let two or three buyers,
who were swept away in the bidding, return their items to be &quot;reoffered&quot;.

<P>
There won't be another auction.. the items have already been resold.
There's no word on which items were returned. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

