<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 05/02/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, May 2, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Budget Cuts 
<LI>Gays Legislation
<LI>Halton Rape 
<LI>Toronto Homicide 
<LI>Dying Mom Cancer 
<LI>Runaway Bus 
<LI>Melanoma Awareness 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Budget Cuts </H3>

<P>
Registered nurses in Ontario say someone could die because of
spending cuts in health care. A survey by the Ontario Nurses Association
found most nurses feel low staffing levels have created unsafe
conditions for patients. 
<HR>

<H3>Gays Legislation</H3>

<P>
The government's gay rights bill will be law within days and some
Liberal MP's don't like it. 
<P>
23 liberals voted against the legislation , now some say the government
is cutting off debate and ramming the bill through parliament.

<HR>

<H3>Halton Rape </H3>

<P>
Halton Region Police have released details of another sexual assault
in Burlington, but said they don't believe it was committed by
the serial rapist being sought for brutal attacks on three youngsters.

<P>
A 14-year-old girl was sexually assaulted April 24th, as she walked
home from a baby-sitting job. She was approached by a man and
forced into a secluded driveway, where she was assaulted. But
the suspect's description does not match that of a man who raped
three youngsters, in Kitchener, Brampton and Oakville over the
past four years. 
<HR>

<H3>Toronto Homicide </H3>

<P>
A 43-year-old man faces a charge of second-degree murder in connection
with the slaying of his 23 year old stepdaughter in Toronto. 
<P>
Officers were called to the victim's basement apartment yesterday
afternoon. They found a man, as well as the body of the woman.
The man was taken to hospital, suffering from self-inflicted knife
wounds to his wrists, neck and arms. It's Toronto's 17th homicide
of the year. 
<HR>

<H3>Dying Mom Cancer </H3>

<P>
Donna Mercier was remanded to June 13th when she appeared in a
Toronto court today on a public mischief charge. 
<P>
She's the woman who told police she was dying of cancer and had
been robbed, prompting an outpouring of public donations. Her
lawyer won't say how she will plead. But he says the matter is
wearing her down. 
<HR>

<H3>Runaway Bus</H3>

<P>
It's probably the nightmare of every parent... sending a child
to school on a bus. This past Monday in Knox Indiana, a school
bus driver taking children home, had a seizure.. and lost control
of his bus as it began heading toward a river and a decrepit old
bridge. 
<P>
Surveillance tape shot inside the bus, shows how the children
were thrown around when the driver passed out. Both police and
local school officials are crediting 17-year old John Waldren
with saving the children. Waldren was able to pull the emergency
break and stop the vehicle just as it reached the bridge. 
<HR>

<H3>Melanoma Awareness </H3>

<P>
Melanoma is a deadly form of skin cancer and the number of people
getting it is increasing. But a new survey shows about half of
the men and a third of the women questioned, didn't recognize
the term. 

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

