<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 04/24/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, April 24, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Nurses/Doctors - Cuts 
<LI>Ont. Survivalists
<LI>Somalia Documents 
<LI>Gorby Kill 
<LI>Subway Trial 
<LI>Margot Kidder 
<LI>Jackie O Auction 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Nurses/Doctors - Cuts </H3>

<P>
Ontario's nurses are being asked to take big pay cuts... while
doctors are pushing for their OHIP billing cap to be lifted. 
<P>
It is the latest episode in the health care funding battle...
a battle that began with Medicare more than 25 years ago. Anthony
Pooley has the details. 
<P>
<I>More than 17 billion dollars of taxpayers money is spent each
year on providing health care for Ontarians... and the way in
which that money ought to be spent has always sparked loud and
sometimes acrimonious debate both within and against the health
care community... perennially versus government. </I>
<P>
<I>Several years ago, an OHIP billing cap was imposed on doctors
by the NDP administration... and this year, billings exceed the
cap by a half billion dollars. The physicians want it... and Premier
Mike Harris says they can't have it. </I>
<P>
<I>While all of this is going on ... those who deliver by far
the lion's share of medical care in hospitals... nurses... are
being asked to take a pay cut... a cut that would amount to more
than 20 percent over three years ... a cut that would mean nurses
would earn pennies an hour more than cafeteria workers. </I>
<P>
<I>As ONA regional representative Ancilla Ho-young puts it...
you get what you pay for. </I>
<P>
<I>So the stage is set for another episode in the never-ending
soap opera... nurses versus doctors versus the Ontario government
and the Ontario Hospital Association. It is a fight about money,
to be sure, but it is also a fight about the quality and indeed
the future of Ontario's beleaguered health care system, with those
doctors and nurses alike digging in for a fight. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Ont. Survivalists</H3>

<P>
The Ontario Provincial Police report that two para-military groups
recently formed in the province, are under surveillance. 
<P>
A number of ultra right wing, para military militias, operating
in the united states are fueled by anti government sentiment.
The OPP won't say where the Ontario groups, called &quot;survivalists&quot;
are operating. 
<P>
Solicitor General Bob Runciman says there is some cause for concern.

<HR>

<H3>Somalia Documents </H3>

<P>
More revelations about a military cover-up in the Somalia affair.
A memo to Canada's top soldier appears to contradict what general
Jean Boyle told military police about altered documents released
to the media. 
<HR>

<H3>Gorby Kill </H3>

<P>
Former soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev was attacked while campaigning
in Russia's presidential election today. His aides called it an
assassination attempt but one report says he was simply punched
in the face by a drunken man. 
<P>
The 65-year-old Gorbachev was attacked while on his way to address
a largely hostile meeting in the western Siberian city of Omsk.
He was not hurt. the assailant was arrested. 
<HR>

<H3>Subway Trial </H3>

<P>
The man accused of masterminding what Japan calls it's &quot;crime
of the century&quot;.... went on trial today. Shoko Asahara is
accused of murder in last years nerve gas attack on subway trains
in Tokyo. 
<HR>

<H3>Margot Kidder </H3>

<P>
Police say Canadian actress Margot Kidder was &quot;frightened
for her life&quot; when she disappeared. She was found yesterday,
dazed and disoriented, in a Glendale, California, backyard. 
<P>
Investigators say there's no evidence kidder was the victim of
foul play. She's in hospital undergoing a psychiatric assessment.

<HR>

<H3>Jackie O Auction </H3>

<P>
An incredible auction continues today in New York. Items from
the estate of the late Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis are on sale
at Sotheby's auction house. 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

