<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 04/19/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, April 19, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>K.W. Protest 
<LI>Mulroney 
<LI>Beer Pricing 
<LI>Enviro Reportcard 
<LI>Wolf Attack 
<LI>Israel Diplomacy 
<LI>Canuck- Egypt 
<LI>Oklahoma Anniversary
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>KW Protest </H3>

<P>
It was a great day for a protest. Rainy skies cleared up in time
for a giant noon hour rally in Kitchener, the third community
action day in Ontario. 
<P>
Although this latest protest wasn't as large as previous ones
in London and Hamilton, what it lacked in numbers, it made up
for in spirit. 
<HR>

<H3>Mulroney </H3>

<P>
Brian Mulroney has wrapped up his pre-trial statements in his
50 million dollar libel lawsuit against Ottawa. 
<P>
The former prime minister is suing the RCMP and the Justice Department
for alleging he received kickbacks in the 1988 sale of airbus
jets to Air Canada. 
<P>
Today in Montreal, Mulroney repeated he was innocent. He also
said when he first learned of the allegations, he offered to let
police look at his financial records to prove he could not have
taken any kickbacks. But he says they wouldn't give him the time
of day. 
<HR>

<H3>Beer Pricing </H3>

<P>
This past week the provincial government changed rules which determine
how beer prices are set. The idea was to spark more competition
between brewers. But few people in the hospitality industry feel
the new rules will result in lower beer prices for consumers.

<HR>

<H3>Enviro. Reportcard </H3>

<P>
Just three days before the celebration of &quot;Earth Day&quot;,
Ontario's New Democratic Party has given the Harris government
a failing grade on environmental issues. 
<P>
The NDP's report card gives the government an &quot;F&quot; in
the protection of everything from land, air and water. But it
did receive an &quot;A&quot; in environmental rhetoric. 
<P>
The NDP accuses the government of gutting the environmental bill
of rights, lifting the ban on municipal garbage incinerators,
and contracting out, or closing up to 15 provincial parks. 
<P>
NDP environment critic, Marilyn Churley says the government's
message is &quot;full steam ahead&quot; for short-term profit.
But Churley adds, protection of the environment is still high
on the public's agenda. 
<HR>

<H3>Wolf Attack </H3>

<P>
A man and woman are in hospital at this hour after they were attacked
by a lion at the African Lion Safari near Cambridge earlier this
afternoon. 
<P>
Although few details have been released, it is known the 20 year
old woman is suffering from a head injury. She was a passenger
in a car at the safari and her window was partly rolled down.
The driver suffered an injury while trying to assist the woman.

<P>
And a 24 year old woman is dead after being attacked by wolves
at the Haliburton Wildlife Reserve late yesterday. The woman was
inside a fenced compound when the wolves attacked. Dead is Tricia
Wyman of Haliburton. 
<HR>

<H3>Israel Diplomacy </H3>

<P>
There are hopes tonight that the fighting along Israel's border
with Lebanon could soon end. Hezbollah rockets today pounded northern
Israel. Israeli artillery and gunboats also were in action. 
<P>
There are no reports of new casualties. But prospects of a cease-fire
remain alive. 
<HR>

<H3>Canuck-Egypt </H3>

<P>
A Canadian is among the 18 foreign tourists gunned down yesterday
in the Egyptian capital of Cairo. 
<P>
50 year old Nick Petrou, a London Ontario native, was on his first
pilgrimage to famous holy sites in the middle east when his bus
was attacked by Islamic fundamentalists. All of the victims were
part of a tour group composed mainly of Greeks. 
<HR>

<H3>Oklahoma Anniversary</H3>

<P>
Oklahoma City was silent today - to remember the victims of the
bombing that rocked the city a year ago. Mourners met at the bombing
site to mark the first anniversary of the tragedy that killed
168 people. 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

