<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 04/18/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, April 18, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Israeli Attack Wrap 
<LI>Lebanon Reaction 
<LI>Egypt Attack 
<LI>Drug Bust 
<LI>Teen Killed 
<LI>OPSEU Pep Talk 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Israeli Attack Wrap </H3>

<P>
Foreign Affairs Minister Lloyd Axworthy says today's deadly artillery
attack by Israel in south Lebanon is unacceptable. 
<P>
The UN says at least 75 people were killed in this morning's attack
on a UN refugee camp. Axworthy says he has called in diplomats
from both the Israeli and Lebanese missions in Ottawa, to urge
them to persuade the Hezbollah and Israel to agree to a cease-fire.

<P>
US President Clinton is also calling for an immediate end to the
fighting. 
<HR>

<H3>Lebanon Reaction </H3>

<P>
In Israel, PLO leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli prime minister
Shimon Peres had this reaction to today's attack. 
<HR>

<H3>Egypt Attack </H3>

<P>
Meanwhile, gunmen shouting Islamic slogans opened fire in front
of a hotel near the pyramids in Egypt today, killing at least
18 Greek tourists and wounding 17 other people.
<HR>

<H3>Drug Bust </H3>

<P>
An international police operation against drug dealers in Canada,
Europe and Colombia, has led to the arrest of 24 people belonging
to two Montreal crime networks. 
<P>
Among those arrested is Frank Cotroni, said to be the boss of
the Montreal Mafia. The arrests follow months of multi-million
dollar drug seizures by police in Toronto Montreal, and western
Europe. A large quantity of cocaine and hashish has been seized.

<HR>

<H3>Teen Killed </H3>

<P>
Police in Kitchener have arrested a 25 year old man in connection
with the murder of his 17 year old, pregnant girlfriend. 
<P>
Police say the accused called them late last night, to say he
had discovered the body of the victim, who was eight months pregnant,
in a basement apartment. 
<P>
The boyfriend, who was arrested at the scene, has not been identified.
An autopsy will be conducted today to determine the cause of death.

<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Pep Talk </H3>

<P>
Some of the people expected to take part in tomorrow's protest,
showed their disapproval of the Harris government by hitting the
picket lines for five weeks. 
<P>
Today Ontario's Civil Service Union said it will not take punitive
action against those members who crossed the picket line. 
<P>
