<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 04/11/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, April 11, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Dying Mom Update 
<LI>Ontario Cuts 
<LI>120 km/h 
<LI>Sisters Drown 
<LI>Pint Sized Pilot 
<LI>Beirut Attack 
<LI>Bernard Goetz 
<LI>Harding Divorce 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Dying Mom Update </H3>

<P>
A Toronto mother who was reported to be dying of cancer has been
charged with public mischief. 
<P>
27-year-old Donna Mercier was taken into custody late this afternoon.
She will be released later tonight. 
<P>
Donations topping 110-thousand dollars poured in for the woman
and her seven-year-old son after reports her purse was stolen
last week. An investigation was launched after anonymous callers
questioned her story. 
<HR>

<H3>Ontario Cuts </H3>

<P>
Over the next two years, ten thousand civil servants in this province
will be handed pinks slips. The announcement came today as the
government tries to trim its budget by 4.5 billion dollars. 
<P>
Residents will soon be paying more for everything from marriage
licenses and tourist attractions to public housing. 
<HR>

<H3>120 km/h </H3>

<P>
Are we driving too fast? maybe not, says Transport Minister Al
Palladini. 
<P>
Improved road technology, safer cars, and legions of rebellious
drivers, have made the posted speed limit of 100 kilometers an
hour; virtually meaningless. That's why the minister may be considering
some new signs; that could raise maximum speeds, and require minimum
speeds, on major provincial highways. Scot Urquhart has more:

<P>
<I>The speed limit is 100. But cars on Canada's busiest highway,
routinely ignore the rules .... OPP Sergeant John Mason says,
a suggestion by Transport Minister Al Palladini to bump the posted
speed limit to 120 kilometers an hour ... doesn't really worry
him. Speed isn't the problem. aggressive behaviour ... is. </I>
<P>
<I>Bob Pring, is with the Insurance Bureau of Canada. He agrees
with John Mason ... speed isn't really a factor.  In fact, slow
drivers, can be just as dangerous, and worse yet says Pring ...
many of us aren't paying attention, no matter what speed we drive.</I>
<P>
<I>Both the police, and the insurance companies say ... it's not
number on the sign that matters; it's what we do with it.</I>
<HR>

<H3>Sisters Drown </H3>

<P>
A family, northwest of Kitchener is in mourning today, after two
young sisters fell through the ice of a partially frozen pond
on their grandfather's farm. 
<P>
Four year old Lena Martin and her three year old sister Naomi
were trapped under water for up to 30 minutes before rescue workers
reached them. Their five year old cousin, Cindy Martin, was rescued
by a neighbor who slid across the ice to the hole where the girls
had fallen through. 
<HR>

<H3>Pint Sized Pilot </H3>

<P>
A seven year old girl has been killed in an attempt to become
the youngest pilot ever to fly across the United States. 
<P>
A plane flown by Jessica Dubroff, crashed in a rainstorm in Cheyenne,
Wyoming. The little girl, her father and a flight instructor were
all killed in the crash. 
<HR>

<H3>Beirut Attack </H3>

<P>
For the first time in 14 years, Israeli aircraft have attacked
the Lebanese capital of Beirut. 
<P>
Helicopters fired rockets at the city's southern suburbs, where
pro-Iranian Hezbollah rebels are based. 
<P>
Hours earlier, Israeli aircraft struck in eastern and southern
Lebanon to avenge Hezbollah attacks that killed an Israeli soldier
and injured 38 other people in the past three days. 
<HR>

<H3>Bernard Goetz </H3>

<P>
It's been more than eleven years since Bernard Goetz opened fire
on a group of black teenagers on a New York City subway car, after
the group tried to rob him of five dollars. 
<P>
Goetz claimed he fired in self defense and was acquitted of attempted
murder in the case.. but today he was back in court facing civil
charges.
<HR>

<H3>Harding Divorce </H3>

<P>
And in the where are they now category... Tonya Harding has filed
for divorce from Michael Smith, whom she married three and a-half
months ago. 
<P>
Harding's agent says she doesn't want any distractions as she
focuses on her skating comeback. Yes, the bad girl of ice skating
is attempting a comeback. 
<P>
For those who are counting, it was her second marriage, and his
fourth. 


<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

