<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 04/05/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, April 5, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Chretien-Premiers 
<LI>Doctors Jobless 
<LI>Cancer-Gene 
<LI>GO Fatal 
<LI>Soul Voc 
<LI>Via Dolorosa 
<LI>Pope-Confessions 
<LI>Hawk Watch 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Chretien-Premiers</H3>

<P>
Prime Minister Jean Chretien ...is putting all of his political
eggs into one Easter basket. 
<P>
The prime minister's office announced today; that a first minister's
meeting on national unity; is tentatively set for June 20th. The
two day conference will include Quebec premier Lucien Bouchard;
but sources say the date could be changed, if a summer election
is called by BC. premier Glen Clark. 
<HR>

<H3>Doctors Jobless </H3>

<P>
There are too many big city doctors in Ontario... and not enough
patients to support them. So says the Ontario government. And
because of that, new doctors in the province may be forced to
leave Ontario to practice ... or find themselves on the unemployment
line. 
<HR>

<H3>Cancer-Gene</H3>

<P>
While doctors in Ontario are wondering about the &quot;where's&quot;
of medicine ... doctors in Philadelphia; are wondering about the
&quot;why's&quot;. In particular ... they are looking at a genetic
link to lung cancer; and believe they may have found a key, to
that deadly disease.
<HR>

<H3>GO Fatal </H3>

<P>
An accident on the GO Transit line in east end Toronto this afternoon,
has claimed the life of an unidentified woman. 
<P>
Police say the victim was hit by a train near Guildwood Station
around noon. The accident forced the temporary closure of the
line ... as transit traffic was re-routed around the accident
scene. No other details of the accident, are yet available. 
<HR>

<H3>Soul Voc </H3>

<P>
A Canadian version of the so-called, million man march ... was
small, but significant, according to organizers. 
<P>
Dubbed &quot;Soultrek&quot; the Good Friday march in downtown
Toronto, was promoted as a gathering of atonement, and reconciliation.
The march ended in a noon hour rally at Oakwood Collegiate; where
organizer Don Mohammed addressed the crowd.
<HR>

<H3>Via Dolorosa </H3>

<P>
Half a world away ... another march for atonement and reconciliation
... this one in Jerusalem ... where religious pilgrims took part
in the traditional Good Friday walk, on the Via Dolorosa. The
path is believed to be the same one that Christ followed to his
crucifixion. 
<HR>

<H3>Pope-Confessions </H3>

<P>
And in Rome ... Pope John Paul heard the confessions of 12 penitents
... gathered from countries around the world... as part of his
Good Friday tradition. 
<P>
Later in the day, the pontiff carried a wooden cross around the
exterior of Rome's coliseum, in a symbolic re-creation of Christ's
journey to Golgotha. 
<HR>

<H3>Hawk Watch </H3>

<P>
And on this Good Friday, in the Niagara peninsula ... scores of
eyes were turned towards the heavens ... for a sign of something
to send the spirits soaring. 
<P>
Though not divine; some would say that the aerial show above Grimsby,
is indeed, a gift from god: Deborah Walker explains: 
<P>
<I>For twenty years now, naturalists have perched atop the Niagara
escarpment in the Beamer Conservation Area, to tally the number
of raptors who sail overhead on their way to northern breeding
grounds. The raptors come this way to skirt the open waters of
lake Ontario and lake Erie, searching instead for the thermals
that rise from the warming earth and carry them aloft. </I>
<P>
<I>Today, turkey vultures are a common sight. Other sightings
evoke a more thrilling reaction. Every day, from the first of
march to the middle of may, someone is stationed here to continue
the count. And once each season, on Good Friday, the naturalists
invite the public to share their passion. </I>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

