<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 03/18/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, March 18, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Queens Park Protest 
<LI>Krasowski-Liberals 
<LI>Karla Report 
<LI>Belleville Teen 
<LI>Killer Guns 
<LI>Salvi Verdict 
<LI>Mandela Divorce 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Queens Park Protest</H3>

<P>
A noisy demonstration at Queens Park turned violent today when
police and striking OPSEU workers clashed at the entrance of the
legislative building. 
<P>
Two people were taken to hospital after police used batons to
control the crowd of over a thousand. The protest was planned
around the opening of the spring session of the Ontario legislature.

<HR>

<H3>Krasowski-Liberals</H3>

<P>
A Liberal Party official from Niagara Falls has thrown his hat
into the ring for leader of the Liberals provincial party. 
<P>
Ted Krasowski, secretary of the Niagara Falls Provincial Liberal
Association, will seek the top job when the convention is held
in November. Krasowski is a statistician with a pharmaceutical
firm and is active in politics at both the federal and provincial
levels. 
<HR>

<H3>Karla Report </H3>

<P>
Convicted killer Karla Homolka will not face additional criminal
charges. That was the recommendation from Mr. Justice Patrick
Galligan... the judge who reviewed the controversial plea deal
made with Homolka. 
<P>
She was sentenced to a maximum of 12 years in prison in exchange
for testimony against her ex husband Paul Bernardo. Lauran Sabourin
has the story. 
<P>
<I>In his report Judge Galligan agreed with the decision not to
proceed with charges against Homolka in the sexual assault of
Jane Doe because it would have damaged her credibility on the
stand. And the jury might have returned a lesser charge against
Bernardo in that case. Even though Homolka failed to tell authorities
about the assault until after she signed her 12 year deal. And
she was serving her term in prison. The public was outraged. </I>
<P>
<I>Donna French, Kristen French's mother, wasn't happy with the
12 year deal either. She wanted a much longer sentence. Homolka's
father Karel said he expected the results in the review. Because
as he put it, his daughter followed the rules. </I>
<P>
<I>But Gwen Hunter, the Dundas woman who along with a group produced
a 320 thousand name petition, doesn't buy that. And she says the
petition won't stop here. </I>
<P>
<I>Homolka's sentence has caused public to seriously question
the plea bargaining system. But as donna French sees it, it's
a system in most cases that works. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Belleville Teen </H3>

<P>
The school attended by slain Belleville Ontario teenager, Mark
Fyke held a prayer service today to help students cope with their
grief. 
<P>
The 18 year old was shot and killed last week in Daytona Beach,
Florida, where he was spending March break. An 18 year old Florida
man turned himself in and is charged with first degree murder.

<HR>

<H3>Killer Guns</H3>

<P>
School is out for most of the week in Dunblane, Scotland as the
townspeople hold funerals for victims of a massacre. 
<P>
16 kindergarten children and a teacher were gunned down last week
by a shooter who then killed himself. 
<HR>

<H3>Salvi Verdict </H3>

<P>
A Massachusetts jury has convicted abortion clinic shooter John
Salvi on all counts. 
<P>
Salvi murdered two women and tried to kill five people in December
of 1994. The jurors rejected arguments that Salvi was insane when
he planned and carried out the attacks at clinics in the Boston
area. 
<HR>

<H3>Mandela Divorce </H3>

<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela has accused his estranged
wife, Winnie, of adultery. 
<P>
He was testifying at the start of their divorce proceedings. Mandela
told the court that when he left prison in 1990 after serving
27 years of a life sentence, he went to live with his wife in
Soweto but they experienced no real intimacy. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

