<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 03/11/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, March 11, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>OPSEU Talks-2 
<LI>Sci/Tech 
<LI>Terrorism 
<LI>Rafsanjani Terror 
<LI>China 
<LI>Chechnya Battles 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Talks-2 </H3>

<P>
A union spokesman reports slow progress in talks aimed at ending
Ontario's civil service strike. 
<P>
Labor ministry mediators are shuttling back and forth between
rooms of a downtown Toronto hotel, carrying messages both the
union and the government. The two sides were called back yesterday
in a bid to end the strike by 54 thousand civil servants. 
<HR>

<H3>Sci/Tech </H3>

<P>
Ottawa has a new strategy for science and technology. Federal
politicians are hoping the plan will help improve 
<P>
Canada's international research and development reputation and
help create more jobs as well. after an exhaustive two year review,
Ottawa is announcing changes that among other things will give
Canadian corporations more money and more control in developing
new technologies. 
<HR>

<H3>Terrorism </H3>

<P>
Prime Minister Jean Chretien leaves late tonight for Wednesday's
one day summit in Egypt on terrorism. 
<P>
Chretien says the meeting, to be attended by officials from about
30 countries, is aimed at showing support for the mid-east peace
process. The process has been shaken by four suicide bombings
in Israel over the past few weeks. 
<HR>

<H3>Rafsanjani Terror</H3>

<P>
Iran's president meanwhile, is denying his country is linked to
the recent bombings in Israel. 
<P>
Hashemi Rafsanjani says Iran has a political relationship with
Hamas, but he says, it does not give the group financial or military
support. 
<HR>

<H3>China </H3>

<P>
US President Clinton has ordered a second aircraft carrier, the
USS Nimitz, to the China sea, as Beijing prepares for a week of
military exercises. 
<P>
The show of force is aimed at Taiwan, which holds presidential
elections in two weeks. China considers the island a renegade
province, and officials are warning the US to stay away. 
<P>
The pentagon says the measures are simply precautionary.
<HR>

<H3>Chechnya Battles </H3>

<P>
In the Chechen capital of Grozny, a relative, general calm has
replaced the chaos of recent battles. 
<P>
After nearly a week of intense fighting between Russian forces
and separatist guerrillas, the two sides now engage each other
in a game of cat and mouse, with the Chechens launching sniper
attacks and the Russians retaliating. And as the war grinds on,
the Chechen people try to sort through the mess left behind. 

<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

