<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 03/07/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, March 7, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>OPSEU Day 11 
<LI>School Cuts Follow
<LI>Budget Follow
<LI>Politics - Budget 
<LI>Killer Bags 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Day 11</H3>

<P>
Inmates rioted at Toronto's Don Jail today. And striking jail
guards had to be called inside to quell the disturbance. 
<HR>

<H3>School Cuts Follow</H3>

<P>
High school students from throughout Halton region converged at
school board headquarters in Burlington today to protest massive
layoffs of teachers and support staff. 
<P>
All of this on the heels of the release of the so-called tool
kit from Queen's Park... that was supposed to have been a help
in managing the cuts. Anthony Pooley has the details. 
<P>
<I>These students protested loudly today... fearing that their
education is at risk. And their fears are well- founded. </I>
<P>
<I>The Halton Board of Education recently sent out 1500 layoff
notices... trying to come to terms with massive cutbacks in education
funding from Queen's Park. </I>
<P>
<I>Yesterday, Education Minister John Snobelen unveiled a so-called
tool kit that was expected to help boards deal with the cuts...
but Halton Board chair Linda Glover says nothing in it will enable
trustees to back- pedal on the announced cuts. </I>
<P>
<I>Back outside... not all of the students are in agreement...
and a handful who support the tough measures are chastised by
their peers for their opposing point of view. </I>
<P>
<I>At OSSTF District 8 Headquarters in Hamilton meanwhile, there
is tension in the air. </I>
<P>
<I>Back at the protest in Burlington, student organizers were
able to speak with Premier Mike Harris over the phone. They also
met briefly with school board officials... but the tough medicine
remains just as difficult to swallow. In Burlington... Anthony
Pooley... Channel 11 News. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Budget Follow</H3>

<P>
The budget is out, now the selling begins. The head of the Treasury
Board now says federal government workers could be in for their
first raise in six years. 
<P>
Marcel Masse says he is lifting the wage freeze because there
is light at the end of the government's deficit tunnel. 
<HR>

<H3>Politics - Budget </H3>

<P>
The absence of deep spending cuts in yesterday's federal budget
has political pundits wondering what the Liberals are trying to
do. 
<P>
Some suspect it means an election may not be too far off. Others
think the Chretien government is just reacting to the national
mood. 
<HR>

<H3>Killer Bags </H3>

<P>
The US government is taking a second look at airbags in cars,
after a number of them actually killed people they're designed
to save in a crash.  
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

