<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/19/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, February 19, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Kinkaid-New Suspect 
<LI>OPSEU Talks 
<LI>Hampton Runs 
<LI>Chretien 
<LI>Bus Bomb 
<LI>Ferry Deaths 
<LI>Two Dollar Coin 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Kinkaid-New Suspect </H3>

<P>
The hunt is now on for a second suspect in the murders of Marsha
and Tamara Ottey. 
<P>
Toronto police have issued a Canada wide warrant for 20 year old
Rohan Ranger. Ranger is the former boyfriend of one of the girls
and the cousin of another murder suspect, Adrian Kinkead. 
<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Talks </H3>

<P>
The mood was somber today as negotiators for the government and
its biggest public sector union sat down to resume formal contract
talks. 
<P>
Members of OPSEU rejected the government's latest offer this weekend
by a vote of 66 percent. That lent a new urgency to contract talks
that resumed this morning. 
<HR>

<H3>Hampton Runs </H3>

<P>
The field of candidates is growing for the provincial NPD leadership.

<P>
Rainy River MPP Howard Hampton is the fourth to enter the race.
The 43 year old Hampton says his campaign is about taking back
the future. He says the Harris government is dismantling our education
and health-care systems. Hampton also believes he can attract
a broader base of voters to the New Democratic Party. 
<P>
Hampton joins MPP's Frances Lankin, Tony Silipo and Peter Kormos
in the race. 
<HR>

<H3>Chretien </H3>

<P>
The Prime Minister has broken his silence following last week's
confrontation with a protester in Hull, Quebec. 
<P>
Jean Chretien says the RCMP should have been clearing a path in
front of him, and that it's deplorable that he was forced to grab
a protester by the neck to force him out of his way. The mounties
now say they'll beef-up security around Chretien in the future.
And the protester at the centre of this incident is being coy
about whether he'll file a complaint against the Prime Minister.

<HR>

<H3>Bus Bomb</H3>

<P>
Police in London say they have two people in custody after yesterday's
IRA bomb blast aboard a double decker bus. 
<P>
One person died in the explosion. Police think he may have been
the bomber, and that the device may have gone off sooner than
planned. 
<HR>

<H3>Ferry Deaths</H3>

<P>
In the Philippines, officials say more than 50 people died and
15 are missing after a wooden ferry overturned.
<P>
The Philippine coast guard says the ship was carrying more than
twice its legal capacity. The aging ferry failed a safety check
last week. Officials say the dead include 31 children.
<HR>

<H3>Two Dollar Coin </H3>

<P>
Toonie, bearbuck, blooney, doosie, loonie two... take the time
you need picking out a name for this one. But as of today, the
coin sporting the Queen's face and a polar bear on the reverse,
replaces the two dollar bill as part of our currency. 
<P>
The Royal Canadian Mint struck 60 million of the new coins for
today's launch.  
<P>

