<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/15/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, February 15, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Evng Scuffle 
<LI>Harris-OPSEU Vote 
<LI>Silipo 
<LI>Marchi Runs? 
<LI>Ottawa Drive By 
<LI>Father's Plea 
<LI>London Bomb Wrap 
<LI>Runaway Train 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Evng Scuffle </H3>

<P>
The Mounties are remaining tight lipped tonight following an incident
earlier today involving Prime Minister Jean Chretien and a demonstrator
near Ottawa. 
<HR>

<H3>Harris-OPSEU Vote</H3>

<P>
The Ontario Labor Board has ruled that the vote, currently taking
place across the province by the civil service is legal. 
<P>
The board made that decision late this afternoon. 
<HR>

<H3>Silipo </H3>

<P>
The field of candidates seeking the leadership of the Ontario
NDP has grown to three. 
<P>
Toronto MPP Tony Silipo announced today he is a candidate to succeed
outgoing leader Bob Rae. Silipo joins fellow MPP's Peter Kormos
and Frances Lankin as leadership candidates for the June convention.

<HR>

<H3>Marchi Runs? </H3>

<P>
Meanwhile, Environment Minister Sergio Marchi also appears to
be laying the groundwork for a run at the leadership of the Ontario
Liberal Party. 
<P>
Sources say Marchi has been quietly approaching Ontario Liberals
to seek their support if he decides to leave parliament hill for
Queen's Park. A spokesman for Marchi says he is merely keeping
his options open. 
<HR>

<H3>Ottawa Drive By </H3>

<P>
In Ottawa, a jury has convicted a 17 year old teenager in the
drive-by shooting of a British tourist. 
<P>
Witnesses testified that Rubens Henderson shot Nicholas Battersby
once through the heart from a passing car, as Battersby walked
through an Ottawa nightclub district. 
<P>
Henderson's lawyer said the teen did not mean to kill Battersby
and had urged the jury to bring in a verdict of manslaughter.

<HR>

<H3>Father's Plea </H3>

<P>
Police have received 200 tips concerning the hunt for a suspect
wanted in three killings in Toronto. 
<P>
Investigators believe 20 year old Adrian Kinkead is hiding in
Toronto, possibly with the help of friends. Officers are watching
a Scarborough apartment complex where Kinkead is known to have
frequented. 
<P>
He's wanted in connection with the fatal stabbings of a transit
worker and two teenage sisters. 
<P>
Meanwhile, the minister at the Kinkead family's church has made
a plea for the suspect to surrender. 
<HR>

<H3>London Bomb Wrap </H3>

<P>
In London, England, police deactivated a bomb just hours after
the Irish republican army appeared to reject demands for a new
cease-fire. 
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility but Scotland Yard says two coded
telephone warnings &quot;bore all the hallmarks of the IRA. 
<HR>

<H3>Runaway Train </H3>

<P>
Authorities now say sabotage is suspected in a train crash in
Minnesota. 
<P>
A runaway train, traveling at 80 kilometres per hour, slammed
into a railroad office today, injuring at least nine people. 

<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

