<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/12/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, February 12, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Child Abductions 
<LI>Kladuz Trial 
<LI>Hate Clip 
<LI>Boiler 
<LI>Rent Controls 
<LI>Train Wreck 
<LI>Italy Crash 
<LI>Japan Tunnel 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Child Abductions </H3>

<P>
Police from across southern Ontario are focusing on London as
they search for a suspect wanted in the sexual assaults of three
children. 
<P>
Investigators are trying to determine if there is a link between
the attacks and about a dozen attempted abductions of children
in London. 
<HR>

<H3>Kladuz Trial </H3>

<P>
Jury selection began today in the trial of a man accused in a
heartbreaking child murder. 
<P>
It was July 1991 when three year old Kayla Kladuz vanished from
the fenced in yard, of her Toronto Parkdale apartment building.
Three weeks later her body was found in the Harbour. 
<P>
The trial of 36 year old David Alexander Snowden, a janitor in
Kayla's building, is expected to last 3 to 4 months. 
<HR>

<H3>Hate Clip</H3>

<P>
A groundbreaking study commissioned for the federal government
says hate crimes in Canada are much more common than we think.

<P>
The report was prepared by a University of Ottawa criminologist
and suggests that only ten percent of hate crimes are reported
to police. That lack of accurate statistical information has social
advocates worried that governments aren't doing enough to remedy
what appears to be a grossly underestimated problem. 
<HR>

<H3>Boiler </H3>

<P>
It's still unclear what caused a boiler explosion at Mohawk College
on Hamilton mountain. 
<P>
The side of a boiler, used to heat the college, blew out last
night sending an engineer to hospital. He was released and returned
to the college late last night to help investigators. 
<P>
Officials with the Fire Marshall's Office and the fuel safety
branch have been at the college all day, trying to pinpoint a
cause and a damage estimate. 
<P>
Classes at Mohawk haven't been affected, and there's apparently
no danger of another explosion taking place. 
<HR>

<H3>Rent Controls </H3>

<P>
Ontario New Democrats have launched a &quot;hands off rent control&quot;
campaign. 
<P>
The Harris government wants to get rid of rent controls, to encourage
the construction industry to build more rental units. But the
NDP say without controls ..rents will go sky high.
<HR>

<H3>Train Wreck </H3>

<P>
Cleanup crews are fighting wind and swirling snow today as they
struggle to move 25 cars that left the tracks. 
<P>
The derailment occurred yesterday on CP Rail's main line in a
remote part of a northern Ontario. At least six tanker cars carrying
liquid sulphur careened into the Spanish river, spilling their
loads. 
<HR>

<H3>Italy Crash </H3>

<P>
Notoriously fast drivers and sudden fog... a recipe for disaster
on Italian highways. 
<P>
In the latest pileup, at least 11 people were killed this morning
when 300 cars collided in a chain reaction that left twisted metal
and gasoline-fed flames across a main highway in northern Italy.

<HR>

<H3>Japan Tunnel </H3>

<P>
In Japan, hope is turning to grief as 20 people remain trapped
inside a collapsed tunnel. 
<P>
Workers failed today for a second time to blast a huge, 50 thousand
tonne boulder off the highway tunnel.  
<P>

