<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/09/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, February 9, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>London Blast 
<LI>Auto Insurance 
<LI>Lap Dancing 
<LI>Bernardo Tapes 5 
<LI>Tapes Tag 
<LI>Radarsat 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>London Blast</H3>

<P>
The Prime Ministers of Ireland and Britain are condemning an explosion
in an east London business district. 
<P>
At least four people are badly hurt and 18 were slightly injured.
The blast came shortly after a report that the Irish republican
army has ended its 17 month old cease-fire. 
<HR>

<H3>Auto Insurance </H3>

<P>
Some major changes have been announced to Ontario's auto insurance
system with the goal to reduce premium hikes. 
<P>
Rob Sampson, the minister in charge of auto insurance reform says
Ontario consumers are entitled to stable auto insurance rates.
And he says under the new plan, accident victims would be allowed
to sue for all injuries, not just for pain and suffering.
<HR>

<H3>Lap Dancing </H3>

<P>
A former stripper is hailing an Ontario Court of Appeal ruling
that lap dancing is an indecent act. 
<P>
Katharine Goldberg says the decision will save many exotic dancers
from a lot of pain and suffering. 
<P>
The appeal court ruled lap dancing degrades and dehumanizes women
and portrays them a sex objects. The judges also say lap dancing
is a form of prostitution and violates community standards. 
<HR>

<H3>Bernardo Tapes 5 </H3>

<P>
The Ontario government disagrees with the families of Kristen
French and Leslie Mahaffy by saying the law does protect the public
from pornographic evidence. 
<P>
That argument was made in a St. Catharines court today in response
to the families claim that the law should be changed to guarantee
that pornographic evidence would not be seen or heard in a public
courtroom. 
<P>
Lauran Sabourin has more in this report. 
<P>
<I>Crown attorney John Pearson agrees that the videotapes that
show Paul Bernardo sexually brutalizing Kristen French and Leslie
Mahaffy are degrading, dehumanizing and debasing. And that allowing
access to those tapes is not in the public interest. But the issue
as the family sees it is justice Patrick Lesage's decision to
allow the public to hear the videotapes. </I>
<P>
<I>They want to the law to specify that allowing what is deemed
child pornography to even be heard by the public is harmful and
that the public should not be allowed to see or hear that evidence.
The crown's position is that the law already gives the judge the
power to clear the courtroom when such evidence is presented.
</I>
<HR>

<H3>Tapes Tag </H3>

<P>
The trustees of the French/Mahaffy Legal Assistance Fund announced
today that their fundraising efforts are winding down. 
<P>
Donations to the fund will be closed off effective March 31st,
1996. 320 thousand dollars have been raised by the fund. The trustees
say another 100 thousand dollars may be needed by the families
to continue their legal fight.
<HR>

<H3>Radarsat </H3>

<P>
Canada's pride and joy will soon be the envy of the world, as
soon as it's up and running. It's called &quot;Radarsat&quot;,
and many Canadians are waiting to see just how impressive the
technology is. 
<P>
Canada's space agency has been working on it for well over a decade
and although it's not supposed to be fully operational just yet,
our very special satellite has already been called upon.  
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

