<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/06/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Tuesday, February 6, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>OPSEU Final Offer 
<LI>French/Mahaffy 2 
<LI>Manley Clip 
<LI>Simpson 
<LI>E-Mail Virus 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Final Offer </H3>

<P>
The Harris government made its final offer today, to the union
representing some 67-thousand government workers. 
<P>
If accepted, some laid off civil servants could walk away with
a full year's salary, but union negotiators say no deal. 
<HR>

<H3>French/Mahaffy 2 </H3>

<P>
Anti pornography expert Catherine Mackinaw says the tapes that
Paul Bernardo made of Leslie Mahaffy and Kristen French are pornography
by any standard. 
<P>
Mackinaw testified today on behalf of the French and Mahaffy families
who are trying to change the law to ensure that sexually explicit
evidence deemed pornography would never be played in open court
again. 
<P>
Lauran Sabourin has more. 
<P>
<I>Professor Catherine Mackinaw has made the study of the impact
of pornography her life's work. She says that pornography is damaging.
It sends out a message to people that women enjoy being raped
and that rape and sexual violence are okay. </I>
<P>
<I>Mackinaw says that in her opinion the tapes that show Paul
Bernardo sexually brutalizing Kristen French and Leslie Mahaffy
are pornography. She viewed those tapes in march of last year.
</I>
<P>
<I>Mackinaw used Nick Pron's book based on testimony and transcripts
at the Bernardo murder trial as evidence of how pornography and
how damaging it can be. </I>
<P>
<I>Mackinaw goes as far as to insist that those tapes should have
never even been heard in open court. </I>
<P>
<I>Twelve copies of the videos Bernardo made of Kristen and Leslie
have been held by the police. Today eight of those tapes were
destroyed. They were burned in St. Catharines police station parking
lot this morning. Two sets are being kept pending an appeal. </I>
<P>
<I>The public thought that the destruction of the tapes would
give the families some closure. That same public is asking why
they are putting themselves through this again. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Manley Clip </H3>

<P>
Industry Minister John Manley says businesses should be thinking
about people, and not just profits. 
<P>
Manley says the goal of business is to make money, but &quot;it's
also necessary to look at the effect of cuts on employees&quot;.

<P>
Many top Canadian companies are reporting strong profits but continue
to slash jobs by the thousands. 
<HR>

<H3>Simpson</H3>

<P>
OJ. Simpson continued his media blitz today, with an appearance
by telephone on a morning radio show in Los Angeles. The themes
were familiar. 
<HR>

<H3>E-Mail Virus </H3>

<P>
Can you imagine a computer virus that not only destroys your files,
but is so lethal your computer starts to burn up. That's the latest
Internet virus, computer users are talking about. But it may turn
out to be more smoke than fire. <I> </I>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

