<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 02/02/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Friday, February 2, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Deep Freeze 
<LI>Living With Cold 
<LI>Mcmurtry-Courts 
<LI>Flag Flap 
<LI>Gene Kelly Obit 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Deep Freeze</H3>

<P>
It might be a good weekend to stay indoors, turn up the heat and
curl up with a good book. 
<P>
Frigid arctic weather is here ..at least for the weekend, and,
as Dwight Ryan reports, two expert weather forecasters disagree
on just how long winter will last. 
<P>
<I>Southern Ontario is having its turn at the deep freeze. Temperatures
have plummeted as the result of a stream of air known as the Siberian
pipeline. The cold air mass which has drifted all the way from
Siberia will keep temperatures bone-crunchingly cold at least
through the weekend. The mass has already set records for low
temperatures in northwestern Ontario and the US. Midwest. </I>
<P>
<I>Will this winter ever end? According to Canada's most famous
weather forecaster, spring is on the way. Wiarton Willie crawled
out of his hole this morning and didn't see his shadow. </I>
<P>
<I>But that one bright spot was dulled by Wiarton Willie's American
cousin, Punxatawney Phil. The Pennsylvania spotted a ray of sunshine
thus predicting at least six more weeks of winter. While road
crews repair one broken water main after another some take the
cold weather with a grain of salt. Others with a grain of something
stronger. </I>
<P>
<I>Lows over the weekend will reach near minus 25 degrees Celsius.
Much colder with the wind-chill. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Living With Cold </H3>

<P>
And with the cold weather comes the natural quest for warmth.
With that in mind doctors recommend that most people especially
young children and the elderly stay indoors. Even indoors many
will be looking to warm up the coldest corners of their homes.
But as Jamie west reports be careful how you do that....some methods
can present more potential hazards than the bitter cold itself...

<P>
<I>Could be a busy weekend.... I should have sealed that door
last fall.,.. drafty outlets no doubt a money vacuum. </I>
<P>
<I>The furnace filter...needs changing ..once a month...no wonder
my furnace is so inefficient. </I>
<P>
<I>My water pipes haven't frozen yet that's good, but I suppose
they could. I better buy a pipe thawing cable. </I>
<P>
<I>Maybe I'll buy a spaceheater... alright maybe I'll just curl
up beside the fire ... I should have had the chimney cleaned last
fall. Maybe I'll switch to a gas fireplace. </I>
<P>
<I>After Frank's visit to my house I knew I should check that
chimney, but if I'm going outside I'll need some really warm gear,
I know just the place the place to go and still preserve my fashionable
appearance... minus 30 ...snowpants for sure... ....thermal boots
check. ...gotta slide into some longjohns... ... need, gloves
serious gloves. ...a warm scarf for sure... and last but not least
some serious headgear...</I>
<HR>

<H3>Mcmurtry-Courts</H3>

<P>
One of Ontario's top judges says if the Harris government goes
ahead with proposed cuts in funding to the courts, it will plunge
the province's justice system in to chaos. In an exclusive interview
with Queens Park reporter Bob Ireland, Chief Justice Roy Mcmurtry,
of the Ontario court, says the proposed cuts are short sighted
and ill-timed. 
<HR>

<H3>Flag Flap </H3>

<P>
A Toronto couple has drawn the wrath of their neighbors at a Florida
trailer park by flying the Canadian flag. The park manager demanded
that Jim and Bev Harris remove what they called &quot;an insult
to the United States.&quot; 
<P>
Clearwater Mayor Rita Garvey says she's &quot;embarrassed&quot;
over the incident, and says Canadians are welcome to fly their
flag. 
<HR>

<H3>Gene Kelly Obit </H3>

<P>
Dancer, choreographer, and actor Gene Kelly has died. Kelly, who
brought his athletic grace to hit movie musicals like &quot;Singin
in the Rain&quot;, died today at his home in Los Angeles. 
<P>
His publicist, Warren Cowan says he died peacefully in his sleep.

<P>
Gene Kelly was 83. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

