<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/31/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, January 31, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Cabinet Bar Hours 
<LI>OPSEU Demo 
<LI>Harnick-Justice 
<LI>Sri Lanka Bomb 
<LI>Oklahoma City 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Cabinet Bar Hours </H3>

<P>
Ontario is getting ready to shed its reputation for having Canada's
tightest liquor laws. 
<P>
Consumer Minister Norm Sterling says he plans to allow extended
drinking hours to 2 a-m or 3 a-m. Critics say extended bar hours
will mean more drunk drivers on the roads... but restaurant owners
say the move will mean more jobs and more tax revenues for the
province. 
<HR>

<H3>OPSEU Demo</H3>

<P>
A group of about 40 employees from the Hamilton Family Support
Plan office staged a sit-in at the Attorney General's office in
Toronto today. 
<P>
The group is protesting the government's plan to shut down eight
regional offices ...Hamilton being one of them. 
<P>
The agency helps collect child support and searches out deadbeat
parents who don't make payments. 
<P>
The protesters were met by Hamilton East Liberal MPP Dominic Agostino.
About half the demonstrators were allowed inside the building,
without their signs, and permitted to go up to Attorney General
Charles Harnick's office. After about an hour they left without
seeing the minister..
<HR>

<H3>Harnick-Justice</H3>

<P>
Attorney General Charles Harnick says he wants to work with judges
to try to streamline the justice system. 
<P>
Harnick says he takes &quot;very seriously&quot; a letter from
the province's top three judges that argues plans to cut the justice
system could create legal chaos. 
<HR>

<H3>Sri Lanka Bomb </H3>

<P>
In international news today, an explosion in Sri Lanka has killed
at least 53 people and left as many as 14 hundred injured. A truck
packed with explosives crashed into the country's central bank
in Colombo around midday their time. It set off a string of high-rise
fires, trapping hundreds of people. 
<HR>

<H3>Oklahoma City </H3>

<P>
The two suspects in the Oklahoma City bombing were back in court
today. Lawyers for Timothy McVeigh and Terry Nichols want to move
the trial from the city. They claim their clients can't get a
fair trial there. 
<P>
The judge is holding four days of hearings to determine where
the trial should be held. New information has surfaced that could
give investigators more insight about a potential motive for the
attack.  
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

