<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/29/96</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, January 29, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Bill v/o 
<LI>Measles-Kid 
<LI>Plane Crash 
<LI>France Tests 
<LI>Girls-Entrepreneurs 
<LI>Oldest Tree 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Bill v/o </H3>

<P>
The provincial government's controversial omnibus bill is on the
brink of being made law. 
<P>
Third and final reading of bill 26 is under way in the legislature.
Debate on the massive savings and restructuring act began this
morning. 
<HR>

<H3>Measles-Kid </H3>

<P>
A province wide campaign to vaccinate school-children against
measles began today ... amid a swirling debate on the merits of
the program. 
<P>
While medical professionals say, it's the wise thing to do; some
are questioning not only the merits of the program; but the way
in which it is being carried out. 
<HR>

<H3>Plane Crash </H3>

<P>
In Nashville this morning, a US Navy f-14 fighter jet, crashed
into a residential neighborhood killing it's crew and at least
three people on the ground. 
<HR>

<H3>France Tests </H3>

<P>
France is ending its nuclear tests in the south pacific. 
<P>
President Jacques Chirac made the announcement today. He said
the series of underground blasts means France will have a modern
nuclear defence. The sixth and final blast came Saturday night,
and it touched off new protests by environmentalists and countries
in the pacific. 
<HR>

<H3>Girls-Entrepreneurs </H3>

<P>
Lesson's in real life are hard to come by when you're only 12
years old and in grade six. 
<P>
But the Wentworth County Board of Education thinks a new program
designed to spark the entrepreneurial spirit in young women, may
be just the ticket to a lifetime of self sufficiency and financial
independence.... Jamie west explains... 
<P>
<I>These are the nineties right? ...and anything men can do women
can do... just ask Investment Executive Sonia Khurana. </I>
<P>
<I>So to get the message across Entrepreneur Day was held at Highland
Secondary School in Dundas. 91 grade six girls with the help of
local business people, teachers, and older students spending the
day cutting, grinding and hand crafting their way to self sufficiency.
</I>
<P>
<I>Everything from the initial design to the final packaging of
a product is being taught. That's where Junior Achievement Executive
Director Carol Houslander comes in... each young woman will try
to sell enough, jewelry or jewelry trees or gift boxes to cover
a 65 dollar fee to attend a special entrepreneur camp in may called
&quot;inventing your future&quot;. The two day camp will teach
them about the stock market, career options and will feature guest
speakers from the business and media community. </I>
<P>
<I>A similar program for grade six boys is now being planned.
</I>
<P>
<I>In Dundas Jamie West Channel Eleven News. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Oldest Tree </H3>

<P>
Scientists in Tasmania have begun analyzing what could be the
oldest tree in the world.  
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

