<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/25/96</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, January 25, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Cabinet Noon 
<LI>Cabinet - Ontario 
<LI>27000 Civil Servants 
<LI>Exorcism Follow
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Cabinet Noon</H3>

<P>
The Chretien cabinet has a new look today. 
<P>
The Prime Minister shuffled his cabinet with an aim to put a new
face on his government as it tackles looming unity troubles. His
goal is to set the Liberals on a course to fight the next election
and the next referendum, both of which could come in 1997. 
<HR>

<H3>Cabinet - Ontario</H3>

<P>
Today's shuffle affects most of the cabinet members from Ontario...
and there is one new face from this province... as Anthony Pooley
reports. 
<P>
<I>It is perhaps the continuation of a political dynasty in Brant,
with Jane Stewart first elected to the house of commons in 1993,
and today appointed to the Liberal cabinet of Prime Minister Chretien
as Minister of National Revenue. </I>
<P>
<I>Her father, Robert Nixon, never stepped into federal politics,
but served as Ontario's Liberal Leader and later as Treasurer
and Deputy Premier. Stewart is the only new face in cabinet chosen
from among existing members of the liberal caucus. </I>
<P>
<I>Hamilton East's Sheila Copps was among cabinet members who
chose to take their respective oaths of office in both official
languages, as she was sworn in as Heritage Minister and Deputy
PM. In the heritage post, she will play a role in the grits' national
unity strategy. </I>
<P>
<I>Sudbury's Diane Marleau remains in the cabinet as Public Works
Minister. It had been thought that the former Health Minister
would be dropped, but in the cabinet's regional breakdown, she
is the voice of northeastern Ontario and also the only franco-Ontarian
at the cabinet table. </I>
<P>
<I>Former Toronto Mayor Art Eggleton, who represents York centre
in the commons, was moved from treasury board to International
Trade. </I>
<P>
<I>And York west's Sergio Marchi leaves immigration to take over
Copps' old job in environment. </I>
<P>
<I>Anthony Pooley... Channel 11 News.</I> 
<HR>

<H3>27000 Civil Servants </H3>

<P>
Top Conservatives say Ontario has no choice but to cut more civil
servants than originally planned. 
<P>
Last year, the Tories said that about 13 thousand workers could
get pink slips... but today, a Toronto newspaper reported that
number had jumped to 27 thousand. 
<P>
OPSEU officials say the &quot;leaked document&quot; is simply
a tactic to terrorize members during contract talks. 
<HR>

<H3>Exorcism Follow</H3>

<P>
Charges have been dismissed against one person in the exorcism
death of a child in Cambridge. 
<P>
A judge ruled today that there's no evidence that 45 year old
Donatilde Aguiar was aware of what was going on in her home the
night Kira Canhotto died. The two year old girl was killed while
being force fed water. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

