<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/24/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, January 24, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Harris-Bill 26 
<LI>Harris Doc Fraud 
<LI>Harris Trade 
<LI>Cambridge Economy 
<LI>Copps-Heritage 
<LI>Stranded Snow-er 
<LI>Fishermen Rescued 
<LI>Deposition Day 3 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Harris-Bill 26</H3>

<P>
With only four days left before the Harris government presents
its omnibus bill to the legislature, both the public and opposition
parties are desperately trying to delay the vote. 
<P>
Today Liberal Leader Lyn McLeod made a motion that would force
the Premier to appear before a legislative committee to answer
questions on the bill. And then she dropped a bombshell saying
her party had obtained a confidential government document outlining
how 96 million dollars can be chopped from OPP budgets.
<HR>

<H3>Harris Doc Fraud </H3>

<P>
Premier Mike Harris says a lesson can be learned from an outrageous
OHIP claim deliberately filed by a Georgetown Doctor. 
<P>
Dr. Mike Dunn claims he was testing the system when he filed a
false billing for performing a heart-lung transplant at a patient's
home, using a local anesthetic. Dunn was paid for the billing
but says he won't keep the money. 
<P>
The premier says the government will look into whether Dunn should
be punished. 
<HR>

<H3>Harris Trade </H3>

<P>
Premier Mike Harris says the team Canada trade mission to South
Asia was an important step in Ontario's economic recovery that
resulted in more than 50 potential contracts for Ontario companies.

<P>
At a news conference accompanied by over a dozen businessmen who
were on the mission, the Premier voiced his support for Co-ordinate
Ontario Trade Efforts, rather than individual companies looking
for business abroad. 
<P>
Today, Harris was asked about doing business with countries which
employ child labor and do not recognize human rights. 
<HR>

<H3>Cambridge Economy </H3>

<P>
But while the Premier is busy trying to boost business ... many
say, Ontario is going down the drain. Layoffs seem to be everywhere.
Everywhere but Cambridge. 
<HR>

<H3>Copps-Heritage</H3>

<P>
In Ottawa tomorrow, Prime Minister Jean Chretien will be doing
the cabinet shuffle. The Prime Minister is expected to announce
changes early Thursday morning in his federal cabinet. 
<P>
There is much speculation he will dump three of his top ministers
... Foreign Minister Andr&eacute; Ouellet, International Trade
Minister Roy Maclaren and Heritage Minister Michel Dupuy. Deputy
Prime Minister Sheila Copps is expected to shift to the heritage
job from her current environment portfolio. 
<HR>

<H3>Stranded Snow-er </H3>

<P>
A snowmobiler was left stranded in a pond in Sault Ste. Marie
for almost seven hours, despite calls to police. 
<P>
38 year old Gary Marshall was snowmobiling Friday night when his
machine plunged into a pond, stranding him in waist-high water.
When a friend called police, a sergeant said he wouldn't call
rescue crews because the situation wasn't life threatening. 
<P>
Marshall was eventually rescued Saturday morning by the OPP. He
says he plans to file a complaint. 
<HR>

<H3>Fishermen Rescued</H3>

<P>
Meanwhile, three Windsor area men are safe and sound tonight after
spending most of last night on frozen lake St. Clair. The ordeal
began when the three men lost their way in thick fog, then became
stranded by open water. 
<HR>

<H3>Deposition Day 3</H3>

<P>
Ronald Goldman's sister has lashed out at OJ Simpson saying he's
afraid to face her. 
<P>
Simpson's lawyers have barred Kim Goldman from sitting in, on
his deposition, in a wrongful death suit. the suit was brought
by the families of Goldman and Nicole Brown. And Simpson will
be on the hot seat tonight when he sits down with a reporter for
his first televised interview since his acquittal in October.
<I> </I>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

