<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/17/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Wednesday, January 17, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>OFL Strike
<LI>Lankin Health
<LI>Budget Clip
<LI>Casino Preps
<LI>Infectious Diseases 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>OFL Strike</H3>

<P>
The Ontario labor movement has named Hamilton as its next target
for a mass demonstration. 
<P>
The protest is part of labor's fight against the cutbacks and
labor reforms of Ontario's Tory government. 
<P>
The picketing will take place on both Friday February 23rd and
Saturday the 24th, the same week-end the Conservatives are holding
their annual convention in Hamilton. 
<HR>

<H3>Lankin Health </H3>

<P>
NDP Health Critic Frances Lankin says &quot;bill 26&quot; is still
a very bad bill, even with proposed amendments. 
<P>
Health Minister Jim Wilson announced the amendments today. The
amendments include limiting his power to close or merge hospitals
to four years. Lankin and Liberal Leader Lyn McLeod say the amendments
are minimal because the bill would still give Wilson the power
to close hospitals. 
<HR>

<H3>Budget Clip </H3>

<P>
Canada's Finance Minister is being given a blunt warning about
his upcoming federal budget. The commons finance committee says
the government must continue its attack on the deficit. 
<P>
But the Liberal-dominated committee also had some suggestions
for collecting more revenue. They include increasing the taxes
on gasoline and tobacco. 
<P>
Another suggestion would put a tax on lottery winnings ... an
idea rejected last year. 
<HR>

<H3>Casino Preps</H3>

<P>
Canada is being accused of declaring an aesthetic war on US sensibilities
at Niagara falls. 
<P>
An editorial in the Buffalo News charged that the proposed casino
development in the honeymoon city is just another example of Canadians
contaminating Americans view of the falls. 
<HR>

<H3>Infectious Diseases</H3>

<P>
Doctors were once confident they had infectious diseases on the
run. But new data show that these potential killers are surging
back. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

