<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/16/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Tuesday, January 16, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>Golden Report 
<LI>Racism Clip 
<LI>Harris Apologizes 
<LI>PABIAC Regs. 
<LI>Bosnia Clip 
<LI>Russia-Chechnya 
<LI>Yeltsin 
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>Golden Report </H3>

<P>
A task force report released today, is recommending drastic changes
to the political structure and taxing system in the greater Toronto
area. 
<P>
The area affected, stretches from Burlington on the west to beyond
Oshawa in the east. 
<HR>

<H3>Racism Clip </H3>

<P>
A commission on racism in Ontario's justice system has concluded
the problem is rooted in the system itself. 
<HR>

<H3>Harris Apologizes</H3>

<P>
Premier Mike Harris has apologized to dancer Karen Kain, who was
refused entry to the legislature during a protest last November.

<P>
Kain tried to enter the building with petitions signed by ten
thousand people protesting provincial cuts to the arts. 
<P>
Harris wrote Kain last month to say he was &quot;shocked&quot;
to find out she wasn't allowed to deliver the messages to his
office. He thanked her for bringing the petition to his attention
but said the province &quot;is in a financial crisis&quot; and
must take a look at its role in funding activities, including
the arts. 
<HR>

<H3>PABIAC. Regs.</H3>

<P>
At the moment; it is costing us millions. Rehabilitation for more
than 70 brain-injured Canadians, in American facilities, is costing
the province more than it is willing to pay. 
<P>
The government wants to bring these patients home; but at the
moment, a lack of facilities, expertise, and especially standards
could mean, that a different kind of price; could be paid by the
patients. Scot Urquhart reports. 
<P>
<I>The health minister has opened the door ... but is Ontario
ready to bring 80 brain-injured Canadians home from treatment
centers in the states? </I>
<P>
<I>And that's what this meeting, is all about. This is the Provincial
Acquired Brain Injury Advisory Council; or PABIAC. A sort of stakeholders
group representing all of the players, in the brain injury field.
</I>
<P>
<I>And that's where Chris McDonell comes in. She represents CARF:
the American group that sets the standards for accreditation south
of the border.  In a field where Americans have more than two
decades of experience, while Ontario has virtually none, the government
says it will bring Canadian patients home over the next three
years.</I>
<P>
<I>PABIAC is hoping that before they get here, the industry will
not only have standards in place for their treatment, but provincial
regulations, that will require rehabilitation therapists to adhere
to those standards. </I>
<P>
<I>In Toronto, Scot Urquhart Channel Eleven News. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Bosnia Clip</H3>

<P>
Defence officials moved to head off yet another controversy over
the behaviour of peacekeeping troops today, after allegations
surfaced that Canadian soldiers beat patients, hosted wild parties
and had sex with nurses at a mental hospital in Bosnia. 
<P>
The soldiers from Val Cartier Quebec, were assigned to help inmates
at the hospital back in 1994. Defence officials claim the allegations
are unfounded. 
<HR>

<H3>Russia-Chechnya </H3>

<P>
In world news tonight, Russian troops and Chechyn rebels battled
hand-to-hand today among a village's burned-out houses. 
<P>
Federal forces are trying to wipe out the separatists and free
dozens of hostages. Russian security officials say 26 of the hostages
have been released since the Kremlin launched the assault on the
village yesterday. The fate of the 100 or so remaining hostages
is unclear. 
<HR>

<H3>Yeltsin </H3>

<P>
Whenever a government unholsters its military, there is a political
consequence, sometimes good, sometimes not. 
<P>
Those consequences are currently playing out in and around Russia's
new parliament. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

