<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 01/08/96</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Monday, January 8, 1996 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>U.S. Travel 
<LI>U.S. Travel Tag
<LI>Snow Bound 
<LI>Canhotto Sentence 
<LI>York Region Body 
<LI>Subway Inquest 
<LI>College Scabs 
<LI>Bosnia-Mission
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>U.S. Travel</H3>

<P>
One of the worst blizzards of the century have paralyzed much
of the eastern United States, with eight states declaring a state
of emergency. 
<P>
Record snowfalls have stranded thousands of travelers and closed
down businesses and governments. 
<P>
Meanwhile, on this side of the border, phones at travel clubs
are ringing off the hook with would-be tourists looking for updates
on road conditions. Marci Ien reports. 
<P>
<I>They're calling it the blizzard of '96. The worst snow storm
to sweep the northeastern U.S. in over 70 years. </I>
<P>
<I>The blizzard has dumped over 70 centimetres of snow in some
areas--shutting down schools and businesses. </I>
<P>
<I>At least 23 people have died in the storm including two Canadians
killed in separate accidents in Kentucky. </I>
<P>
<I>Major airports in many U.S. cities are closed ...causing big
headaches for travelers... including this basketball team from
McGill University in Montreal. </I>
<P>
<I>In Hamilton, Marci Ien, Channel 11 News. </I>
<HR>

<H3>U.S. Travel Tag</H3>

<P>
And again you are advised to keep off the roads leading south...but
if you find yourself out there ...travel expert Dave Hunter says
the I-75 is your best bet because there are plenty of reasonable
motels along the route in case of emergency. 
<HR>

<H3>Snow Bound</H3>

<P>
A Guelph University student and a pal from Brock University say
they're lucky to be alive today. 
<P>
The two got lost while on a skiing holiday in Vermont... and spent
a bone-chilling night on top of a mountain.
<HR>

<H3>Canhotto Sentence</H3>

<P>
A Cambridge woman will return to court on Wednesday to be sentenced
in the death of her 2-year-old grand- daughter. 
<P>
43-year-old Anna Marie Canhotto has pleaded guilty to manslaughter
in the death of Kiro Canhotto last January. The child died during
a ritual in which she was force fed water to rid her of the devil.

<P>
Three others were charged in the case, including the girl's mother,
who will be sentenced later this year. 
<HR>

<H3>York Region Body</H3>

<P>
Police are still searching for the killer of a York Region baker
found shot to death in his mini-van. 
<P>
The body of Frank Loiero was found riddled with bullets in the
parking lot of a mall in Woodbridge, northwest of Toronto. Police
say he was visiting a relative last night when he took a phone
call around 7:30 and went outside. A short while later he was
found dead. 
<HR>

<H3>Subway Inquest</H3>

<P>
Last summer's deadly subway accident in Toronto was the result
of failure at many levels says Crown Attorney Chris Punter. He
told an inquest into the crash that the transit control centre
had little or no control over trains in the tunnel... and despite
reports of a faulty signal throughout the day the device was never
fixed. 
<P>
An internal TTC report says driver Robert Jeffrey went through
three red lights before the accident. Punter says the inquest
will focus on the tendency of some drivers to &quot;cheat the
system&quot; in order to keep their trains on schedule. 
<HR>

<H3>College Scabs</H3>

<P>
A Toronto visa school for international students ,has locked out
its teachers in a contract dispute, and hired replacements. Its
the first incident of such action since new labor laws went into
effect in Ontario. 
<HR>

<H3>Bosnia-Mission</H3>

<P>
Canadian soldiers are going to Bosnia armed with a list of do's
and don'ts. They have been issued a small card detailing the rules
of engagement, including a reminder to soldiers that the torture
of civilians is not allowed. This time, Canada's military doesn't
want to take any chances. 
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

