<HEAD>
<TITLE>Interformat On-Line Editing</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 <HR>

<H1><CENTER>Interformat On-Line Editing</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
On-line editing refers to the final packaging of audio-video material.
It involves the electronic &quot;cutting&quot; of pictures and
sound as well as adding special effects, digital effects, graphics
and voice overs.
<P>
Our primary on-line suite is an interformat design, that accomodates
both Betacam and 1&quot;, with a/b/c roll playback/record options
to either format. The suite incorporates Chyron titling, an NEC
System 10 Unit for Digital Effects, a Grass Valley 200 switcher...
and is completely automated for on-lining from EDL's.<HR>

<P>
BETA EDIT: VPE141 EDITOR Super Edit Software
<UL>
<LI>Slaves up to 9 sources including record VTR
<LI>Switcher set-up stored in EDL
<LI>Full edit list management including 409 and TRACE
<LI>Translates EDL files from CMX, Convergence, Calaway or IBM
text
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
SWITCHER: Grass Valley 200-2 production switcher
<UL>
<LI>Streamline menu function with Key Frame and Timeline
<LI>20 inputs
<LI>2 - M/E with 4 effects keyers
<LI>additional 40 matrix wipes
<LI>2 - Mattes and background generators
<LI>Dual Component Chroma key
<LI>Disk storage of swithcer set-up
<LI>1 - downstream keyer
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
DIGITAL EFFECTS: NEC System 10 featuring:
<UL>
<LI>rotation
<LI>perspective
<LI>expansion
<LI>page turn
<LI>infinite compression
<LI>variable cropping
<LI>A/B switching
<LI>100 event memory
<LI>off-line storage on micro-floppy disks
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
GRAPHICS: Chyron 4100 EXB Dual Channel character generator
<UL>
<LI>Two 8&quot; disk drives
<LI>Channel combine module (CCM)
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
VIDEO TAPE FACILITIES
<UL>
<LI>1 - Sony 3100 1&quot; Master record
<LI>2 - Sony BVW 75
<LI>1 - Sony BVW 65 - playback only
<LI>Telecom Research time-code generator
<LI>Capability of adding alternate machine when customer requires
<LI>2 - 20 inch Ikegami colour monitors for input/output of machines
<LI>8 monochrome monitors for previewing sources
<LI>1 VHS machine
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
AUDIO CONSOLE: GRAHAM PATTEN SYSTEM 616 E.S.A.M.
<UL>
<LI>16 main frame inputs with programmable transition rates
<LI>stereo and mono outputs
<LI>Monitoring via 2 - Auratone 5C or Auratone T6
<LI>1 Otari 4 track 1/4&quot; stereo reel to reel deck
<LI>1 Technics SLP-555 CD player
<LI>1 Sony cassette deck
<LI>1 QSC1200 power amp (stereo)
</UL>
<HR>

