<HEAD>

<TITLE>1" On-Line Editing</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">
<HR>

<H1><CENTER>1&quot; On-Line Editing</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
On-line editing refers to the final packaging for air of audio-video
material. It involves the electronic &quot;cutting&quot; of pictures
and sound as well as adding special effects, digital effects,
graphics and voice overs.
<P>
Our 1&quot; suite offers a/b roll editing from 1&quot; stock to
a 1&quot; master as well as providing producers with access to
switcher effects, an NEC System 10 DVE, and a Chyron &quot;Scribe&quot;
for titling. <HR>

<P>
ONE INCH EDIT SYSTEM: SONY BVE-3000A EDITOR
<UL>
<LI>3 - Sony BVH-1100A VTR machines 2 - Playback , 1 - Record
<LI>Grass Valley GVG100 switcher, 10 inputs with Key mem
<LI>Sony Trinitron Playback monitor
<LI>4 -- Electrohome B &amp; W monitors for source monitoring
<LI>Telecom Research TimeCode centre
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
SWITCHER: GVG 100 Digital Switcher
<UL>
<LI>10 inputs
<LI>1 Key Bus, 1 Downstream key
<LI>Chroma key (studio camera only)
<LI>No Disk Storage, Key Mem only
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
DIGITAL EFFECTS: NEC System 10 featuring:
<UL>
<LI>rotation
<LI>perspective
<LI>expansion
<LI>page turn
<LI>infinite compression
<LI>variable cropping
<LI>A/B switching
<LI>100 event memory
<LI>off-line storage on micro-floppy disks
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
GRAPHICS: Chyron Super Scribe character generator
<UL>
<LI>1 -- 5&quot; disk drive
<LI>Font Conversion Available
<LI>1 Panasonic colour monitor for operator, 1 B&amp;W Electrohome
for Menu
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
