<HEAD>

<TITLE>Off-Line Editing</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 <HR>

<P>
<CENTER><H1>Off-Line Editing</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
Off line editing refers to the preliminary editing of audio/video
material on a less sophisticated videotape format, to save time
and money when it comes to the final polish or &quot;On-Line&quot;.

<P>
Our Off-Line facilities consist of a/b capable BetacamSP playback
to a 3/4&quot; recorder. A complete EDL (edit decision List) can
be extracted in print or on disk for transfer to either CMX, GVG,
or Sony configurations, for on-line. <HR>

<P>
<CENTER>Contact: Jim McDougall, Wayne Doan or Wilf Venne, (905)
522-1101, Toronto Direct Line 366-9688, Fax: (905) 527-5022 or
<BR>
E-mail your questions or comments to
<A HREF="mailto:production@chch.wic.ca">production@chch.wic.ca</A></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
