<HEAD>

<TITLE>Audio Post-Production Facilities</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 <HR>

<P>
<CENTER> 
<H1>Audio Post-Production</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../gifs/audio.gif"></CENTER><HR>

<P>
Our Audio Post-Production facility allows for the creation of
a fully &quot;sweetened&quot; soundtrack including original sound,
music, sound effects, and Foley effects... as well as input from
digital media and samplers.<HR>

<P>
YAMAHA 2408 MULTI TRACK CONSOLE
<UL>
<LI>24 main frame mic/line inputs, each with 3-band EQ., stereo
pans, &amp; dual aux capability
<LI>In-line mixdown
<LI>8 track-masters, each with A/B outputs which feed multi track
machine
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
ADAMS-SMITH 2600AV SYNCHRONIZER
<UL>
<LI>Ability to Vari-lock speed of machines
<LI>Ability to cross-lock different timecode rates
<LI>Ability to trigger other devices with G.P.I.s or MIDI
</UL>

<P>
Sync-locks to the following 5 machines:
<UL>
<LI>Ampex MM1200 16-track machine
<LI>BVU 800 3/4&quot; with burn-in timecode
<LI>Studer A80 1&quot; layback machine
<LI>Studer A810 1/4&quot; reel to reel
<LI>Fostex D20B DAT machine<BR>

</UL>

<P>
PLUS
<UL>
<LI>Tascam 601 CD player, G.P.I. triggered by 2600AV
<LI>Sony DAT machine, G.P.I. triggered by 2600AV
<LI>Akai S1100 and S1100 EX Sampler with 64 meg RAM, Midi triggered
by 2600AV
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
ANCILLARY AUDIO FACILITIES
<UL>
