<HEAD>

<TITLE>Stephen Benedict Biography</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 <HR>

<H1><CENTER>Stephen Benedict</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
Stephen Benedict is an accomplished Producer, Director, and Writer
with more than fifteen years experience in both studio and location
production. As a credit to his abilities and versatility, Stephen
offers an expansive breadth of production involvements in television
formats ranging from comedy, through music performance and &quot;live
events&quot;, to commercials and documentaries.
<P>
Consistently honoured with numerous awards for commercial and
program producing and directing, Stephen has shot on locations
across Europe and the Caribbean, as well as extensively here in
Canada. Stephen has worked with major Canadian and international
talents, including names like Polly Draper, Alan Thicke, Steve
Smith, and &quot;Weird&quot; Al Yankovich, plus musical artists
like Jeff Healy, Triumph, The Northern Pikes, Blue Rodeo, Colin
James, Kim Mitchell and many more. Whether in the studio or on
location, Stephen delivers a consistently imaginative, original
and professional product.
<P>
Some of Stephen's commercial and promotional production credits
have included projects for:
<UL>
<LI>Lakeport Breweries
<LI>The Art Gallery Of Hamilton
<LI>The Hamilton Canucks
<LI>The Hamilton Tigercats
<LI>Y95 Radio
<LI>CHAM Radio
<LI>Theatre Aquarius
<LI>Northern Telecom
<LI>McMaster University
<LI>The Children's Aid Society
<LI>Q107 Radio
<LI>The Family Channel (Canada)
</UL>

<P>
... with a numerous list of retail clients who rely on his winning
sense of marketing and production to generate effective, creative
product for their businesses.<HR>

<P>
<CENTER>For further information, contact: Jim McDougall, (905)
522-1101, ext. 251,
<P>
Toronto Direct Line 366-9688, Fax: (905) 645-3217 or
<P>
E-mail your questions or comments to
<A HREF="mailto:production@chch.wic.ca">production@chch.wic.ca</A></CENTER>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER>CHCH Television, 163 Jackson Street West, Hamilton, Ontario,
L8N 3A6, Canada</CENTER><P>
