<HEAD>

<TITLE>Steve Lambert Biography</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 <HR>

<H1><CENTER>Steve Lambert</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
I have been a resident of the hallowed halls of CHCH for eighteeen
years. It is true when they say time goes fast when you're having
fun. I came to CHCH in 1977 after completing the three year Television
Broadcasting course at Mohawk College here in Hamilton. After
spending a year in the Props Department I took a position in the
Videotape Department which involved running on-air programming
and various stories for the newscasts. January, 1983 marked my
transition to becoming a film and videotape &quot;Screener&quot;
where I learned to edit shows and movies and first noticed my
hair was going a little grey!
<P>
A job opening in Program Promotion in September of 1986 catapulted
me into a whole new creative environment. Along with producing
and scheduling the daily on-air promotional spots, each year I
helped write and produce our Fall Sales Presentation, which highlights
the upcoming seasons' programming. In September, 1994, with a
few more grey hairs intact, I moved over to Commercial Production
and have found the many new challenges to be quite rewarding.
<P>
During my time here at CHCH, I have also been involved with C.A.B.E.,
the Canadian Association of Broadcast Employees, the internal
employee association, and am currently serving my third term as
Vice-President. As for the future, I, like you, am &quot;staying
tuned...&quot;<HR>

<P>
<CENTER>For further information, contact: Jim McDougall, (905)
522-1101, ext. 251,
<P>
Toronto Direct Line 366-9688, Fax: (905) 645-3217 or
<P>
E-mail your questions or comments  to
<A HREF="mailto:production@chch.wic.ca">production@chch.wic.ca</A></CENTER>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER>CHCH Television, 163 Jackson Street West, Hamilton, Ontario,
L8N 3A6, Canada</CENTER>

