<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Patsy!" A Musical Tribute to Patsy Cline</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">


<CENTER><IMG SRC="pat2.jpg"></CENTER>
<CENTER><H1>About The Show</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
Patsy Cline's 5 song legacy of <I>She's Got You</i>, <I>Crazy</I>, <I>Sweet Dreams</I>, <I>I Fall To Pieces</I> and <I>Walkin' After Midnight</I> has been called the greatest in the history of Country Music.  These 5 classics form the core of the 22 songs around which <B>Patsy!</B> is built.  The 2 hour show features an outstanding six piece band, a quartet of backing vocalists and, of course, Patsy, all live on stage as her dramatic life and phenomenal career are traced from the Honky Tonks of Virginia to the Grand Ole Opry, Las Vegas and Carnegie Hall.  Some very funny comedy is thrown in to the mix to ensure a memorable evening at the theatre.
<P>
<B>Patsy!</B> was honoured on November 5, 1995 with three major awards in Branson, Missouri... Best New Musical, Best New Female Performer (Gail Bliss as Patsy) and Best Backup Vocal Group.  The show ran 10 months in Boston, 6 months in Kansas City, toured to sold out houses in 75 U.S. cities and just wrapped up an 8 month stint at Branson's 4,000 seat Grande Palace Theatre.
<P>
We're sure you'll agree that <B>Patsy!</B> is also destined to be a monster hit in Nashville North (otherwise known as Toronto).

<HR>
