<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Queen Elizabeth Theatre</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><H1>The Queen Elizabeth Theatre</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
The Queen Elizabeth Theatre seats 1,309 people with 936 Orchestra Seats and 373 Mezzanine Seats.  Sightlines are excellent with the Mezzanine not overhanging the Orchestra Section but rather being a raised section at the back of the theatre.  Legroom is very generous and the refurbished seats are wide and extremely comfortable.
<P>
The Theatre is fully air conditioned and fully wheelchair accessible.  Acoustics are excellent.  There is a 450 seat restaurant on the second floor of the Theatre which is accessible both by a sweeping marble staircase from the Lobby, and by elevator.

<H2>Map to the Queen Elizabeth Theatre:</H2>

<CENTER><A HREF="thtrmap.jpg"><IMG SRC="thmapsml.jpg"></A></CENTER>
<CENTER><A HREF="thtrmap.jpg">Click to display a larger map.</A></CENTER>



