<TITLE>What the Critics are saying about "Patsy!"</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<CENTER><H1>What Critics are Saying About &quot;Patsy!&quot;</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>

<B>&quot;The two-hour evening is a foot-stomping, hand clapping, heartwarming delight for die-hard Cline fans and the curious and uninitiated alike&quot;</B> - Carl Lebovitz, Journal Gazette
<P>
<B>&quot;Bliss is a sensaysh carbon of Cline, vocally and visually and the audience cheered her every rendition of Cline's hits!&quot;</B> - Daily Variety
<P>
<B>&quot;Bliss works her way through such hits as <I>Crazy, Walkin' After Midnight, Sweet Dreams, I Fall to Pieces</I> and 18 other Cline tunes yodeling, caressing, belting and wooing the audience.&quot;</B> - Quad City Times
<P>
<B>&quot;Nothing's been overlooked - especially recreating Cline herself!&quot;</B> - The Kansas City Star
<P>
<B>&quot;I knew Patsy better than anyone and she would have loved this show... you've got to see it!&quot;</B> - Charlie Dick, Patsy Cline's Husband
