<HEAD>

<TITLE>About Caption Resource Centre</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H1><CENTER><I>Caption Resource Centre</CENTER></I></H1>
<HR>

<H3><CENTER><I>Opening the Pathways of Communication</CENTER></I>
</H3>

<P>
The Caption Resource Centre is located in Oakville Ontario, Canada.
  Its primary function is to provide operating space and office
services to not-for-profit or not-yet-profitable organizations
whose missions are to improve the quality or increase the quantity
of closed captioning in Canada.
<P>
The CRC is philanthropic in nature and provides its services and
facilities at cost.  The occupant organizations benefit from the
resulting synergy of sharing facilities, staff and expertise,
all of which is crucial to their survival.
<P>
To occupy space at the CRC, the organization must qualify in all
three of the following:
<OL>
<LI>Its primary mission must be to improve the quality or increase
the quantity of  closed captioning for the deaf and hard of hearing
in Canada.
<LI>It must be a not-for-profit, charitable or not-yet-profitable
organization.
<LI>Should a profit making organization become financially successful,
the CRC reserves the right to charge for services at fair market
value or to terminate the organizations occupancy.
</OL>

<P>

<P>
Presently there are four organizations at the CRC.  <A HREF="cci.htm">Canada Caption
Inc.</A>, <A HREF="lobco.htm">LOBCO Inc.</A>, <A HREF="chouse.htm">Caption Clearinghouse</A>, and <A HREF="cacc.htm">Canadian Association of Captioning Consumers</A>.
<H3><CENTER><I>Caption Resource Centre</I></H3>

<H3>443 Reynolds St.</H3>

<H3>Oakville, Ontario</H3>

<H3>L6J 3M5</H3>

<H3>Phone: (905) 338-1246</H3>

<H3>Fax: (905) 338-7483</CENTER></H3>
<HR>

<CENTER>| <A HREF="../crc.htm">Return to the <I>Caption Resource Centre</I> Home Page</A> |</CENTER>

<CENTER>| Send your questions or comments to: <A HREF="mailto:captions@captions.org">captions@captions.org</A> |</CENTER>


