<HEAD>

<TITLE>About LOBCO Inc.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H1><CENTER>LOBCO Inc.</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<H3><CENTER>To Be Seen Is To Be Heard</CENTER> </H3>

<P>
 
<P>
Established in 1990, LOBCO Inc. enjoys diverse corporate activity
which, in itself, is its most outstanding quality.  It is an organization
which has no template to follow.  Every accomplishment represents
precedent setting work and original thought.
<P>
As a consultant, LOBCO Inc. works with television broadcasts in
implementing operations policy and procedures related to social
issues.  CanWest Global, Baton Broadcasting and CBC are just a
few of the many institutions LOBCO Inc. works with to ensure positive
feedback from consumer groups, government and other authorities
that may influence issues from time to time.
<P>
Its efforts with Rogers Cablesystems in creating a Closed Caption
decoder program has allowed potentially 20,000 deaf, deafened
and hard of hearing people access to closed captioned programming.
 The framework for this decoder program has been utilized by most
cable operators across Canada.
<P>
LOBCO Inc. created <A HREF="cci.htm">Canada Caption Inc.</A>, a charitable organization
dedicated to finding funds for the closed captioning of Canadian
programming.  As an entrepreneurial charity, its business strategy
is based on a win/win scenario that has proven very successful.
<P>
In creating <A HREF="cci.htm">Canada Caption Inc.</A>, LOBCO Inc. established a network
of corporate sponsors allowing the company to caption over 2500
hours of Canadian programming in 1995.
<P>
Research is a quality for which LOBCO Inc. is noted.  Its expertise
in the area of captioning has been called upon for two major research
undertakings.  LOBCO Inc. has provided its expertise in the area
of Canadian captioning to table &quot;The Monitor Project&quot;
and &quot;Key Issues in Canadian Captioning&quot; in association
with the Canadian Captioning Development Agency, and The Department
of Communications, now called The Department of Canadian Heritage.
<P>
Its recommendations are now becoming guidelines for industry standards.
<P>
In conjunction with Sheridan College and <A HREF="cci.htm">Canada Caption Inc.</A>,
LOBCO Inc. completed an in-depth study on the effects of captioning
on language acquisition for English as a second language learners.
 Like the previous study, this project will set a new precedent,
influencing English as a second language curriculum for future
learners across Canada.
<P>
As LOBCO Inc. creates bonds in its client base and mirrors the
diversification of the industries it represents, it is charged
with highly motivated result oriented human resources.
<P>
Its method of establishing a strategy and following it through
is LOBCO Inc.'s calling card.  It prides itself in successfully
competing the work it sets out to do.
<P>
Beverley Ostafichuk, founder and President of LOBCO Inc. has an
entrepreneurial spirit that is the driving force behind LOBCO
Inc.'s success.  Ever the optimist, LOBCO Inc. believes in creating
opportunity where none existed.<HR>


