<HEAD>

<TITLE>VoiceWriter(tm)</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H1><CENTER>VoiceWriter(tm)</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<H3><CENTER>Breaking through barriers and captioning the future</CENTER>
</H3>

<P>
Captioning is a time consuming expensive process.  It takes eight
to sixteen times the video time to fully caption a program.  As
a result there are few captioned programs and those that are captioned
are done poorly.  
<P>
 
<P>
VoiceWriterTM is a closed captioning, non-linear application that
increases productivity by 50% with a significant long term reduction
in cost.  This application has been Beta Tested by the closed
captioning professionals and meets all of the industry's requirements.
<P>
It is a MS Windows based application which is tightly coupled
with the hardware.  The GUI (Graphical User Interface) allows
caption editors to create captions with the use of  the keyboard,
mouse and voice recognition.  
<P>
Voice recognition allows the end user to navigate and dictate
within VoiceWriterTM.  It is speaker independent and allows end
users to fine-tune or create voice driven commands or text.
<P>
What's unique about VoiceWriterTM is the fact that it is the only
voice recognition captioning system available today.  This disk
based captioning system gives the captioner the ability to quickly
access the location of the text that is required.
<P>
Meeting all FCC regulations, the system follows the EIA-608 recommended
practice for line 21 data service in NTSC and PAL environments.
 For added simplicity the VoiceWriterTM style guide gives Captioning
Editors an On-line reference for industry captioning standards.
<P>
With continued research and development VoiceWriterTM's target
date is September 1, 1996 for real-time captioning with continuous
voice recognition.  
<P>
As a result of the evolving technology the CRTC (Canadian Radio
and Television Commission) issued a mandate (1995-48) requiring
every broadcaster in Canada billing over 10 million dollars per
year to caption all live news programming by September 1, 1998
and 90% of all programming by their next licence renewal.  
<P>
The technology is available today for broadcasters to caption
100% of their programming.   With VoiceWriterTM the target can
be met by 1996.
<H3><CENTER>For more information on this 100% functional system
contact: </H3>

<H3>Beverley Ostafichuk at (905) 338-1246.</CENTER></H3>
<HR>

