<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Caption Clearinghouse</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<H1><CENTER>The Caption Clearinghouse</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<H3><CENTER>Always better the second time around</CENTER> </H3>

<P>
The Caption Clearinghouse is a provider of second-run closed captioning
to Canadian and International Broadcasters.  It archives the accumulated
captions for programs that have already been aired and are now
being purchased by alternate broadcasters for rebroadcast.  The
master copies of these programs are not captioned and as a result
the acquiring broadcaster must seek out the captions independently.
<P>
The Caption Clearinghouse acts as a library, compiling captions
and providing them to broadcasters making it much simpler and
less expensive for broadcasters to acquire the captions.  If the
requested captions are not on file, The Caption Clearinghouse
will undertake the job of searching for and retrieving the captions
on behalf of the broadcaster.  The Caption Clearinghouse acts
as a clearinghouse for all second-run captions and undertakes
searches for international captions.  Most second-run captions
will be readily available making it cheaper and less time consuming
for broadcasters to caption second-run programming.  This will
leave the broadcasters captioning budget intact allowing them
to use these funds to caption programs that have not previously
been captioned.
<P>
The Caption Clearinghouse is also a library of reports, studies
and any evaluative documentation that has been done in relation
to closed captioning.  The Caption Clearinghouse compiles information
related to captioning for the deaf and hard of hearing as well
as alternative uses for captioning as in English as a Second Language
(ESL), and literacy applications.  It is a lending library of
these resource materials to reference libraries and interested
organizations internationally.
<P>
The Caption Clearinghouse also provides volume discount rates
for both offline and online captioning without compromise of captioning
quality.
<P>
The Caption Clearinghouse is a self-sustaining entity, operated
on a non-profit basis.  Any revenue generated distributing second-run
captions or brokering captions will only support the operational
overhead and staffing requirements of the Caption Clearinghouse.
<P>
Summary of Benefits
<UL>
<LI>Broadcasters are able to retrieve captions easily and in little
time, with one phone call.
<LI>The captions are provided at a reduced cost and in a timely
manner;
<LI>Lower costs result in more programs being closed captioned;
<LI>Centralized library will make information known and accessible
to all interested organizations.
</UL>

<P>

<P>
There is no charge to deposit your captions at The Caption Clearinghouse,
and the integrity of the captions will remain intact indefinitely
.
<P>
For more information or to take advantage of The Caption Clearinghouse
solution to a 100% captioned broadcast day , please contact Ramona
Perini at (905) 338-1246.
<H3><CENTER>At The Caption Clearinghouse</H3>

<H3>WE CARE FOR YOUR CAPTIONS</CENTER></H3>
<HR>

