<HEAD>

<TITLE>CISA TV, Lethbridge, Alta.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/cisa.gif"></CENTER>
<CENTER>1401 - 28 Street North, Lethbridge, Alberta, T1J 4A4</CENTER><BR>
<CENTER>Tel.: (403) 327-1521  Fax: (403) 320-2620</CENTER>


<P>
The story of Lethbridge Television is in fact the story of 
television broadcasting in Southern Alberta.  CJLH TV as it 
was known then was the first TV station on the air south of 
Calgary, and it remains first in the hearts of many to this 
day.  It was November 20th, 1955 when the power switch was 
thrown, and Channel 7 - CJLH TV, a network affiliate of the 
Canadian Broadcasting Corporation was officially on the air.  
Over the course of the next 40 years the station has assumed 
many changes in call letters.  From CJLH, we became CJOC, then 
CFAC, next was 2&7 Lethbridge and now we are known as 2&7 CISA. 
CISA was chosen to signify "Canadian Independent Southern Alberta".         

<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
