<HEAD>

<TITLE>CITV, Edmonton, Alta.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/itv.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>5325 - 104th Street, Edmonton, Alberta, T6H 5B8</CENTER><BR>
<CENTER>Tel.: (403) 436-1250 or 1-800-301-6414, Fax: (403) 434-4732</CENTER><HR>

<P>
A new image campaign, innovative sales promotion initiatives,
increased emphasis on news and an intensified focus on commercial
production were key elements of ITV'S
strategy in fiscal 1994. Under the direction of Barry Duggan,
who was appointed President in January 1994, ITV introduced its
new image. All creative work on the logo and image was done inhouse
and post-production was provided by Studio Post &amp; Transfer.
ITV now produces 24.5 hours of live local news and sports each
week. A new set has been introduced and personnel added to increase
the station's already competitive position. ITV News is also offered
by Edmonton cable operator Videotron as part of the Videoway interactive
system. This system allows viewers to call up additional information
on a particular topic within the newscast. The Allarcom soundstage,
part of ITV's impressive studio facilities, was selected as the
production facility for filming of the interior scenes for the
series Destiny Ridge.

<HR>

