<HEAD>

<TITLE>Family Channel Canada</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<H1><CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/family.gif"></CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
Canada's &quot;national family network&quot; experienced a 4 per
cent growth in the number of subscribers during fiscal 1994. The
Family Channel features high-quality entertainment with up to
60 per cent of programming coming from the Disney Channel; of
the remaining 40 per cent, 25 per cent is Canadian and 15 per
cent foreign.
<P>
The Family Channel's application for a national animation specialty
service entitled The Cartoon Network was denied by the CRTC. However,
the Family Channel may reapply in 1995 if and when, as has been
suggested, the CRTC calls for submissions for further licensing
of specialty channels.
<P>
Allarcom Pay Television owns 50 per cent of the Family Channel.

