<HEAD>

<TITLE>Home Theatre Pay-Per-View</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/homethea.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER> 

<P>
WIC's pay-per-view service offers audiences additional entertainment
choices in the comfort of their own homes. Home Theatre competes
with video rentals in both price and product, and beats the video
store hands-down in convenience. Home Theatre's multi-channel
service delivers movies that recently ended their theatrical releases,
and special events, such as boxing, wrestling and concerts, in
response to the viewer's phone-activated request.
<P>
Home Theatre is available to basic cable subscribers with addressable converter/decoders
provided by their cable company.
<P>
An average of 50 per cent of houses with access to Home Theatre
take advantage of the service, renting at least one movie every
month. 


