<HEAD>

<TITLE>Talk 640/Q107 Toronto, Ont.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../images/talk640.gif" ALT="Talk640 Logo" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=122 BORDER=0> <IMG SRC="../images/q107.gif" ALT="Q107 Logo" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=88 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>
<H1><CENTER>Talk 640 and <A HREF="http://www.Q107.com">Q107</A>,
Toronto, Ont.</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
Q107, with its solidly focused music direction and innovative
marketing initiatives, has achieved strong ratings results, boasting
listenership in excess of 697,000 to remain firmly entrenched
as English Canada's No.1 rock station. The annual Q107 Rock Awards
took on a new dimension this year when the station combined with
WIC television station CHCH to produce a highlights show that
ran in the country's top three markets.
<P>
In October 1995, AM640 became the last of the Westcom AM stations to
make the switch to news, talk, sports and information programming.  AM640
is now known as &quot;Talk 640 - Toronto's Information Station&quot;.  Previously,
the teen-oriented AM640 had provided daytime talk programming, specifically
oriented to its younger audience.  Now, Talk 640 caters to a more mature listener
and features both local and national news, talk, sports and information programming,
24 hours-a-day, seven days-a-week.


<HR>

