<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHED/Power 92 Radio</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../gifs/ched.gif"><IMG SRC="../gifs/power.gif">
</CENTER>
<H1><CENTER>CHED and POWER 92</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
630 CHED became &quot;Alberta's Information Superstation&quot;
on December 1, 1993. With its service in news, talk, sports and
information. CHED moved from the bottom to the top of the AM ranking
for adults 25 years and older in Edmonton's central market. <BR>
Power 92, a contemporary hits FM station targeted to listeners
aged 18 to 34, enjoys the No. 1 ranking overall in Edmonton's
central market. This marketing position as &quot;Today's Best
Music,&quot; and coupled with an aggressive marketing and promotions
campaign helped move Power 92 ahead of all other AM and FM stations
serving Edmonton. <HR>

<H3>Management</H3>

<UL>
<LI>Doug Rutherford - President And General Manager
<LI>Wayne Keen - General Sales Manager
<LI>Pat Cardinal - Manager
<LI>Diana Davis - Business Manager
<LI>Tom Davies - Chief Engineer
<LI>C. R. Nichols - News Director
</UL>


<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
<TABLE COLSPACE=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0 BORDER=0>
