<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHML Hamilton, Ont.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/chml.gif" ALT="CHML Logo" WIDTH=256 HEIGHT=71 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I>Hometown Radio</I>, CHML, Hamilton, Ont.</H1>
</CENTER>

<HR>

<P>
Founded in 1927, Hamilton-born <B>CHML</B> is the area's undisputed leader for news, talk, sports and 
information programming.  At 900Khz and 50,000 watts, <B>CHML</B> is recognized as Hamilton's &quot;first 
choice for news&quot;.  Strong on-air personalities deliver informative, entertaining and national award-winning 
talk radio.  A selection of information and specialty music programming.
<P>
<B>CHML</B> is the proud voice of the Hamilton Tiger Cats, and also broadcasts play-by-play coverage of
Maple Leaf Hockey, Blue Jay Baseball, Raptor Basketball and our new American Hockey League Team the 
Hamilton Bulldogs.
<P>
With it's strong support of community events, charities and local promotions since 1927, it's easy to see how 
<B>CHML</B> has established itself as &quot;Hometown Radio&quot;, a term that has been synonymous with
the City of Hamilton.
<P>
Combined with sister station <A HREF="y95.htm">Classic Rock Y95</A>, the two stations deliver more than
half of the audience reached by Hamilton radio stations.
<P>



