<HEAD>

<TITLE>Y95 Hamilton, Ont.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/y95.gif" ALT="Y95 Logo" WIDTH=290 HEIGHT=151 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I>Classic Rock</I>, Y95, Hamilton, Ont.</H1>
</CENTER>

<HR>

<P>
Labour Day weeken 1991, a 100,000 watt powerhouse was born.  <B>Classic Rock Y95</B> filled 
a major format void with classic rock from the 60's, 70's, 80's and today, including artists like The Doors,
Eric Clapton, The Rolling Stones, April Wine, The Eagles, Elton John and Bob Dylan.
<P>
Promotionally agressive, <B>Y95</B> has sent listeners to all four corners of the world and awarded
prizes of every shape, colour and size.  The on-air personalities are as diverse as they are entertaining
and informative, each on bringing a new ingredient to the Classic Rock menu.
<P>
At 95.3 Mhz, <B>Y95</B> dominates the airwaves of Southern Ontario with a cumulative audience of nearly 
400,000 listeners, and average quarter hours numbering 25,000 (Spring 1996 BBM).  <B>Y95</B> is positioned
as the fourth largest rock station in Canada!
<P>
Combined with sister station <A HREF="chml.htm">AM 900 CHML</A>, the two stations deliver more than
half of the audience reached by Hamilton radio stations.
<P>

