<HEAD>

<TITLE>KIK-FM, Calgary, Alta.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../images/kikfm.gif" ALT="KIK-FM Logo" WIDTH=314 HEIGHT=182 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<H1><I>Rock 107 - The New KIK FM</I>, Calgary, Alta.</H1>
</CENTER>

<HR>

<P>
<B>Rock 107</B> is the continuing evolution of Calgary's premiere rock station.  Even though
CKIK was the second rock FM station to sign on in Calgary, it has always been the trailblazer.  <B>Rock 107</B>
has had an eclectic heritage, ranging from its initial &quot;Ball to the Wall&quot; approach in the early 
80's, to its current hybrid New Rock/Rock format.  This format has been in place since March 1996.
<P>
<B>CKIK</B> signed on in 1982 as a hard rock station.  Its high level of community involvement and 
broadcasting standards have engendered uncommon loyalty among its core audience.  The radio station
supports, among other causes: The Sheriff King Home for Battered Women and Children, The Alberta Lung
Association, The Alberta Children's Hospital Foundation, and the United Way as well as many smaller 
community groups.
<P>
<B>Rock 107</B>'s on-air team is currently led by the morning tandem of Roger Rhodes and Spyder O'Neil, 
who are both ably assisted by Stew the Producer guy.
<P>
The mid-day is held down by 19 year veteran, and 7 year KIK-ster Paul Boucher.  The afternoon drive is taken 
care of by our import ringer, and Assistant Program Director, Carter Brown.  Zenon West, the longest serving KIK
announcer has been around - on and off - since the beginning in 1982, and he covers the evening scene in 
Calgary better than anyone else out there.
<P>
Our management staff, with the exception of Program Director, is shared with our sister AM station 
<A HREF="qr77.htm">QR 77</A>.
<P>
<B>Rock 107</B> also has one of the premiere radio station websites, run in-house by Paul Boucher with expert
outside assistance from Passageway Communications, and supplier Nucleus Information Service.  
<P>

