<HEAD>

<TITLE>CJOB Radio</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../gifs/cjob.gif"></CENTER> 
<H1><CENTER>CJOB and 97.5 CLASSIC, Winnipeg, Man.</CENTER></H1>
<HR>

<P>
Winnipeg's No. 1 station, CJOB, is known as &quot;Manitoba's Information
Station.&quot;  Repeatedly setting the day's agenda in news, weather,
sports, traffic and talk. From breaking news and sports stories,
to health care documentaries and senate petitions.
<P>
Classic Rock 97.5FM is the only radio station in the Winnipeg
market that has continually grown in the last six BBMs.  The station
boasts the highest share of male listeners aged 25 to 54 in Winnipeg.
 Promotions, from concerts to sporting events, further raised
the station's profile.  An outdoor campaign was developed to position
the radio station and inform Winnipeg of 97.5's mix of classic
rock and its strong on-air personalities.
<P>
CJOB and 97.5FM's involvement in the community was highlighted
by an all-out campaign for the United Way.  In one day, more than
$50,000 was raised.  Both radio stations continue to work with
the many worthy organizations in Winnipeg, through fundraising
and public service.  Some of the organizations that benefit are
the Heart &amp; Stroke Foundation, Christmas Cheer Board, Alzheimer
Society, Red Cross and Big Brothers.<HR>

<H3>Management</H3>

<UL>
<LI>Ralph Warrington - President And General Manager
<LI>Garth Buchko - General Sales Manager
<LI>Robert McMahon - Vice-President, Finance
<LI>Ted Farr - Program Director, CJOB
<LI>Morley Calahan - Program Director, 97.5FM
<LI>Lorne Edwards - News Director
<LI>Bob Irving - Sports Director
</UL>



