<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Sunset Beach" a sizzling new daytime drama from Aaron Spelling, premieres January 6, 1997 on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>December 24, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Sunset Beach&quot;</H1>
<H2>a sizzling new daytime drama from Aaron Spelling,</H2>
<H2>premieres January 6, 1997 on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>


<P>
<I><B>Sunset Beach</B></I> is a place where everyone knows everybody
else's business.  It's home to the rich and poor, young and old,
warm beaches, casual charm and a legend that pervades the entire
character of the community.  <I><B>Sunset Beach,</B></I> the first
daytime serial to debut on television in eight years and Aaron
Spelling's first entry into the daytime arena, premieres <U>Monday,
January 6, 1997 (3:00 - 4:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
The 21 member cast includes such names as veteran actress <B>Lesley-Anne
Down, Sam Behrens, Susan Ward, Clive Robertson, Leigh Taylor Young,
Kathleen Noone</B> and <B>Ashley Hamilton</B>.  <BR>

<P>
Set in a small Southern California coastal community, <I><B>Sunset
Beach </B></I>is comprised of a diverse mix of people: police
officers, lifeguards, newspaper reporters, doctors, waiters and
restaurant owners.  It has its share of interesting personalities
like the &quot;trophy&quot; wife of a high-powered, unscrupulous
attorney, who lusts after power and social status; a mysterious,
wealthy entrepreneur; an eccentric, personable socialite; a career-driven
physician; a good cop gone bad; an all-American hero with a tormented
past; a troubled young runaway; a conniving half-sister; and a
young man who holds a secret that could destroy his entire family.
 <BR>

<P>
To keep up with the latest goings-on, most residents can be found
at the Java Web cyber coffeehouse, the blues/rock club called
The Deep, or Elaine's Waffle House.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Sunset Beach</B></I>, the hottest spot to be come January,
premieres <U>Monday, January 6, 1997, at 3:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<BR>


<P>

