<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Holiday Season Sparkles on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>The Holiday Season Sparkles</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>


<P>
<B>CHCH-TV</B> welcomes the holiday season with familiar favourites
and new traditions. Following are special Christmas holiday treats
the whole family can enjoy:<BR>

<P>
(in chronological order)<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>CHRISTMAS ON DIVISION STREET<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
A youth, charmed by the wisdom and generosity of a feisty 80-year-old
homeless man, pursues a relationship with the fellow. The alliance
enriches the boy's life just as his old friend relinquishes his.
The bitter-sweet drama, <I><B>Christmas on Division Street</B></I>,
airs <U>Tuesday, December 10, 1996, (8:00 - 10:00 p.m.)</U> on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Hume Cronyn, Fred Savage, Kenneth Welsh, Cloyce Morrow, Casey
Ellison, Kahla Lichti</B> and <B>Badja Djola</B> star. <BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Christmas On Division Street</B></I>, 14-year-old Trevor
Atwood (Savage), still suffering the loss of his grandfather,
fails to share his family's excitement about their move to Philadelphia.
The transition is made more difficult when Derek (Ellison), the
school jokester feels it his duty to torment the &quot;new guy.&quot;
Then, one day while in the library researching information for
a history paper, Trevor encounters Cleveland Meriwether (Cronyn),
an elderly homeless man and self-proclaimed &quot;Minister of
Education.&quot; His personality and exhaustive knowledge of American
history win Trevor over.<BR>

<P>
As the story unfolds, Trevor pursues a complex friendship with
Cleveland, a man besieged with drinking problems after causing
the death of a boy in an auto accident years ago. 
<P>
So enamored with Cleveland is Trevor that he is unwilling to desert
him no matter the outcome. Even after Cleveland rejects their
friendship, a lie initiated by a social worker, Trevor refuses
to stop caring for the man who would leave him with wonderful
memories and numerous examples of magnanimity: like the time Trevor
was stranded in the rain without train fare and Cleveland sold
his blood to give him the train fare; or the time Cleveland distributed
among the neighbourhood's needy, a sack of clothing Trevor had
brought for him; and so sweet was the time the two walked the
streets through the season's first snowfall when Cleveland landed
a job, temporarily. <BR>

<P>
Only after Cleveland's death, does the essence of the holiday
season take on a new and profound meaning for Trevor and his family.
<I><B>Christmas on Division Street</B></I>, a WIC Entertainment
production, airs <U>Tuesday, December 10, 1996, at 8:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>KATHIE LEE: JUST IN TIME FOR CHRISTMAS<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<B>Amy Grant, The Manhattan Transfer</B>, new country sensation
<B>Bryan White</B> and the <B>Oklahoma City Philharmonic Orchestra</B>
join <B>Kathie Lee Gifford</B>, her husband Frank and their two
children -- Cody and Cassidy -- in a warm, family celebration
of song, dance and comedy skits. <I><B>Kathie Lee: Just In Time
For Christmas</B></I> airs <U>Wednesday, December 11, 1996 (9:00
- 10:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>A CELEBRATION OF CHRISTMAS WITH FRANK MILLS<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
Internationally renowned composer/pianist, Frank Mills, will make
a wonderful season even more so, as he performs his own widely-acclaimed
compositions: <I>Music Box Dancer, Peter Piper </I>and<I> the
Happy Song</I>, along with such traditional favourites as <I>Joy
to the World, Silent Night </I>and<I> White Christmas</I>. <I><B>A
Celebration of Christmas with Frank Mills</B></I> airs <U>Saturday,
December 14, 1996 (7:00 - 8:00 p.m.)</U>. <BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>EBBIE<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
A tough business woman, who has lost sight of the important things
in life, experiences a Christmas haunting which leaves her with
a renewed appreciation for love, goodness and compassion in <I><B>Ebbie</B></I>,
airing <U>Sunday, December 15, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>.
<BR>

<P>
Starring in the modern day version of Dickens' classic holiday
favourite, &quot;A Christmas Carol,&quot; are <B>Susan Lucci,
Wendy Crewson, Jeff DeMunn</B> and<B> Taran Noah Smith</B>.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Ebbie</B></I>, Elizabeth &quot;Ebbie&quot; Scrooge (Lucci)
is a shrewd CEO of Dobson's Department Store. Her rise to the
top has been achieved through difficult decision-making and personal
sacrifices that have succeeded in her obtaining a powerful position,
but also in alienating her from her inner, gentle self and the
important people in her life. <BR>

<P>
Then, on one Christmas Eve, Ebbie is visited by a colourful cast
of midnight visitors who take her on an emotional journey through
her past, present and future. Reliving her former heartaches and
glimpsing into a lonely, unhappy future, Ebbie realizes the outcome
of her selfish choices and awakens Christmas morning with a new,
hopeful perspective.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Ebbie</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, December 15, 1996, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>UNLIKELY ANGEL<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<B>Dolly Parton</B> (<I>Steel Magnolias, Straight Talk, Rhinestone</I>)
stars as an angel who returns to earth in order to earn her wings.
Her task is to unite a family experiencing emotional upheaval
during the Christmas holidays. <I><B>Unlikely Angel</B></I> airs
<U>Tuesday, December 17, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Brian Kerwin</B> (<I>Murphy's Romance, Switched at Birth, Torch
Song Trilogy</I>) stars with <B>Dolly Parton</B>, who has written
and will perform original songs in the movie.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Unlikely Angel</B></I>, a brassy lounge singer, Ruby
Diamond, (Parton) meets St. Peter after she accidentally drives
her car off a cliff. Having lived life as a woman who only looked
after herself, Ruby is promptly sent back to earth to &quot;earn
her wings&quot; by helping a family in distress -- a widowed father,
Ben, with two young children who haven't celebrated Christmas
since Ben's wife died. Her task must be accomplished by Christmas.
<BR>

<P>
With St. Peter's comical help, Ruby endears herself to the family
and sets out to find Ben a wife a mother to his children. Hilarious
misunderstandings almost bungle her plans, but everything falls
neatly into place just in time for Christmas and St. Peter welcomes
Ruby back into heaven.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Unlikely Angel</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, December 17, 1996
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>. <BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>COMEDY CLUB CHRISTMAS SPECIAL<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<B>Ben Guyatt</B> wishes everyone a happy holiday by hosting his
first <I><B>Comedy Club Christmas Special.</B></I> The all new
one hour special will feature such stand-up comedians as <B>Jimmy
Flynn</B> -- famous for his east coast comedy -- and more! The
<I><B>Comedy Club Christmas Special</B></I> airs <U>Saturday,
December 21, 1996 (10:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>HOME FOR CHRISTMAS<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<I><B>Mickey Rooney</B></I> stars in this tenderhearted story.
Amanda, a little girl of six, wishes for a grandfather for Christmas.
In a strange and magical way, her wish is granted. <BR>

<P>
Elmer (Rooney), a petty thief is caught breaking into a car. The
stiff-lipped owner, Reg, who lacks any kind of sentiment, allows
Elmer to work for him doing odd jobs to compensate for the damages.
Reg's daughter, Amanda, and Elmer are immediately drawn to each
other. Plus Amanda thinks Santa brought her a grandfather for
Christmas.<BR>

<P>
In reality he did. When Elmer discovers that Reg is the son he
never met, he flees in shame, not wanting the secret to be revealed.
Distressed by Elmer's sudden departure, Amanda follows him onto
the tough city streets. Only a miracle and perhaps a loving grandfather
will be able to find her.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Home For Christmas </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, December 22 (7:00
- 9:00 p.m.)</U> as well as on Wednesday, <U>December 25, 1996,
at 12:00 noon</U>.<U> <BR>
<BR>
</U>
<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>TIMEPIECE<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
Emmy Award winner <B>Richard Thomas</B> (<I>The Waltons</I>) and
Tony Award winner <B>James Earl Jones</B> (<I>The Great White
Hope</I>) star in a prequel to the timeless drama, <I>The Christmas
Box </I>(airing December 25 at
9:00 p.m. on CHCH-TV; see page 7). A tender tale of love, loyalty
and forgiveness, <I><B>Timepiece</B></I> tells the story behind
an old watch bequeathed to Richard Evans' (Thomas) daughter as
a wedding gift. The program airs <U>Sunday, December 22, 1996,
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<P>
<I><B>Timepiece</B></I> opens on the eve of Richard's daughter's
wedding. As he gives his child Mary Parkin's (the aged widow from
<I>The Christmas Box</I> who transformed and enriched the family's
lives) rose-gold watch he recounts the story of Mary's life: 
<P>
During World War II, Mary worked for and eventually married wealthy
industrialist David Parkin. At their wedding, David gave Mary
the rose-gold timepiece brought to him by his friend, Lawrence
Flynn (Jones), a man who made his living by repairing clocks and
watches. After a wealthy widow bequeathed a valuable clock to
Lawrence, her nephew broke into his shop where Lawrence shot him
in self-defense. Fearing for his friend, David declared to the
police that he fired the fatal shot. David was absolved of the
crime, however, friends of the nephew set the Parkin mansion ablaze
and Andrea, the Parkin's daughter, perished in it. Her death haunted
Mary, David and Lawrence until an extraordinary act of compassion
and forgiveness healed their grief. <BR>

<P>
<I><B>Timepiece</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, December 22, 1996, (9:00
- 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>. <BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>DOFASCO CHRISTMAS<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
The songs of the holiday season are performed by the talented
Dofasco Male Chorus, the Dofasco Ladies Choral Ensemble and the
Hamilton Philharmonic Youth Orchestra under the direction of Geoff
Bullivant and Glen Mallory.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Dofasco Christmas </B></I>can be enjoyed <U>Tuesday, December
24, 1996 (8:00 - 8:30 p.m.)</U> and again on <U>December 25, 1996,
at 6:00 p.m.<BR>
<BR>
</U>
<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>CELEBRATION IN SONG</I></CENTER></H2>

<H3><CENTER><I>(Ryerson United Church Christmas Special)<BR>
</I></CENTER></H3>

<P>
The combined choirs and hand bell ringers from Ryerson United
Church pay tribute to the traditional carols of Christmas. <I><B>Celebration
In Song</B></I> airs <U>December 24 (8:30 - 9:00 p.m.)</U> and
again <U>December 25 at 5:30 p.m</U>. on <B>CHCH</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>WHITE CHRISTMAS</I> <BR>
</CENTER></H2>

<P>
Memorable Irving Berlin scores are showcased in this 1954 classic
starring <B>Bing Crosby, Danny Kaye, Rosemary Clooney</B> and
<B>Vera Ellen</B>. The plot is simple in the delightful musical
-- two army buddies (Crosby and Kaye) develop a comedy act, then
team up with two performing sisters (Clooney and Ellen).
<P>
<I><B>White Christmas </B></I>airs <U>Tuesday, December 24, 1996,
(9:00 - 11:30 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>CAROLS AND MIDNIGHT MASS<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
Annually on this holy night, <B>CHCH</B> broadcasts Midnight Mass,
<I>live</I>, from the Cathedral of Christ The King. His excellency
Bishop Anthony F. Tonnos will celebrate the first Mass of Christmas.
<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Carols and Midnight Mass</B></I><B> </B>commence at <U>11:30
p.m.</U> on <U>Tuesday, December 24, 1996</U>. <I><B>Midnight
Mass</B></I> is repeated <U>Wednesday, December 25 (8:00 - 10:00
a.m.).<BR>
<BR>
</U>
<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>CLARENCE<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
The angel from the 1946 classic, <I>It's A Wonderful Life</I>,
descends to earth once again in the TV movie, <I><B>Clarence</B></I>.
Headlining in the warmhearted comedy are <B>Robert Carradine</B>
and <B>Kate Trotter</B>.
<P>
In <I><B>Clarence</B></I>, we discover that the angel, by the
same name, has become younger in age over the past forty-five
years and is a clock maker in heaven. With a great lack of
<P>
enthusiasm, Clarence consents to return to earth to save the life
of a fellow angel's wife. The woman is contemplating suicide as
her company is heading for financial ruin.<BR>

<P>
Raise your spirits with the heavenly humour of, <I><B>Clarence</B></I>,
<U>Wednesday, December 25, 1996 (3:00 - 5:00 p.m.)</U>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>ROUGH EDGES<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<B>Catherine Swing</B> and <B>Mary Bellows </B>star in this upbeat,
urban Christmas tale about a chance encounter between two women
from opposite sides of the tracks.<BR>

<P>
The charming, poignant drama forces the two women to look beyond
their &quot;wrappings&quot; and see where the real riches of the
Christmas spirit thrive. <BR>

<P>
<I><B>Rough Edges, </B></I>based on a stage play by Donna Hinkle,
with screenplay by William Finlay, airs <U>Christmas Day (5:00
- 5:30 p.m.)</U>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>THE CHRISTMAS BOX<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
<I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I>,<I><B> </B></I>a heartwarming,
ageless tale about love, family and the gift of sharing, airs
<U>Sunday, December 25, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<BR>

<P>
<B>Richard Thomas, Maureen O'Hara</B> and <B>Annette O'Toole </B>star
in the drama.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I>, the Evans family -- Keri (O'Toole),
Richard (Thomas) and their six-year-old daughter, Jenna, live
in a cramped downtown apartment. When Keri learns about a caretaker
position in a grand old home, she convinces her over-worked husband
to accompany her on the interview.<BR>

<P>
Almost instantly, Richard is at odds with the elderly, overbearing
owner of the house, Mary Parkin (O'Hara). Despite their unfriendly
meeting, Mary retains the couple, with the contentious relationship
between Mary and Richard persisting. Richard even experiences
troubled dreams of angels and senses that Mary and her home hold
a sinister secret. Keri and Jenna, on the other hand, enjoy a
warm friendship with Mary, who recognizes how much the little
girl misses her hard-working father.<BR>

<P>
However, it has been pre-determined that Mary and Richard forge
a bond of affection. This accomplished, Richard learns surprising
secrets from Mary's past that awaken him to the true meaning of
Christmas.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, December 25, 1996
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV, </B>simulcast<B>/CBS</B>.
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>CHCH-TV/Y95 CLASSIC ROCK NEW YEAR'S EVE SUPER PARTY</I>
<BR>
</CENTER></H2>

<P>
<B>CHCH-TV</B> and <B>Y95</B> usher in the New Year with the second
annual <I><B>CHCH-TV/Y95 Classic Rock New Year's Eve Super Party</B></I>,
<U>Tuesday, December 31, 1996</U>, broadcast <I>live to air</I>
on <B>Y95</B> <U>(9:00 p.m. - 1:00 a.m.),</U> simulcast with <B>CHCH-TV</B>
(<U>11:30 p.m - 12:30 a.m.)</U>. <BR>

<P>
Hosting the super celebration at the Convention Centre in downtown
Hamilton, with live cut-ins from the <I>First Night</I> festivities
at City Hall, will be <B>Y95</B>'s <B>Scott Thompson</B> and <B>Lori
Love.<BR>
</B>
<P>
The<B> <I>CHCH-TV/Y95</I> <I>Classic Rock New Year's Eve Super
Party</I></B> will<I><B> </B></I>feature over 1,500 revelers dancing
to the beat of classic rock's best. Then, when <B>CHCH</B> joins
the fun in progress at 11:30 p.m., the viewers at home will also
get a chance to enjoy the huge video party, complete with three
monitor walls displaying classic rock artists. Add to the merriment
some grand prizes and big surprises -- especially at the midnight
hour -- and you have one super New Year's Eve party! <BR>

<P>
The hotline number for tickets is 905-388-5281.<BR>

<P>
Say good-bye to '96 and blast into '97, one year closer to the
next millennium, at the second annual <I><B>CHCH-TV/Y95 Classic
Rock New Year's Eve Super Party</B></I>, <U>Tuesday, December
31, 1996</U>, broadcast <I>live to air</I> on <B>Y95 </B><U>(9:00
p.m. - 1:00 a.m.)</U>, simulcast with <B>CHCH-TV</B> <U>(11:30
p.m. - 12:30 a.m.)</U>. <BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<H2><CENTER><I>THE JAPANESE RED AND WHITE SHOW<BR>
</I></CENTER></H2>

<P>
For the 12th consecutive season, <B>CHCH </B>will broadcast the
<I>live</I>, musical extravaganza from Tokyo, Japan. Traditionally,
each New Year, 22 of the most popular male vocalists (white team)
and 22 of the most popular female vocalists (red team) have engaged
in a fierce, but friendly rivalry in song. This year, over 60
artists are competing in the <I><B>Japanese Red and White Show</B></I>.
<BR>

<P>
During the program, millions of viewers in Japan cast their votes
for their favourite singer. However, millions more watch this
New Year's tradition as it is broadcast around the world and seen
by fans in Korea, the United States, France, China, Canada and
more.<BR>

<P>
Start a new tradition in 1997, watch <I><B>The Japanese Red And
White Show</B></I>, <U>Wednesday, January 1 (9:00 a.m.- 1:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<HR>

<P>
Please be reminded that the shows and times outlined in this package
are subject to change. We will be certain, however, to keep you
apprised of any changes.<BR>
<BR>

<P>


