<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Hockey Greats Past and Present" on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 18, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Hockey Greats Past and Present&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The career of hockey great Darryl Sittler is profiled in the half-hour
special, <I><B>Hockey Greats Past and Present</B></I>, airing
<U>Tuesday, December 3, 1996 (10:30 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<BR>

<P>
Hosting the program is NHL All-Star <B>Steve Payne</B>, with narration
provided by <B>Ron Hewat</B>. <B>Lanny McDonald</B> and <B>Cliff
Fletcher</B> are among the well-known names scheduled to make
guest appearances.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Hockey Greats Past and Present</B></I> looks back at Sittler's
early days in the small Ontario town of St. Jacobs, his signing
with The Leafs in 1970, his trade to The Flyers and his winning
goal in the 1976 Canada Cup.<BR>

<P>
During his career, Darryl Sittler played in 1096 games, scored
484 goals, made 637 assists and totalled 1121 points.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Hockey Greats Past and Present</B></I>, a must for any true
hockey fan, airs <U>Tuesday, December 3, 1996, at 10:30 p.m.</U>,
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, immediately following <I>Molson Leaf Hockey
on Eleven</I> with The Leafs facing off against the St. Louis
Blues.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<P>


