<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Gone In A Heartbeat", a new televison movie on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 18, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Gone In A Heartbeat&quot;</H1>
<H2>a new television movie on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A woman with a heart condition is kidnapped by two high school
students and then abandoned in her car during a snowstorm. The
situation develops into a tense drama as negotiations with the
abductors become intricate and rescuers race against time to save
the hostage's life in, <I><B>Gone in a Heartbeat</B></I>, airing
<U>Sunday, December 1, 1996 (9:00 -11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<BR>

<P>
<B>Michael Tucker</B> (<I>L.A. Law</I>)<B> </B>and<B> Jill Eikenberry</B>
(<I>L.A. Law</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Gone in a Heartbeat</B></I> is about the abduction of a
small town woman by two youths. The one boy, Michael, is the all-American
sort -- good looking, comes from a wealthy family and has a bright
future ahead of him. The other, Burt, is the blackguard type.
<BR>

<P>
Their delinquent behaviour begins when they break into a classmate's
home under the assumption that he has taken some CDs from them.
After unlawfully entering his home, they discover they were wrong,
but decide to steal from him anyway. Other criminal activities
follow, each escalating in severity, until eventually, they kidnap
a woman to raise money for a drug deal.<BR>

<P>
The circumstances are seriously complicated by the woman's heart
condition, the boys' negotiation tactics and their desertion of
her during a fierce blizzard. <BR>

<P>
The suspense mounts as every minute could lead to a fatal outcome
in <I><B>Gone in a Heartbeat</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, December
1, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.
<BR>

<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
