<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH-TV has the action drama "Spenser: Judas Goat".</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 5, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H2>CHCH-TV has the action drama</H2>
<H1>&quot;Spenser: Judas Goat&quot;</H1>
</CENTER>


<P>
Everyone's favourite tough, yet, philosophical private eye goes
after a powerful group of terrorists in a case that could have
explosive international repercussions in, <I><B>Spenser: Judas
Goat</B></I>, airing <U>Friday, November 29, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00
p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Robert Urich</B> (<I>Lonesome Dove, A Perfect Little Murder,
Princess Daisy, Spenser: Ceremony, Spenser: Pale Kings and Princes,
Spenser: A Savage Place</I>), <B>Avery Brooks </B>(<I>The Emest
Green Story, Spenser: Ceremony, Spenser: Pale Kings and Princes,
Spenser: A Savage Place</I>) and <B>Wendy Crewson</B> (<I>The
Good Son, The Santa Clause, Folks, Spenser: A Savage Place</I>)
star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Spenser: Judas Goat</B></I>, the family of industrialist
Hugh Dixon is killed by a terrorist bomb.  When Spenser (Urich)
is called in to find the culprits, his investigation leads to
a startling twist -- Dixon was not the actual target.  The intended
victim was and is Winston Boyko, an idealistic African freedom
fighter, whose life is still in danger.<BR>

<P>
With the assistance of his streetwise friend, Hawk (Brooks), and
psychologist girlfriend, Susan (Crewson), Spenser entraps a beautiful
young woman who holds the key to locating the mastermind behind
the terrorists and their actions.<BR>

<P>
Many questions remain to be solved in, <I><B>Spenser: Judas
Goat</B></I>, airing <U>Friday, November 29, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
