<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Bob Hope's Laughing with the Presidents", on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 5, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Bob Hope's Laughing with the Presidents&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Historical footage, both on film and tape, captures the familiar
sight of <I><B>Bob Hope's Laughing With The Presidents</B></I>.
 The veteran comedian's television special airs <U>Saturday, November
23, 1996, (8:00 - 9:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
The incomparable funny man himself, <B>Bob Hope</B>, hosts the
one hour celebration along with co-host <B>Tony Danza</B>.  <BR>

<P>
<B>President of the United States</B>, <B>Bill Clinton; First
Lady Hillary Rodham Clinton;</B> <B>President George </B>and<B>
Barbara Bush; President Gerald </B>and<B> Betty Ford;</B> as well
as <B>David </B>and<B> Julie Eisenhower </B>are among the featured
guests.<BR>

<P>
Special guests include <B>Don Johnson</B> (<I>Nash Bridges, Born
Yesterday, Guilty As Sin</I>), singer <B>Naomi Judd</B> (<I>Rio
Diablo</I>), <B>Ann-Margret </B>(<I>Grumpy Old Men, Grumpier Old
Men, Twice in a Lifetime</I>) and <B>Tom Selleck </B>(<I>Friends,
Folks, An Innocent Man</I>).<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Bob Hope's Laughing With The Presidents</B></I>, a rare
treat, airs <U>Saturday, November 23, 1996, at 8:00 p.m.</U> on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.<BR>

