<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Angel Flight Down", a powerful story of heroism and courage on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>November 4, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Angel Flight Down&quot;</H1>
<H2>a powerful story of heroism and courage on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
When an emergency medical airlift plane, transporting a two-year-old
child in critical condition, crashes into the snowy slope of a
cliff, all passengers, in addition to the child, face the possibility
of dying before being discovered.  Fighting time and unforgiving
weather conditions, a rescue team battles the odds to save everyone
in, <I><B>Angel Flight Down</B></I>, airing <U>Saturday, November
23, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Based on official documents, personal interviews and published
accounts, the two-hour production stars <B>Patricia Kalember</B>
(<I>Sisters, thirtysomething</I>), <B>David Charvet</B> (<I>Baywatch</I>),
<B>Christopher Atkins</B> (<I>Child Bride of Short Creek</I>)
and <B>Gary Graham </B>(<I>Robot Jox, The Last Warrior</I>).<BR>

<P>
In<I><B> Angel Flight Down</B></I>, x-rays taken at a small-town
hospital in Colorado reveal that a young toddler's irritated cough
is caused by a small object caught in her esophagus.  When nonsurgical
procedures to remove the object fail, it becomes apparent the
child faces fatal consequences if she does not receive immediate
care from a larger facility in Denver.<BR>

<P>
Despite severe blizzard warnings, the Angel Flight crew --a team
of dedicated professionals comprised of a trained nurse, paramedic
and pilot -- prepare for their emergency flight with the child
and her father.  However, when the twin engine malfunctions, the
small aircraft crashes into the slope of a cliff, leaving all
lives in peril.<BR>

<P>
What ensues is a dramatic rescue effort, as the husband of one
of the nurses leads a team to save all lives concerned in, <I><B>Angel
Flight Down</B></I>, airing <U>Saturday, November 23, 1996, at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
