<HEAD>
<TITLE>The World's Greatest Magic III, on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>October 28, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;The World's Greatest Magic III&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
For the third straight year, the most celebrated masters of deception
from around the world assemble at Caesars Palace in Las Vegas
to bring viewers two hours of non-stop mystifying illusions and
clever comedy in <I><B>The World's Greatest Magic III</B></I>,
airing <U>Wednesday, November 27, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Host<B> John Ritter </B>and special guest comedienne <B>Rita Rudner</B>
will add to the excitement as they introduce 18 magicians performing
their all time best illusions.<BR>

<P>
World famous acts include the mysterious <I>Appearing Lamborghini</I>
by <B>Brett Daniels</B>; <I>The Twister</I> by Canada's <B>Greg
Frewin</B>; and a remarkable, grand illusion by the renowned <B>Pendragons</B>
who will make 25 beautiful Las Vegas showgirls disappear.<BR>

<P>
Returning from last year is the ever popular <B>Mac King School
of Magic</B>, who will teach ordinary people how to perform simple
tricks that will impress their friends.<BR>

<P>
For an evening of pure amazement, watch the entertaining special,
<I><B>World's Greatest Magic III</B></I>, airing <U>Wednesday,
November 27, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
