<HEAD>
<TITLE>"What Kind of Mother Are You?", a new television movie on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>October 28, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;What Kind of Mother Are You?&quot;</H1>
<H2>a new television movie</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
When a troubled teen encounters a minor brush with the law, her
misled mother, wishing to teach her daughter a lesson, consents
to an overnight jail detention.  Through a miscarriage of justice
the stay is much longer and the task of obtaining the girl's release
becomes an arduous, complex battle in the fact-based movie, <I><B>What
Kind of Mother Are You?</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, November 17,
1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Mel Harris</B> (<I>thirtysomething, Something So Right</I>)
and <B>Nicholle Tom</B> (<I>Beethoven's 2nd</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>What Kind of Mother Are You?</B></I>, teenager Kelly
Jameson (Tom) and her boyfriend, Jake, cut school one day and
Jake attempts to steal a blouse at a mall.  Following their arrest,
Kelly's mother, Laura (Harris), and stepfather confront her with
some biting accusations, which compel her to run off with Jake.
 Days later, Kelly is escorted home by a police officer -- the
result of Jake's second theft attempt.  During a heated exchange
of words, Kelly strikes her mother, triggering, for Laura, the
memory of Kelly's abusive, alcoholic father who committed suicide.
 The officer suggests that Kelly be put in jail overnight to 'cool
off,' but when Laura comes the next morning to pick up her daughter,
she is informed Kelly has been transferred to Juvenile Hall and
assault charges filed.  <BR>

<P>
A manipulative case worker, Marcy Hackman, critical of Laura's
parenting ability, decides that Kelly should be held longer and
sends her off to a centre where an inmate is raped by a maintenance
worker, another suffers a nervous breakdown and Kelly, herself,
is beaten by another girl.  After media attention is focused on
the case, Marcy fabricates a story of Kelly's attempted suicide,
sending the girl back to Juvenile Hall.<BR>

<P>
During a painful mother/daughter psychological evaluation, the
truth about Kelly's father is revealed, leaving Kelly enraged
and her future in jeopardy.  However, at a hearing Laura publicly
blames her own inadequacies as a mother for the problems and Kelly
admits her misdeeds.  The judge, recognizing the promise of a
stronger relationship between the two, rules in favour of Kelly's
release despite Marcy's recommendations for a longer term.  <BR>

<P>
<I><B>What Kind of Mother Are You?</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, November
17, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>NBC</B>.

<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
