<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Telus/West Edmonton Mall Curling Classic&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Over ten World Champions will compete for a $75,000 purse in one
of the major professional curling bonspiels during the upcoming
curling season -- the <I><B>TELUS/West Edmonton Mall Curling Classic</B></I>.
 The semi-finals will be aired live on <U>Saturday, November 2,
1996</U> followed by the finals on <U>Sunday, November 3, 1996
(4:00 - 6:30 p.m. both days)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Included among the ten World Champions competing in the 16 rink
Curling Classic are <B>Kevin Martin, Kerry Burtnyk, Ed Werenich,
Al Hackner, Russ Howard, Ed Lukowich </B>and <B>Rick Folk</B>.
<BR>

<P>
The first rock of the <I><B>TELUS/West Edmonton Mall Curling Classic</B></I>
drops Friday, November 1 at West Edmonton Mall.  Curling fans
can share in the excitement of the game as <B>CHCH</B> brings
viewers live coverage of the semi-finals on <U>Saturday, November
2, 1996</U> and the finals on <U>Sunday, November 3, 1996</U>
with a 4:00 p.m. start both days.

