<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Murderous Intent", a psychological thriller on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>October 21, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Murderous Intent&quot;</H1>
<H2>a psychological thriller</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A young woman is confronted with the ultimate personal moral dilemma
when her mother and her mother's lover devise a murderous plan
that requires her assistance for its successful execution in,
<I><B>Murderous Intent</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, November 3,
1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Inspired by actual events, the thriller stars <B>Corbin Bernsen</B>
(<FONT SIZE=2>TV Credits: <I>L.A. Law, Dangerous Intentions, Line
of Fire: The Morris Dees Story, Breaking Point, Love Can Be Murder;</I>
Feature Film Credits<I>: Radioland Murders, Tales From the Hood,
Major League, Major League II</I>), Golden Globe Award winner
and New York Film Critic's Award winner <B>Lesley Ann Warren</B>
(TV Credits:<I> Family of Spies;</I> Film Credits:<I> In Sickness
and In Health, Victor, Victoria, Clue, Choose Me, Cop, Pure Country,
The Color of Night</I>), <B>Tushka Bergen</B> (Film Credits: <I>Barcelona,
Swing Kids, Outback, Mad Max III: Beyond the Thunderdome</I>)
and <B>Dash Mihok</B> (Film Credits: <I>Foxfire, Black is White,
Gun, Sleepers</I>).<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
In <I><B>Murderous Intent</B></I>, Colleen Bernish (Bergen) is
rendered powerless as she watches her single mother, Gayle (Warren),
become entangled in an all-consuming affair with Brice Talbot
(Bernsen), a married family man with a mercurial temperament.
 When Brice moves in with the Bernishes, Colleen is obliged to
assume responsibility for her mentally challenged brother (Mihok),
for her mother has become single-focused on her lover.<BR>

<P>
After constant battling with his wife over the custody of his
children, Brice's emotional threshold reaches its peak.  The result
is an elaborate murderous plot devised by himself and Gayle to
kill his wife, however, the scheme's success relies on Colleen's
involvement.<BR>

<P>
Faced with a supreme moral dilemma, Colleen must decide if she
will become an accomplice to murder in order to hold on to her
mother's love, or if she will turn her mother over to the authorities
and risk losing her forever.  <BR>

<P>
<I><B>Murderous Intent </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, November 3, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m. </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>


