<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Secret She Carried", a new television movie, on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>October 8, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;The Secret She Carried&quot;</H1>
<H2>a new made-for-television movie,</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
When a rape victim becomes pregnant, the torment she and her husband
endure waiting to discover the identity of the child's father
does not compare with the anguish the couple will suffer when
the rapist plots to take away their baby in, <I><B>The Secret
She Carried</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, October 27, 1996 (9:00
- 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Peri Gilpin</B> (<I>Frasier, The Outer Limits</I>), <B>Jere
Burns</B> (<I>Something So Right</I>) and <B>D.W. Moffett</B>
(<I>Danielle Steel's &quot;Fine Things&quot;</I>) star. <BR>

<P>
In <I><B>The Secret She Carried</B></I>, Ellen Hayward (Gilpin),
arriving home early one night, is violently assaulted by Lewis
Snow (Burns) -- a man enraged by the fact that his wife and children
have left him.  Before leaving, he threatens to kill Ellen and
her husband, should she dare tell anyone about their encounter.
<BR>

<P>
Ignoring her assailant's threat, Ellen confides in her spouse,
Mitch (Moffett).  The situation is further complicated when Ellen
discovers she is pregnant.  The couple are then faced with the
pain of not knowing the true identity of the child's father. 
At long last medical tests prove that Mitch is indeed the father,
but, Lewis, still on the prowl, imagines himself to be the proud
father.<BR>

<P>
Shortly after Ellen gives birth, a nightmare she experiences becomes
a reality.  One night she answers the phone to hear Lewis' voice
and the cry of her baby in the background.  Lewis is demanding
Ellen come immediately, and alone, to calm their son.  Upon her
arrival, Ellen desperately tries to talk sense to Lewis, but he
turns a deaf ear.  When Ellen grabs her son and flees, Lewis follows
closely behind, with the future of the Hayward family hanging
precariously in the balance.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>The Secret She Carried</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, October 27,
1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.


<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
