<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Sophie and the Moonhanger", a riveting drama, on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>October 1, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Sophie and the Moonhanger&quot;</H1>
<H2>a riveting drama</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A woman's loyalty between a trusted confidant and her husband,
a grand Wizard in the Ku Klux Klan, is severely tested when she
must plead with him to spare her friend from his fanatical wrath
in, <I><B>Sophie and The Moonhanger</B></I>, airing <U>Wednesday,
October 16, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<BR>

<P>
<B>Patricia Richardson</B> (<I>Home Improvement</I>), <B>Lynn
Whitfield</B> (<I>The Josephine Baker Story, State of Emergency</I>),
<B>David Andrews</B>, <B>Ja'Net DuBois</B> and <B>Jason Bernard</B>
star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Sophie and The Moonhanger</B></I>, a young, innocent
black woman, Sophie Cooper (Whitfield), lives in rural South Carolina
in the 1950s with her ill-humoured mother and two children.  Employed
by a white family as their housekeeper, Sophie eventually learns
that the head of the house, respected lawyer Ray Edgerton (Andrews),
is a leader in the Ku Klux Klan.  Edgerton's wife, Bonnie (Richardson),
aware of her husband's Klan activities, constantly lives in fear
that she will one day lose her husband.  Nevertheless, she embraces
Sophie as her friend and her children's responsible caregiver.
<BR>

<P>
In time, Sophie meets and marries Holt Jessop (Bernard), a good
man with much pride and ambition.  Together, the couple work to
fulfill Holt's &quot;moonhanging&quot; dream -- a home, business
and a better life for his family.   <BR>

<P>
But the ultimate anguish finally arrives for Bonnie, when she
discovers Ray and his followers have focused on Sophie and her
family as their next victims.  When Ray violently refuses Bonnie's
pleas to pardon Sophie and her family, she is faced with the harsh
reality of what her husband has become and simultaneously freed
by the truth of her friendship with Sophie.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Sophie and The Moonhanger</B></I> airs <U>Wednesday, October
16, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
