<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Blue Rodeo" A drama based on Jo-Ann Mapson's critically acclaimed novel, airs on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 30, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Blue Rodeo&quot;</H1>
<H2>A drama based on Jo-Ann Mapson's critically acclaimed novel,</H2>
<H2>airs on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The relationship between a mother and son is destroyed when a
tragic accident leaves the young man almost entirely deaf at the
age of 17.  What ensues is the mother's desperate struggle to
reconcile with her child in, <I><B>Blue Rodeo</B></I>, a drama
airing <U>Sunday, October 20, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Ann-Margret </B>(<I>Grumpy Old Men, Grumpier Old Men, Middle
Age Crazy</I>) <B>Kris Kristofferson</B> (<I>No Place To Hide,
Rollover</I>, <I>A Star is Born</I>) and <B>Corbin Allred</B>
star. <BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Blue Rodeo</B></I>, an accident leaves 17-year-old Peter
Yearwood (Allred) almost entirely deaf.  His mother, Maggie (Ann-Margret),
indirectly blames herself, a feeling shared by her son.  In her
attempts to make peace with Peter, Maggie moves to a ranch located
near the school where Peter is sent to learn to deal with his
disability.  Patiently, she ignores her son's anger towards her,
his rejection of her endeavours to make amends and tolerates his
stubbornness.  <BR>

<P>
During this time, Maggie meets and falls in love with her new
neighbour, Owen Whister (Kristofferson), a man Peter instantly
dislikes -- primarily because Owen will not suffer his moodiness
and temper tantrums.<BR>

<P>
Owen's love for Maggie grows, however, complications arise when
Peter's suspicions about the smooth-talking cowboy lead him to
uncover Owen's true identity.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Blue Rodeo</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, October 20, 1996, at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.     
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
