<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Almost Golden: The Jessica Savitch Story", on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 26, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Almost Golden: The Jessica Savitch Story&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Jessica Savage, a bright, journalistic pioneer triumphed in her
profession despite a tormented personal life, drug abuse and disastrous
relationships.  The television biography, <I><B>Almost Golden:
The Jessica Savitch Story</B></I>, chronicles the span of her
career, which ended with her tragic and controversial death at
the age of 36.  <I><B>Almost Golden</B></I> airs <U>Wednesday,
October 9, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Emmy Award winner <B>Sela Ward</B> (<I>Sisters, The Fugitive,
Hello Again, Nothing in Common</I>), <B>Ron Silver</B> (<I>Chicago
Hope, Reversal of Fortune, Lifepod</I>) and <B>Judith Ivey</B>
(<I>Brighton Beach Memoirs, Hello Again</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Almost Golden: The Jessica Savitch Story</B></I> centres
around the career of Jessica Savitch who, at the age of 23, started
out as a cub reporter at a Houston television station.  Overcoming
remarkable odds in her profession, Savitch became the &quot;golden
girl&quot; of television news.<BR>

<P>
However, Savitch's stoic demeanor disguised a turbulent personal
life which included her father's early death, divorce, substance
abuse and a volatile relationship with newsman Ron Kershaw.<BR>

<P>
In 1982, a poll indicated that Savitch was &quot;more popular
than Charles Kuralt, more trusted than Tom Brokaw, Peter Jennings
or Ted Koppel.&quot;   One year later, at the age of 36, the beautiful
blonde was dead.  Her car had plunged into the Delaware Canal
in Pennsylvania.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Almost Golden: The Jessica Savitch Story,</B></I> the most-watched
made-for-basic-cable movie in television history, airs <U>Wednesday,
October 9, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.


<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
