<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Night Visitors", A Science Fiction Thriller on CHCH-TV. </TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 23, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Night Visitors&quot;</H1>
<H2>A Science Fiction Thriller on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A spunky reporter agrees to care for her nephew while his widowed
father is on the run from the government.  When her brother, her
nephew's father, dies under suspicious circumstances, her investigation
of the crime uncovers a bizarre military cover-up in, <I><B>Night
Visitors</B></I>, premiering <U>Sunday, October 13, 1996 (9:00
- 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <BR>

<P>
Five-time Emmy nominee <B>Faith Ford</B> (<I>Murphy Brown, A Weekend
in the Country, Desperate Justice</I>), <B>Stephen Tobolowsky</B>
(<I>Mr. Rhodes</I>), <B>Thomas Gibson</B> (<I>Chicago Hope</I>)
and <B>Charles Dutton</B> (<I>Roc</I>) star. <BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Night Visitors</B></I>, the dauntless and spirited Kelly
Wells (Ford) agrees to take her nephew into her charge while his
father, David (her widowed brother), retreats from the government
after stealing a mysterious box.<BR>

<P>
After David dies under questionable circumstances, Kelly's nephew
is taken hostage.  It is the abductors' hope that Kelly will lead
them to the missing three-foot box -- the contents of which must
be kept secret from not only American citizens, but all of mankind.
<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Night Visitors</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, October 13, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
