<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Dead Man's Revenge" on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 23, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Dead Man's Revenge&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A suspenseful, humourous western, <I><B>Dead Man's Revenge</B></I>
is about an evil rail baron who robs people of their property
and then has them arrested for transgressions they did not commit.
 <I><B>Dead Man's Revenge</B></I> airs <U>Saturday, October 12,
1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<B>Bruce Dern</B><I> (Silent Running, Posse, The Burbs, Middle-Age
Crazy, That Championship Season</I>), <B>Michael Ironside</B>
(<I>Extreme Prejudice, Free Willy, Fortunes of War, Nowhere to
Hide, Red Sun Rising</I>), <B>Vondie Curtis-Hall</B> (<I>Drop
Squad, Passion Fish</I>), <B>Tobin Bell</B> (<I>Deep Red, New
Eden, Ruby</I>) and <B>Randy Travis</B> (<I>Frank &amp; Jesse,
Texas</I>) star.
<P>
 
<P>
In <I><B>Dead Man's Revenge</B></I>, a sinister rail baron (Dern)
aggressively coerces people into selling their land.  However,
when one landowner refuses to give in, his family is destroyed
and the landowner sent to jail.<BR>

<P>
Upon the innocent landowner's escape from confinement, the rail
baron hires a bounty hunter to kill him -- which he does, or so
it seems.<BR>

<P>
Witness a clever, highly-charged sting operation when <I><B>Dead
Man's Revenge</B></I> airs <U>Saturday, October 12, 1996, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<P>
