<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH-TV has the action drama "Spenser: A Savage Place". </TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H2>CHCH-TV Has the action drama</H2>
<H1>&quot;Spenser: A Savage Place&quot;</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
Spenser, the hard-nosed, philosophic detective, is seduced into
coming to the aid of an old girlfriend in one of his most compelling
cases in, <I><B>Spenser: A Savage Place</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday,
October 6, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
Starring in the action drama are <B>Robert Urich</B> (<I>Lonesome
Dove, Magnum Force, Mistral's Daughter, Princess Daisy, Spenser:
Ceremony, Spenser: Pale Kings &amp; Princes</I>), <B>Avery Brooks</B>
(<I>Roots - The Gift, The Emest Green Story, Spenser: Ceremony,
Spenser: Pale Kings &amp; Princes</I>) and <B>Wendy Crewson</B>
(<I>Folks, The Good Son, The Doctor, The Santa Clause</I>).<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Spenser: A Savage Place</B></I>, Spenser (Urich) receives
a desperate call for help from a former flame - crack television
reporter Candy Sloan - when her attempts to expose an apparent
racketeering ring result in the murder of her informant.<BR>

<P>
Candy's plea comes at an inopportune time for Spenser, as he and
his long-time psychologist girlfriend, Susan (Crewson), are considering
living together.  However, he cannot ignore a call for help from
an old friend, who happens to be beautiful.<BR>

<P>
Assisting Spenser on his latest investigation is his mysterious,
streetwise friend, Hawk (Brooks).  Soon, they find themselves
in a dangerous situation that encompasses everything from phony
credit cards to smuggling -- with a lethal mastermind calling
all the shots.<BR>

<P>
Spenser may survive life-threatening predicaments in his effort
to solve the case, but his greatest risk is still to come: will
Susan be waiting for him when he returns?  <I><B>Spenser: A Savage
Place</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, October 6, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
