<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Deadly Love" on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Deadly Love&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A vampire who falls passionately in love with a police detective
makes a heartwrenching decision when she decides to leave him
and entrust him with the most loving gift she has to offer - his
humanity in, <I><B>Deadly Love</B></I>, airing <U>Saturday, October
5, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <BR>

<P>
<B>Susan Dey</B> (<I>L.A. Law, Echo Park, The Comeback Kid</I>),
<B>Stephen McHattie </B>(<I>Beverly Hills Cop 3, The Dark, James
Dean - A Legend In His Own Time</I>) and <B>Jean LeClerc</B> (<I>Blown
Away, Whispers</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Deadly Love</B></I>, Rebecca Barnes (Dey) is a successful
photographer who has it all, even immortality.  Rebecca, however,
abandoned by the vampire who seduced her (LeClerc), hungers for
companionship.  In her quest to find a soulmate, she leaves a
trail of bodies when she &quot;feeds.&quot;  Photographs she snaps
of one of the victims prompts a police investigation and leads
her to Detective Sean O'Connor (McHattie), a man who will eventually
be willing to join her in immortality.<BR>

<P>
As the passion between Rebecca and Sean intensifies, the evidence
against Rebecca mounts.  When Sean is finally exposed to the truth,
he craves to join his lover forever.  Rebecca, knowing the price
of immortality, decides to leave Sean with the most precious gift
she can give to him - his life.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Deadly Love</B></I> airs <U>Saturday, October 5, 1996 at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.        <BR>
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
