<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Rookies" on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Rookies&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
When a seventeen-year-old hockey player from Northern Ontario
becomes involved with the team owner's daughter, his small-town
values are severely tested and one mistake could cost him his
future in the action drama, <I><B>Rookies</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday,
October 1, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Yannick Bisson, Peter MacNeill, Dean McDermott, Ian Tracey,
Christianne Hirt</B> and <B>Andrea Roth</B> star.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Rookies</B></I> is the story of Corey Dyson, a young hockey
hotshot from a small Northern Ontario village who tries out for
the Oshawa Blades and discovers that the competition is stiff
and he must prove himself in the major leagues.  Other rookies
include a local kid, who has only ever wanted to make his home-town
team, plus the younger brother of a hockey superstar, who needs
to demonstrate he can make it on his own.  The team captain is
an aging player with one last shot at the big time.<BR>

<P>
This action-packed drama is comprised of as many stories as there
are players and illustrates that some of the biggest risks these
players take are not always on the ice --  a lesson Corey learns
the hard way, as he is forced to choose between his village sweetheart
and the glamorous daughter of the team's owner.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Rookies</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, October 1, 1996, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
