<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Two Mothers For Zachary", A Touching Drama on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 12, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Two Mothers For Zachary&quot;</H1>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
A woman loses the right to care for her son when her mother sues
for custody of the child on the grounds that her daughter's homosexuality
makes her an unfit mother. Based on a true story, <I><B>Two Mothers
for Zachary</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, September 22, 1996 (9:00 -
11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Valerie Bertinelli </B>(<I>Ordinary Heroes, Shattered Vows</I>),<B>
Vanessa Redgrave </B>(<I>Howards End, Agatha, House of the Spirits</I>)
and <B>James Gammon</B> (<I>Leaving Normal, Major League, Major
League II</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Two Mothers for Zachary</B></I>, a spirited Jody Ann
Shaffell (Bertinelli) moves in with her mother, Nancy (Redgrave),
and her mother's live-in boyfriend, Harlan, following the birth
of her son, Zachary. One morning, after Jody returns from a night
of carousing, Nancy confronts her daughter about her derelict
behaviour and warns her that she will take Zachary away from her
if she fails to straighten out her life.<BR>

<P>
Recognizing the strong bond developing between Nancy and Zach,
and knowing Nancy would carry out her threat, Jody adopts a more
responsible lifestyle. Shortly after starting her new job, Jody
meets Maggie. When the two women's friendship evolves into a warm,
caring relationship, Jody and Zach move in with Maggie. <BR>

<P>
Nancy, appalled to discover that her daughter is gay, finds the
living situation her daughter has chosen to be detrimental to
Zach's upbringing. The issue erupts when Jody disallows Zach to
stay with Nancy anymore as she does not want Zach in the same
house as Harlan, whom, Jody claims, sexually molested her while
she was growing up. Vehemently, Nancy denies the accusations and
successfully sues her daughter for custody of Zach. <BR>

<P>
What ensues is a story filled with anguish, frustration and hope,
as Jody, to this day, fights to win back her son from her mother.
<I><B>Two Mothers for Zachary</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, September
22, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
<TABLE COLSPACE=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0 BORDER=0>
