<HEAD>

<TITLE>Niagara Grape and Wine Festival Celebrates History With The Pen Centre Grande on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>September 13, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H2>Niagara Grape and Wine Festival</H2><BR>
<H2>Celebrates History With</H2><BR>
<H2>The Pen Centre Grande Parade</H2><BR>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
On Saturday, September 28, the Niagara Grape &amp; Wine Festival
will host one of North America's foremost parades, <I>The Pen
Centre Grande Parade.</I> The 45-year-old procession will salute
the city of St. Catharines' bicentennial with the theme: 200 Years
of Pride and Progress. Highlights of <I><B>The</B></I> <I><B>Pen
Centre Grande Parade</B></I> will be broadcast <U>Sunday, September
29, 1996 (3:00 - 4:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <BR>

<P>
Experience the vintage celebration with Honourary Parade Marshall,
Canadian and World Champion Curler <B>Marilyn Bodogh</B> and NHL
Hockey Hall of Fame Inductee, <B>Jack Gatecliff</B>.<BR>

<P>
Billed as the largest parade in its 45 year history, <I><B>The
Pen Centre Grande Parade </B></I>will feature colourful floats,
marching bands, drum corps, majorettes, giant inflatables, street
bands and more.<BR>

<P>
As part of the Niagara Grape and Wine Festival's tribute to the
City of St. Catharines' bicentennial, the event will also include
a float carrying a replica of the &quot;Church at St. Catharines.&quot;
As well, there will be three military re-enactment troops in period
costumes complete with muskets, which they will fire in displays
along the parade route.<BR>

<P>
Be sure to catch the highlights of the 1996 <I><B>Pen Centre Grande
Parade</B></I>, hosted by the Niagara Grape &amp; Wine Festival,
<U>Sunday, September 29, 1996 at 3:00 p.m</U>. on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.

<P>

