<HEAD>

<TITLE>The CRTC Announces Decision on CHCH-TV's Expansion Applications.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 28, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>The CRTC Announces Decision on</H1>
<H1>CHCH-TV's Ontario Expansion Applications</H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
CHCH-TV is pleased to receive approval from the Canadian Radio-television
and Telecommunications Commission (CRTC) to establish rebroadcast
transmitters in seven Ontario markets: Ottawa, London, Muskoka,
North Bay, Sudbury, Sault Ste. Marie and Timmins. <BR>

<P>
&quot;Unquestionably, we are delighted with the Commission's decision,&quot;
says Jim Macdonald, president and chief executive officer, CHCH-TV.
&quot;The station's long term interests depended upon this conclusion.
While we are disappointed the CRTC approval of our applications
did not include Kingston, Peterborough and Thunder Bay,&quot;
continues Macdonald, &quot;we are left with the opportunity to
file applications for these markets at another time. With the
CRTC's endorsement to expand our coverage area within the province,
CHCH will be able to compete more equitably in the future.<BR>

<P>
&quot;What I must also make clear at this point,&quot; emphasizes
Macdonald, &quot;is that CHCH's current commitment to local news
coverage will not be affected by our Ontario expansion plans.&quot;
<BR>

<P>
The targeted time frame for rebroadcast transmitters servicing
London, Muskoka, 
<P>
North Bay, Sudbury, Sault Ste. Marie and Timmins to be operational
is spring 1997. The targeted time frame for the Ottawa market
is February 1997. <BR>

<P>
CHCH-TV is a member of WIC Television Ltd., a WIC Western International
Communications Ltd. company. WIC Television Ltd. owns eight television
stations. In addition to CHCH-TV (an independent), WIC Television
Ltd. owns BCTV-Vancouver and CHEK- Victoria (both CTV affiliates),
CHBC-Kelowna and RDTV-Red Deer (both CBC affiliates), ITV-Edmonton,
CICT-Calgary and CISA-Lethbridge (all independents).<BR>

<P>
WIC Western International Communications Ltd. is a leading Canadian
broadcast, communications and entertainment company with its head
office in Vancouver, British Columbia. WIC operates in four market
segments: television, pay television, radio and satellite network
services. In addition to its eight television stations, WIC owns
12 radio stations and is the pay television licensee in Western
Canada for Superchannel, MovieMax! and Home Theatre, a pay-per-view
service which operates under the name Viewer's Choice. Through
Superchannel, WIC has a 50 percent ownership in The Family Channel
Inc. WIC is active in telecommunications and satellite network
services through its 53.7 per cent ownership of Cancom. WIC and
Cancom together own an equity interest in ExpressVu Inc., a Canadian
satellite television direct-to-home (DTH) distribution company.
WIC is also parent to CellularVision Canada Ltd., a wholly-owned
subsidiary which has applied to Industry Canada to provide wireless
broadband communications services to homes and businesses across
the country.

<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
