<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Dark Horse", on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Dark Horse&quot;</H1>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
Through the love, belief and inexperienced talent of an equestrian
team, an unpredictable stallion accomplishes the impossible in
the inspiring special, <I><B>Dark Horse</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday,
September 1, 1996 (8:00 - 9:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Wayne Robson</B> (<I>The Grey Fox</I>), <B>Christianne Hirt</B>
(<I>Skate!</I>)<I>,</I> <B>Leon Pownall</B> (<I>Dead Poets Society</I>)
and <B>Catherine Disher</B> star.<BR>

<P>
In<I><B> Dark Horse</B></I>, Derek Conrad (Pownall) is having
difficulty selling Torka, a Grand Prix dressage horse.  His lineage
is that of champions, however, this stallion seems more in need
of a psychiatrist than a trainer.  Only Alanna (Disher), Conrad's
daughter, and Elliot (Robson), an untried trainer, share a special
feeling about Torka.  It is through their love and trust that
the stallion begins to fulfill his potential. <BR>

<P>
When Conrad's optimism about selling the horse rises, Alanna and
Elliott convince him, instead, to let Torka prove himself in the
Olympics, just four months away.  After hiring a promising, unseasoned
rider (Hirt), the dark horse team are ready to challenge the world.
<BR>

<P>
The road to the Olympics is simultaneously arduous and exciting
and suddenly the obstacles of the dressage competition seem moderate
compared with the problems the team has already overcome.  With
the impossible already accomplished, an Olympic medal is in sight.
<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Dark Horse</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, September 1, 1996 at
8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
