<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Fighting Back", on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Fighting Back&quot;</H1>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
A young fighter, blinded by a lucky punch, faces the fight of
his life when a promising boxer he trains is pitted against the
fighter who knocked him out of the ring.  <I><B>Fighting Back</B></I>,
an uplifting, powerful story that takes place inside as well as
outside the ring, airs <U>Sunday, September 8, 1996 (8:00 - 9:00)</U>,
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Real Andrews, George Touliatos, Justin Louis, Chris Owens,
Denise McLeod</B> and <B>Christopher Bondy</B> star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Fighting Back</B></I>, Tommy Mills (Andrews) is a fighter
who has everything going for him -- a loving wife, kids at his
boxing club who adore him and an extraordinary right hand that
will take him to the top.  But when a lucky punch from a competitor
leaves him blind, all seems lost.<BR>

<P>
The attempts of his wife and manager to convince Tommy to enter
into a rehabilitation program are fruitless.  However, when he
learns that Phillip, a bright talent who idolized him, has joined
a street gang and is headed for trouble, Tommy talks to him. 
For the first time in a long while, he feels useful.  He even
agrees to become Phillip's trainer and despite his lack of sight,
is able to remember more than most trainers will ever know.<BR>

<P>
When a cunning promoter proposes the idea of pitting Phillip against
the same fighter who blinded Tommy, Tommy opposes the match, arguing
that Phillip isn't ready.  It is his wife who changes his mind
by reminding him of another young, hungry boxer from years ago.
<BR>

<P>
Now, Tommy and Phillip face the fight of their lives in the one
hour special, <I><B>Fighting Back</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, September
8, 1996 at 8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
