<HEAD>

<TITLE>A woman remembers nothing in "Sweet Dreams," on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 19, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H2>A woman remembers nothing in the drama</H2>
<H1>&quot;Sweet Dreams&quot;</H1>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
A young woman, victimized by her husband and his mistress, must
recall who she is before a murderous plot is carried through in,
<I><B>Sweet Dreams</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, September 15, 1996
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.<BR>

<P>
<B>Tiffani-Amber Thiessen</B> (<I>She Fought Alone, Beverly Hills
90210</I>), <B>Amy Yasbeck </B>(<I>Wings</I>), <B>David Newsom
</B>(<I>Homefront</I>), <B>A Martinez</B> (<I>L.A. Law</I>) and
<B>Conchata Ferrell </B>(<I>L.A. Law</I>) star.<BR>

<P>
In <I><B>Sweet Dreams</B></I>, when a young woman (Thiessen) is
found sopping wet and hypothermic on Long Harbour Island's Ruby
Beach, police chief Doug Harrison (Martinez) rushes her to the
hospital.  With the island doctor's help (Ferrell), the young
woman regains her health, but is unable to remember her name.
 Days later, Dr. Jack Renault (Newsom), a psychiatrist who is
renting a house on the island with his wife Laura (Yasbeck) and
year-old daughter, appears on the scene offering his assistance,
claiming he had learned about the &quot;mystery&quot; woman in
the paper.<BR>

<P>
Harrison, attracted to the amnesiac woman known as &quot;Jane,&quot;
is suspicious of Renault and his wife, for they seem overly interested
in the victim's case.  As Renault continues to treat &quot;Jane,&quot;
bits and pieces of her past are revealed and she discovers her
real name is Alison.  Gradually, flashes of elapsed memories strike
a familiar chord, but Alison does not have the luxury of time
to linger over these revelations.  She must uncover her identity
as quickly as possible before the evil duo, Jack and Laura, can
complete their deadly scheme.<BR>

<P>
<I><B>Sweet Dreams</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, September 15, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>NBC</B>.<BR>

<P>
<U><I><FONT SIZE=2>Note:</FONT></I></U><FONT SIZE=2> <I>Sweet
Dreams</I> was shot in Vancouver.<BR>
</FONT>


