<HEAD>

<TITLE>The University Game of the Week kicks off another season on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 16, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H2>OUAA Hall of Famer <B>Neil Lumsden</B> joins CHCH-TV's</H2>
<H1>University Game of the Week</H1>
<H2>commentating team.</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The <I><B>University Game of the Week</B></I> kicks off another
season of gridiron action starting <U>Saturday, September 7, 1996
(2:00 - 5:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B> as the Laurier Golden
Hawks take on the Western Mustangs. <BR>

<P>
Joining the returning football commentating team of <B>Paul Hendrick</B>
and sideline analyst <B>Ken Welch</B> is 10 year CFL veteran <B>Neil
Lumsden</B>, the Hamilton Tiger-Cats' current General Manager
and Director of Business Operations.  As a player, Lumsden won
championships at three levels -- high school, university and professional.
 He remains Canadian University football's all-time leading scorer
with 410 points and, in 1994, was inducted into the Ontario University
Athletic Association Hall of Fame.  Professionally, Lumsden has
earned three Grey Cup rings (1980, 1981 and 1982) while playing
for the Edmonton Eskimos.<BR>

<P>
When the basketball season commences in January 1997, <B>Paul
Hendrick</B> and former NBA player with the Washington Bullets,<B>
Brian Heaney</B>, will cover the college sports zone.<BR>

<P>
Popular features such as &quot;Player Profile,&quot; &quot;Hits
of the Week,&quot; &quot;Fan of the Week&quot;  and &quot;Hoops
of the Half&quot; will again be part of the program format.<BR>

<P>
<B>CHCH</B> and the <B>OUAA</B> have enjoyed a history together
that exceeds 30 years.  Be part of the tradition, catch the <I><B>University
Game of the Week</B></I> <U>Saturdays at  2:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>
commencing September 7, 1996.<BR>

<P>

