<HEAD>

<TITLE>Danielle Steel's "Remembrance", on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>August 14, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>Danielle Steel's &quot;Remembrance&quot;</H1>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
An Italian woman forfeits everything to marry an American army
officer.  What ensues for the couple and their daughter, however,
is a series of heartwrenching tragedies.  Her extraordinary saga
is recounted by her grown daughter in <I><B>Danielle Steel's Remembrance</B></I>
airing <U>Saturday, August 31, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.),</U> on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.  <BR>

<P>
<B>Angie Dickinson</B> (<I>Dressed To Kill</I>), <B>Eva La Rue</B>
(<I>All My Children</I>) and <B>Jeffrey Nordling </B>star.<BR>

<P>
In the classic tradition of the best-selling author, <I><B>Danielle
Steel's Remembrance</B></I> is about Vanessa, a woman who finds
the emotional strength to describe the exceptional life led by
her mother, Serena (La Rue).<BR>

<P>
Born into Italian royalty, Serena leaves everything to marry U.S.
Colonel Brad Fullerton (Nordling).  Following his tragic military
death, a distressed and destitute Serena enters the world of modelling,
where she meets renowned photographer, Vasili.  Her career as
well as her relationship with Vasili soar, until Serena uncovers
the photographer's shocking secret, which ultimately leads to
her death.<BR>

<P>
Through her mother's experiences, Vanessa is finally able to allay
a lifetime of painful memories in <I><B>Danielle Steel's Remembrance</B></I>,
airing <U>Saturday, August 31, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/NBC.<BR>
<BR>

