<HEAD>

<TITLE>"When The Vow Breaks",  starring Patty Duke, on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>July 18, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;When The Vow Breaks&quot;</H1>
<H3><I>starring Patty Duke</I></H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
When a man designates his daughter as sole beneficiary of his
life insurance, his wife files for divorce.  The action ultimately
leads her to a richer existence as she rebuilds her life; enters
law school; and, representing herself, wins a court appeal in,
<I><B>When The Vow Breaks</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday, August 6,
1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
<B>Patty Duke</B> and <B>Linda Dano</B> star in the made-for-television
movie based on a true story.
<P>
In<B> <I>When the Vow Breaks</I></B>, Barbara Porter (Duke) is
a devoted mother and grandmother trapped in a passionless marriage
to a controlling man.  The marriage completely disintegrates when
her husband appoints his daughter as sole beneficiary of his life
insurance policy.  At that point Barbara files for divorce.
<P>
While preparing for the hearing, it is discovered that Barbara's
husband is a millionaire twice-over and he alone has control over
their assets.  At the conclusion of the hearing, Barbara is delivered
several devastating blows by the presiding judge who is notorious
for his contempt for no-fault divorce.  Her husband is awarded
their entire estate and Barbara's plea for no financial support
is ignored and weekly alimony payments decreed.  
<P>
Unwilling to defy the distinguished judge's decision, Barbara's
attorney suggests she represent herself in an appeal.  Following
her lawyer's advice, Barbara enters law school.
<P>
In the middle of reassembling her life, Barbara meets a new man,
renews her relationship with her daughter and achieves her utmost
goal -- she represents herself in court and wins the battle. 
In addition, Barbara discloses damaging information that leads
to the termination of the once venerated judge.
<P>
<I><B>When The Vow Breaks</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, August 6, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

