<HEAD>
<TITLE>"Indecency", A Suspense Thriller on CHCH-TV</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>July 16, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Indecency&quot;</H1>
<H2>A Suspense Thriller</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>


<P>
A beautiful woman recovering from a mental breakdown is caught
in an intricate web of passion, betrayal and murder in, <I><B>Indecency</B></I>,
airing <U>Sunday, August 4, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.),</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
<B>Jennifer Beals</B> (<I>2000 Malibu Road, Flashdance, The Bride</I>),
<B>James Remar</B> (<I>Session Man, Drugstore Cowboy</I>), <B>Sammi
Davis-Voss</B> and <B>Barbara Williams </B>star.
<P>
In <I><B>Indecency</B></I>, Ellie Shaw (Beals), a young woman
still in a delicate state following a mental breakdown, begins
work at a fashionable ad agency owned by Marie Clarkson (Williams).
 When Marie's estranged husband, Mick (Remar), arrives on the
scene staking a claim on a share of his wife's business, Ellie's
life starts to plunge into a mad world of drugs, extortion and
a place where everyone seems to have a motive for murder.
<P>
At first, Ellie is both repelled and attracted to Mick, yet she
chooses to becomes his latest mistress even after Marie commits
suicide and it is disclosed that Marie's shrewd associate (Davis-Voss)
had an extramarital affair with him.
<P>
Soon after, however, Ellie's impassioned emotions for Mick turn
to terror as clues surface  strongly suggesting that Marie's suicide
was not suicide, but murder.
<P>
<I><B>Indecency</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, August 4, 1996, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
