<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Canadian Masters, One of Canada's Major International Golf Championships, on CHCH-TV</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>July 10, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>The Canadian Masters</H1>
<H2>One of Canada's Major International Golf Championships</H2>
<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>


<P>
The<I><B> Canadian Masters</B></I>, the richest tournament on
the Canadian Professional Golf Tour, will be broadcast <I>live</I>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B> for four hours -- <U>Saturday, July 27 (4:00
- 6:00 p.m.)</U> and <U>Sunday, July 28 (4:00 - 6:00 p.m.)</U>.
 The $250,000 event runs July 22 - 28, 1996, at the Heron Point
Golf Links in Ancaster, Ontario.
<P>
Assuming host responsibilities will be <B>CHCH</B>'s own <B>Paul
Hendrick</B> who will be joined by colour commentator <B>Ben Kern
</B>and course roving reporter <B>Bob Panasik</B>.
<P>
Based on <I>The Masters</I> in Augusta, Georgia and launched in
1994 in Canada, the <I><B>Canadian Masters</B></I> consistently
attracts high profile players, ranging from well-known veterans
such as Dan Halldorson to rising international talents like Roger
Wessels and Scott Dunlap.
<P>
The winner of the <I><B>Canadian Masters</B></I> receives the
George Knudson Memorial Trophy.  Scott Dunlap of Sarasota, Florida
won the 1995 <I>Canadian Masters</I>, his second Canadian Tour
victory.  He captured the Xerox Manitoba Open title in 1994. 
<P>
The <I><B>1996 Canadian Masters</B></I> also marks <B>CHCH-TV</B>'s
inauguration as the broadcast sponsor for the event.  With extensive
technical experience in covering major golf and sporting events,
the station is pleased to join Timex Canada, Teledyne Water Pik,
Canpar Transport Ltd., Cadillac and the Cadillac Dealers of Ontario
as a major sponsor of the prestigious championship.
<P>
The <I><B>Canadian Masters</B></I>, one of Canada's major international
golf championships, will be broadcast <I>live</I> from Heron Point
Golf Links in Ancaster on <U>Saturday, July 27 and Sunday, July
28, 1996, starting at 4:00 p.m.</U> (both days) on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

