<HEAD>

<TITLE>"A Kiss Before Dying", a suspenseful thriller on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>July 9, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;A Kiss Before Dying&quot;</H1>
<H3><I>starring Matt Dillion and Sean Young</I></H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
The daughter of a wealthy man marries a charismatic charmer only
to discover he has a ruthless, deadly side and an evil scheme
for success in the suspense thriller, <I><B>A Kiss Before Dying</B></I>,
airing <U>Sunday, July 21, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.),</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Matt Dillon </B>(<I>Drugstore Cowboy, The Flamingo Kid, My
Bodyguard, Little Darlings, Liar's Moon</I>),<B> Sean Young </B>(<I>Dune,
No Way Out, Wall Street</I>),<B> Max von Sydow </B>(<I>The Seventh
Seal, Wild Strawberries, The Kremlin Letter, Three Days of the
Condor, The Exorcist</I>),<B> Diane Ladd</B> (<I>Wild At Heart</I>)
and <B>James Russo </B>(<I>Extremities</I>) star.
<P>
In <I><B>A Kiss Before Dying</B></I> Jonathan Corliss (Dillon)
is a young, handsome, mesmerizing man -- the kind any woman would
want to marry and any mother would want her daughter to marry.
 Jonathan is also a materialistic and ambitious man, determined
to get ahead at all cost.  Among the people he deceives with his
irresistible charm is Ellen Carlsson (Young), the daughter of
wealthy businessman, Thor Carlsson (von Sydow).  
<P>
After killing Ellen's twin sister (Young plays dual roles), he
weds her.  However, what Jonathan really wants is to be chairman
of the board and to succeed Carlsson.  If that means getting involved
with Carlsson's daughters and murder along the way, so be it.

<P>
<I><B>A Kiss Before Dying </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, July 21, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
