<HEAD>
<TITLE>"At Play In The Fields of the Lord", a special movie presentation on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>July 8, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;At Play in the Fields of the Lord&quot;</H1>

<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
Mercenaries and missionaries barter for the land as well as the
souls of a native culture fighting for its survival.  In the process,
high ideals clash with brutal realities and both good and evil
are found to be imperfect in <I><B>At Play in the Fields of the
Lord</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, July 28 (part 1)</U> and <U>Monday,
July 29, 1996 (part 2; 9:00 - 11:00 p.m. both nights)</U>, on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Tom Berenger </B>(<I>The Big Chill, Platoon, Someone to Watch
Over Me, Shattered</I>),<B> John Lithgow </B>(<I>Blow Out, All
That Jazz, Terms of Endearment, Memphis Belle, Raising Cain</I>),<B>
Darryl Hannah </B>(<I>Splash, Steel Magnolias, Roxanne, Grumpy
Old Men, Grumpier Old Men)</I>,<B> Aidan Quinn </B>(<I>Avalon,
Reckless,  Legends of the Fall</I>),<B> Tom Waits </B>(<I>Paradise
Alley, Ironweed, The Fisher King, The Cotton Club, </I>Bram Stoker's<I>
Dracula</I>) and <B>Kathy Bates</B> ( <I>Misery, Fried Green Tomatoes,
Dolores Claiborne</I>) star.
<P>
<I><B>At Play in the Fields of the Lord</B></I>, adapted from
the novel by Peter Matthiessen, is about power, progress, greed,
religion and two cultures in conflict as a moral, human chess
game unfolds.  It is also about how even good intentions, if misguided,
can destroy a thriving culture -- a conclusion reached by two
characters in the film through radically different paths.  
<P>
Hired by a local government official to drive the Niaruna tribe
off their land, Lewis Moon (Berenger) an American mercenary, who
is himself one-half Cheyenne, joins the Brazilian native tribe.
 Opposite Moon is Martin Quarrier (Quinn), a missionary intent
on converting the tribe to Christianity, but finds his respect
for their beliefs in conflict with his mission.  As well, he becomes
disillusioned by the hypocrisy of his superior, evangelist Leslie
Huben (Lithgow).  Both Moon and Quarrier join forces to confront
the power and violence of authorities and in the process question
their moral right to lead the Indians to a &quot;better way of
life.&quot;
<P>
<I><B>At Play in the Fields of the Lord</B></I> airs <U>Sunday,
July 28 (part 1)</U> and <U>Monday, July 29, 1996 (part 2), at
9:00 p.m. (both nights)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
