<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Youth Violence", an informative special on CHCH-TV</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>June 25, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Youth Violence - What's Out There&quot;</H1>
<H3><I>an informative special</I></H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
<I><B>Youth Violence - What's Out There</B></I>, the second show
in the <I>Be Careful, Be Safe </I>RCMP series, is an  energetic,
interactive program, which effectively utilizes dramatic re-enactments
of potentially violent situations and explains how young people
should handle those predicaments in order to prevent the eruption
of violence.  <I><B>Youth Violence - What's Out There</B></I>
airs <U>Saturday, July 6, 1996 (8:30 - 9:00 p.m.)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<I><B>Youth Violence - What's Out There</B></I> offers to young
people the &quot;tools to take a stand and make a difference.&quot;
 Jackson Davies, Sasha Vracarevic and members of the group 8-4-1
KOZ address such situations as: how to avoid violence; how to
keep it out of your community; and what to do if you find yourself
in the wrong place at the wrong time.  Subjects covered include
<I>Intimidation, Gangs, Weapons </I>and<I> Date Rape.</I>
<P>
Designed to appeal to youth, the program also provides information
on how parents can help put an end to youth violence.
<P>
The <I>Be Careful, Be Safe</I> award-winning series is co-produced
by the Royal Canadian Mounted Police, Friday Communications Inc.
and <B>BCTV</B>.  The first series, <I>Safe Children</I>, was
awarded First Place at the 1994 Crime Stoppers International Awards,
as well as the 1996 CANPRO Showcase Award. 
<P>
<I><B>Youth Violence - What's Out There</B></I> airs <U>Saturday,
July 6, 1996 at 8:30 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
