<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Far & Away", starring Tom Cruise, on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>June 24, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Far &amp; Away&quot;</H1>
<H3><I>starring Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman</I></H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
Two young, and highly unlikely, Irish travelling companions escape
to America in search of a new beginning and to possess the one
great prize -- land, in the two-part sweeping saga, <I><B>Far
and Away</B></I>, airing<U> Sunday, July 7 (part 1) and Monday,
July 8, 1996 (part 2; 9:00 - 11:00 p.m. both nights)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Tom Cruise</B> (<I>Mission: Impossible, A Few Good Men, The
Firm, Cocktail</I>) and <B>Nicole Kidman</B> (<I>To Die For, Batman
Forever, Billy Bathgate, Dead Calm</I>) star with <B>Thomas Gibson,
Robert Prosky, Barbara Babcock, Colm Meaney </B>and<B> Eileen
Pollock</B>.    
<P>
In <I><B>Far and Away</B></I>, set in the 1800s, Joseph Donelly
(Cruise) and Shannon Christie (Kidman) are two young people from
different social classes, who escape together to the New World.
 The bickering twosome start out on an adventure of a lifetime
with nothing, except their dreams.  What they discover is the
true depth of their courage, love and resourcefulness as they
head west to win freedom and land during the time of the great
Oklahoma land rush.
<P>
<B>Ron Howard</B> (<I>Apollo 13, Backdraft, Cocoon, Grand Theft
Auto, The Paper, Parenthood</I>) directed the feature.
<P>
<I><B>Far And Away</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, July 7 and Monday,
July 8, 1996 at 9:00 p.m.</U> (both nights) on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

