<HEAD>

<TITLE>"From The Yukon To The Yucatan: Eco Variety" a CHCH special presentation.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>May 21, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I>&quot;From The Yukon to the Yucatan: Eco Variety&quot;</I></H1>
<H3>a special presentation coinciding with Canadian Environment Week on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
<I><B>From the Yukon to the Yucatan: ECO Variety</B></I>, an upbeat,
entertaining and informative one hour special featuring well-known
North American talent, offers solution-oriented reports while
profiling critical environmental concerns.  <I><B>ECO Variety</B></I>
airs <U>Saturday, June 8, 1996, (8:00 - 9:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Actor <B>Graham Greene</B> hosts the variety program which includes
guest appearances by such Canadian musicians as <B>Buffy Sainte
Marie, Sarah McLachlan, Bruce Cockburn, Hemingway Corner, Jane
Siberry, Fred Eaglesmith </B>and children's singer <B>Rosie Emery</B>.
<P>
The theme of <I><B>ECO Variety</B></I> is &quot;we are all interconnected...
regardless of race, colour and nationality, and that our individual
actions make a difference.&quot;  National borders are eliminated
and environmental issues and solutions are linked.  
<P>
Guest artists perform selections related to the environment and
offer personal views on ecological concerns.  Reports explore
common North American environmental issues including the Monarch
butterfly's incredible journey from Canada to Mexico, projects
that encourage smart transportation choices and the new role of
zoos as conservationists -- with a look at the North American
Species Survival Program at the Metro Toronto Zoo.  
<P>
Segments also showcase important contributions made by young people
and animated pieces, focusing on ecological issues, lend a lighthearted
spirit to a serious topic.
<P>
<I><B>Eco Variety</B></I>, an international effort culminating
in unique programs in Canada, the U.S. and Mexico, is produced
by NewVue Productions in Canada, Uplinger Enterprises in the U.S.
and Televisa in Mexico.  The program was created in cooperation
with NACEC (North American Commission for Environmental Cooperation).
<P>
<I><B>From the Yukon to the Yucatan: ECO Variety</B></I> airs
<U>Saturday, June 8, 1996 at 8:00 p.m. </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
