<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Mother's Day Telethon exceeds goal for fourth consecutive year!</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>May 12, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I>The Mother's Day Telethon</I></H1>
<H3>exceeds goal for fourth consecutive year!</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
The fourth annual <I><B>Mother's Day Telethon</B></I>, a partnership
between <B>CHCH-TV</B> and <B>Chedoke-McMaster Hospitals Foundation</B>,
concluded its 24-hour celebration at 7:00 p.m. tonight, <U>Sunday,
May 12, 1996,</U> with the tote board proudly displaying the final
tally, <B>$1,045,630! </B>
<P>
&quot;The generosity of people in the communities we serve is
simply extraordinary,&quot; expressed Ursula Evans, executive
director of the <B>Chedoke-McMaster Hospitals Foundation </B>and
co-executive producer of the telethon. &quot;We are truly grateful
to all the individuals, groups and corporations who have participated
this year. Their tremendous support of the Children's Hospital
will provide much needed equipment to enhance the care of acutely
and critically ill children and their families.&quot; 
<P>
Children's Hospital at Chedoke-McMaster serves a population base
of 1.8 million people in over 70 communities in central west Ontario.
Funds raised from this year's telethon will be allocated to the
purchase of: an <B>NICU Transport Incubator, Laparoscopes, Metabolic
Cart, Microcomputers, PIC Monitors </B>and<B> Ventilators.</B>
<P>
&quot;What is particularly gratifying and inspiring to see each
year,&quot; continues Ursula Evans, &quot;is the number of young
people involved and individuals who come forth with fresh concepts
to raise funds for the Hospital. For example, this year, 85 schools
were responsible for raising over $85,000, and Jimmy Vlajkov from
The Attic, a well-known community supporter, was the impetus behind
the Sports Celebrity Auction, a new telethon feature which garnered
wonderful results.&quot;
<P>
&quot;In addition to the community members who embraced the spirit
of the telethon, I would like to acknowledge everyone who worked
on the production itself,&quot; added Reg McGuire, executive vice
president and general manager of <B>CHCH-TV</B> and co-executive
producer of the production. &quot;The many celebrities, volunteers
and <B>CHCH</B> staff and crew, all gave tirelessly of their time
and special talents. To each, we extend a heartfelt thank you.&quot;

<P>
The fourth annual <I><B>Mother's Day Telethon</B></I> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>
raised <B>$1,045,630!</B>
<P>

