<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Dr. Who", a new two-hour movie on CHCH-TV</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>May 6, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Dr. Who&quot;</I></H1>
<H3>a new television movie on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
The new two-hour movie, <I><B>Dr. Who</B></I>, based on the long-running
BBC science fiction series of the same name, finds The Doctor,
who travels through time restoring justice and overcoming alien
threats, embarking on his eighth adventure.  <I><B>Dr. Who </B></I>premieres
<U>Tuesday, May 14, 1996, (8:00 - 10:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Paul McGann </B> (<I>Withnail &amp; I, Alien</I>), <B>Daphne
Ashbrook</B> (<I>Midnight Heat</I>) and<B> Eric Roberts</B> (<I>It's
My Party</I>) star.
<P>
In <I><B>Dr. Who</B></I>, The Doctor (McGann) experiences a malfunction
with his time machine while transporting the remains of the evil
Master (Roberts) back to his home planet.  The problem forces
him to land in San Francisco on December 30, 1999, whereupon,
the injured Doctor is rushed to the hospital and The Master --
a serious danger to the Universe -- escapes and takes over the
body of an unsuspecting paramedic (Roberts).
<P>
While in hospital, The Doctor is accidentally killed on the operating
table by Dr. Grace Holloway (Ashbrook), who is unaware of his
two hearts.  However, after he regenerates into his new body,
it is the same Dr. Holloway that The Doctor turns to for help
in finding his identity, The Master and a way to save the Universe.
<P>
<I><B>Dr. Who</B></I>, a pilot for a possible television series
for Fall '96, premieres <U>Tuesday, May 14, 1996, at 8:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>Fox</B>.  
<P>

