<CENTER>
<H1><I>&quot;Ladies of Laughter&quot;</I></H1>
<H3>A new comedy special</H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>

<P>
The talents of five comediennes, who can stand-up with the best
of them and who have graced the stage of <I>Comedy at Club 54</I>
over the years, are showcased in, <I><B>Ladies of Laughter</B></I>,
airing <U>Tuesday, May 21, 1996 (10:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Ben Guyatt</B>, host and producer of <I>Comedy at Club 54</I>
and comedienne <B>Anna Collins</B> co-host the special hour of jovial jabs and jives.
<P>
Taped at Club 54 in Burlington, <I><B>Ladies of Laughter</B></I>
profiles the distinct comedic styles of five women: <B>Claudia
Sherman, Mary Anne Nichols, Meg Soper, Anna Collins </B>and <B>Beth
Donahue.  </B>
<P>
The special, <I><B>Ladies of Laughter</B></I>, airs <U>Tuesday,
May 21, 1996, at 10:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
