<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Thrill", the ride of a lifetime on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 30, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;Thrill&quot;</H1>
<H3><I>the ride of a lifetime</I></H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
A man terrified of heights must conquer his paralyzing fear in
order to save his daughter and her fellow passengers riding an
out of control roller coaster weighted with explosives in, <I><B>Thrill</B></I>,
airing <U>Monday, May 20, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.

<P>
<B>Antonio Sabato Jr</B>. (<I>Her Hidden Truth, Melrose Place</I>),
<B>Stepfanie Kramer</B> (<I>Abducted: A Father's Love</I>) and
<B>Maxxe Sternbaum </B>(<I>Sisters</I>) star.
<P>
In <I><B>Thrill</B></I>, Jack Coulson (Sabato Jr.) is a young
widower and father of a nine-year-old girl (Sternbaum), who has
broken from tradition to become an air-conditioning/heating engineer,
while his sister, Theresa (Kramer), continues to run the family-owned
business, Wild Dunes Amusement Park.
<P>
After Theresa is offered a huge sum of money to sell the Park,
problems begin to plague  the computerized mechanism controlling
the park's landmark roller coaster, &quot;Thrill.&quot;   When
a toy bomb is found suspended from the coaster's supports, a longtime
park employee, disgruntled by the sale, is arrested.  Following
the charge, the intimidation continues with one of the rides set
afire.  
<P>
However, the ultimate threat occurs when Jack's daughter and a
group of passengers find themselves trapped aboard a runaway roller
coaster, loaded with explosives.  In order to save them, Jack
must draw upon every ounce of courage and confront his personal
fears.
<P>
For the ride of a lifetime, don't miss <I><B>Thrill</B></I>, airing
<U>Monday, May 20, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
