<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Kidz in the Wood", a new movie on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 29, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H3>An all-star lineup of teens hit the history trail in</H3>
<H1><I> &quot;Kidz In The Wood&quot;</I></H1>
</CENTER>

<P>

An American history teacher takes his inner-city high school students
on a covered wagon journey along the Oregon Trail, where they
learn about themselves as well as their forefathers in, <I><B>Kidz
in the Wood</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday, May 21, 1996, (8:00 -
10:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Dave Thomas</B> (<I>Grace Under Fire</I>) and <B>Julia Duffy</B>
(<I>The Mommies, Newhart</I>) star in the two-hour comedy with
a line-up of talented teens including <B>Tatyana M. Ali</B> (<I>The
Fresh Prince of Bel-Air</I>), <B>Alfonso Ribeiro</B> (<I>The Fresh
Prince of Bel-Air</I>), <B>Candace Cameron</B> (<I>Full House</I>),
<B>Darius McCrary</B> (<I>Family Matters</I>) and <B>David Lascher</B>
(<I>Blossom</I>).
<P>
In <I><B>Kidz in the Wood</B></I>, American history teacher Tom
Foster (Thomas) is about to become part of the past himself if
he doesn't soon harness the unbridled energy of his inner-city
high school class. In an effort to bring the spirit and struggles
of the pioneer days to life, Foster decides to take his &quot;wild
bunch&quot; on a two-week covered wagon tour of the Oregon Trail.
<P>
As their forefathers did, the truly urban group of teens face
the challenges nature and the landscape present. Fighting rainstorms,
river rapids and bears, the young people get more than a history
lesson. They discover that they are reliable, sharp-witted, capable
individuals with a strong liking for the Western life.
<P>
<I><B>Kidz in the Wood</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, May 21, 1996,
at 8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>NBC</B>.  

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
