<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Our Son, The Matchmaker", a drama inspired by actual events, on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 23, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Our Son, The Matchmaker&quot;</I></H1>
<H2>a drama inspired by actual events, on CHCH-TV</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The son a woman gave up for adoption 28 years earlier, reunites
her with her one true love and presides over their wedding ceremony
in, <I><B>Our Son</B></I>, <I><B>The Matchmaker</B></I>, airing
<U>Tuesday, May 7, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Golden Globe Award winner and Emmy nominee <B>Ann Jillian </B>(<I>It's
a Living, Labour of Love: The Arlette Schweitzer Story, Little
White Lies, The Ann Jillian Story</I>) shares the screen in the
two-hour production with Academy and Tony Award winner <B>Ellen
Burstyn </B>(<I>Alice Doesn't Live Here Anymore, Same Time Next
Year, Roommates, Cemetery Club, Hannah's War, The Last Picture
Show</I>).
<P>
In <I><B>Our Son, The Matchmaker</B></I>, beauty shop owner Julie
Longwell (Jillian) is astounded when she learns that the son she
gave up for adoption, over two decades ago, is trying to find
her. The story takes viewers back to the time when Julie was 15
years of age and wildly in love with Steve Carson, a schoolmate.
When Julie becomes pregnant with his child, she is forced by her
mother (Burstyn), a fierce woman, to leave and give the child
up for adoption. Her abrupt departure does not allow for explanations
or good-byes with Steve, who remained oblivious of the circumstances.
<P>
Back in the present, Julie consents to meet with her son, Scott,
who is now a minister, married and expecting a child of his own.
At his insistence, Julie tracks down Steve. Her former sweetheart
is divorced and Julie, herself, engaged to another man, however,
they both discover the years have not diminished their passion
for one another. 
<P>
Through their son's ingenious manipulation, the two find the happiness
that was lost to them 28 years before, and when they reunite officially,
it is their son who officiates at the nuptials. 
<P>
<I><B>Our Son, The Matchmaker</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, May 7,
1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, one day pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
