<HEAD>

<TITLE>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</TITLE>

<TITLE>The Fourth Annual Mother's Day Telethon on CHCH-TV</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 18, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H3>&quot;Bringing Smiles Back for the Fourth Consecutive Year&quot;</H3>
<H1>The Mother's Day Telethon</H1>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
The <I><B>Mother's Day Telethon</B></I>, a partnership between
<B>CHCH-TV</B> and the Chedoke-McMaster Hospitals Foundation,
features <I>live </I>entertainment, a special Celebrity Sports
Auction and inspiring patient portraits of the children and families
helped by the Children's Hospital at Chedoke McMaster.  The fourth
annual 24-hour celebration kicks-off <U>Saturday, May 11, 1996
at 7:00 p.m.</U> and concludes <U>Sunday, May 12, 1996, at 7:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.   The goal is to raise is $1 million!
<P>
Hosted by <B>CHCH-TV</B> news anchors <B>Dan McLean</B> and <B>Connie
Smith</B>, the telethon will also include guest host appearances
by <B>Pat McKenna</B> (<I>The New Red Green Show, Traders</I>),
<B>Aashna Patel &amp; Paul McGuire</B> (YTV hosts of <I>The Breakfast
Zone</I>), Canadian legend <B>Gordie Tapp, Gema Zamprogna</B>
(<I>Road to Avonlea</I>), <B>Jaimz Woolvett</B> (<I>Road to Avonlea</I>),
<B>Catherine Swing, John Dawe,</B> <B>Jim Witter, Wendy Brunelle,</B>
<B>Michael Quast,</B> <B>Maria Hayes, Matt Hayes, Paul Hendrick,
Jennifer Mossop, Kathy Renwald, Alex Reynolds, Lauran Sabourin,
Donna Skelly, Scot Urquhart, Ken Welch,</B> <B>Jeff Lumby,</B>
<B>Ann Riches,</B> <B>Bob Bratina,</B> <B>Sunni Genesco, Peter
Jaycock,</B> <B>Karen Bertelsen</B>, <B>Robert J.</B> and <B>Jimmy
Vlajkov</B>.
<P>
Performing <I>live</I> on the <I><B>Mother's Day Telethon</B></I>
will be such well-known performers as <B>Jim Witter; Marc Jordan;
Amy Sky; Lighthouse; Sharon, Lois and Bram; Quartetto Gelato;</B>
<B>Jude Johnson; The Immigrants; Lawnie Wallace; Reggae Cowboys;
Faith Chorale;</B> <B>John Ellison; Dutch Robinson; D.J. Jones;
The Canadian Male Orpheus Choir; Children's International Peace
Choir; Hamilton All Star Jazz Band; The Russ Little House Band;
Freeflight;</B> <B>Ron Pardo</B> and <B>Elaine Overholt</B>. 
 
<P>
Children's performers will include <B>Cindy Cook</B> (<I>Polka
Dot Door, Time To Read</I>), <B>P.J. Katie</B> (YTV's <I>P.J.
Katie's Farm</I>), <B>Annick Obonsawin</B> (<I>Goosebumps, Squawk
Box</I>), <B>Jack Grunsky</B>, <B>Tebey Ottoh, Kideo, Kayla, Jason
Rumley, Steps Performing Arts Co. </B>and<B> Band-Aid the Clown.
</B>
<P>
The<B> <I>Mother's Day Telethon</I> </B>will also feature special
cameo appearances by <B>Ashley MacIsaac</B>,<B> Martin Short,
Jann Arden, Buffy Sainte-Marie, Susan Aglukark, George Fox, Colin
 James, Isiah Thomas, Blue Rodeo, Tom Cochrane,
Deborah Cox, Burton Cummings, Maureen Forrester </B>and<B> Ben
Heppner, Ronnie Hawkins, Jeff Healey, Kim Mitchell, Alannah Myles
</B>and<B> Russel DeCarle of Prairie Oyster.</B>
<P>
As in the past, however, the true stars of the telethon will be
the children and the thousands of families served by the Children's
Hospital in central-west Ontario.  Their stories will be told
through stirring, informative documentaries as well as through
<I>live </I>interviews originating from <B>CHCH-TV</B>'s television
studio, the Children's Hospital and satellite locations based
in Burlington (The Burlington Mall; Sunday, 12 noon - 2:30 p.m.)
and The Pen Centre (St. Catharines; Sunday 2:30 - 5:00 p.m.).
<P>
The Children's Hospital at Chedoke-McMaster is one of four government
designated, pediatric hospitals in Ontario, providing full health-care
services and facilities, while serving a population base of 1.8
million people in over 70 communities.  Specialized services include
pediatric trauma teams to transport acutely ill babies and children
to the centre for care, a neonatal intensive care unit, treatment
for children with cancer and leukemia, as well as surgical and
medical service to treat the complicated problems for children
with developmental and emotional challenges.
<P>
<B>The 1996 targets for support are the following areas:</B>
<P>
<I>    <B>-</B> NICU Transport Incubator         <B>- </B>Laparoscope
             <B>-</B> Metabolic Cart    </I>
<P>
<I>    <B>-</B> Microcomputers                         <B>-</B>
PIC Monitors and Ventilators</I>
<P>
Celebrate the message of hope and pride with the countless number
of celebrities, volunteers, corporate and individual sponsors,
who have given generously of their time and talents to help <I>bring
smiles back</I> to children and their families.  Watch the fourth
annual <I><B>Mother's Day Telethon</B></I> starting at <U>7:00
p.m. on Saturday, May 11, 1996</U> and concluding, 24 hours later,
on <U>Sunday, May 12, 1996</U> on <B>CHCH-TV.</B>
<P>


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
