<HEAD>

<TITLE>"No One Would Tell", a fact-based drama on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 15, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;No One Would Tell&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>a fact-based drama on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
A young girl's relationship with a popular high school athlete
turns into a fatal nightmare when his violent side is unleashed
in <I><B>No One Would Tell</B></I>, airing <U>Monday, May 6, 1996,
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Candace Cameron</B> (<I>Full House, Visitors of the Night</I>),
<B>Fred Savage </B>(<I>The Wonder Years</I>) and <B>Michelle Phillips</B>
(<I>Malibu Shores</I>) star.
<P>
In <I><B>No One Would Tell</B></I> Stacy Collins (Cameron), a
high school student who enjoys a close relationship with her mother
(Phillips), starts to stray from her as well as her best friend
when she develops a relationship with the campus &quot;dream guy,&quot;
Bobby Thompson (Savage).   
<P>
Realizing Bobby has difficulty controlling his temper, Stacy's
mother and friend become increasingly anxious over his abusive
treatment of her.   When Stacy is found murdered, Bobby is accused
of the crime. 
<P>
The teleplay, inspired by a true story, is directed by Noel Nosseck
(<I>Moment of Truth</I>).
<P>
<I><B>No One Would Tell</B></I> airs <U>Monday, May 6, 1996, at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
