<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Wiseguy", a new television movie on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 15, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Wiseguy&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>a new television movie on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
FBI agent Vinnie Terranova jeopardizes his life to infiltrate
and destroy a corrupt company run by a powerful married couple
in <I><B>Wiseguy</B></I>, airing <U>Wednesday, May 1, 1996, (9:00
-11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Ken Wahl</B>, <B>Debrah Farentino</B>, <B>Ted Levine</B> and
<B>Zachary Brown</B> star.
<P>
In <I><B>Wiseguy</B></I>, Vinnie Terranova (Wahl) secures a job
at an affluent country club frequented by Paul and Emma Callendar
(Levine and Farentino), the couple who head up a suspicious business,
Callendar Industries.  During his first day, Terranova thwarts
a kidnap attempt on the couple's young son, Alex (Brown).  While
recovering from his wounds in the hospital, Paul Callendar offers
Terranova the job of Alex's bodyguard.   
<P>
During an informal meeting with Paul, Terranova learns the nature
of his employer's illegal business -- the selling of high level
secrets to any one who can pay the price.  Soon afterwards, Terranova
accompanies Paul to a meeting with a Korean delegation seeking
classified information.  When Paul realizes the information they
request could put the lives of innocent Americans at risk, he
refuses to do business, which leads to a bloodthirsty shoot-out
and Terranova narrowly saving Paul's life.
<P>
The next morning Terranova awakens to the news that Paul has been
murdered and that his wife, Emma, is president of Callendar Industries.
 He also learns that her dealings with the company are more than
superficial.  It was she who had arranged the first meeting with
the Koreans with her now deceased husband.  As Terranova accompanies
Emma to a second meeting with the Korean group, he witnesses a
carefully orchestrated sting that ultimately sends the woman to
prison.
<P>
With Paul dead and Emma imprisoned, Alex is now left in the care
of his grandparents, however, Terranova vows to remain a constant
part of the child's life.  <I><B>Wiseguy</B></I> airs <U>Wednesday,
May 1, 1996 at 9:00 p.m. </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, one day pre-release/<B>ABC</B>.
    
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<CENTER>
