<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Beast", a four-hour mini-series on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 4, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;The Beast&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>a four-hour mini-series on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
Based on the best-selling novel by Peter Benchley (&quot;Jaws&quot;),
<I><B>The Beast</B></I> is about a gigantic sea creature that
terrorizes a quiet seaside community and, unless it is killed,
will demolish everyone.   <I><B>The Beast</B></I> airs <U>Sunday
and Monday, April 28 and 29, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>William Petersen </B>(<I>To Live &amp; Die in L.A., Manhunter,
Young Guns, Fear</I>), <B>Karen Sillas </B>(<I>True Blue, One
Life to Live, Simple Men, Risk, Under Suspicion</I>), and Emmy
winner <B>Larry Drake</B> (<I>L.A. Law, Darkman, The Karate Kid,
Dr. Giggles</I>) star.  Also appearing are <B>Missy Crider, Charles
Martin Smith, Ronald Guttman, Sterling Macer, Jr. </B>and <B>Murray
Bartlett.</B>
<P>
In <I><B>The Beast </B></I>(Part 1) Coast Guard Lieutenant Kathryn
Marcus (Sillas) authorizes fisherman Whip Dalton (Petersen) and
his partner, Mike (Macer Jr.), to tow in an empty lifeboat drifting
off the coast of Graves Point Island.  A large, sharp claw is
discovered in the raft accompanied by an overwhelming ammonia
scent.  Perplexed and alarmed, the claw is sent to marine biologist
Dr. Herbert Talley (Guttman) for scrutiny. 
<P>
Meanwhile, a number of disturbing events ensue: the steel cables
on the boat of a notorious drunk and poacher, Lucas Coven (Drake),
are neatly severed; the mangled remains of a sperm whale wash
ashore; and two scuba divers disappear without a trace.
<P>
Dr. Talley then identifies the mysterious claw.  It belongs to
an Architeuthis dux -- a sea creature documented as having reached
monstrous proportions.  With its natural food source gone from
the over-fished waters off Graves Point Island, the beast seems
to have found human fare a satisfactory replacement.  In an effort
to preserve the tourist trade, Schuyler Graves (Smith), founder
and landlord of Graves Point, hires Lucas to destroy the beast
any way he must.
<P>
In <I><B>The Beast</B></I> (Part 2) Lucas blows up the 38 foot,
1,000 pound beast.  When Graves denies Dr. Talley permission to
examine the beast for research purposes, Dr. Talley organizes
an excursion to the beast's underwater lair.  While submerged,
a creature triple the size of the beast Lucas killed, attacks
and crushes the sea vessel.  It is clear at that point, that the
attack was one of revenge provoked by the death of one of its
off-spring.
<P>
Again, Graves turns to Lucas for help.  This time, however, Lucas
and his crew, with the exception of Mike, Whip's partner, meet
a gruesome end.   Now, the lives of the townspeople appear to
be in the hands of one man -- Whip Dalton.
<P>
<I><B>The Beast</B></I>, a two-part mini-series, airs <U>Sunday
and Monday, April 28 and 29 at 9:00 p.m. </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>
