<HEAD>

<TITLE>"She Stood Alone: The Tailhook Scandal" on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 3, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;She Stood Alone: The Tailhook Scandal&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
A navy lieutenant, sexually assaulted while attending the 1991
Tailhook Convention, shakes the Navy's very foundation and changes
it forever when she goes public with the disgrace in, <I><B>She
Stood Alone: The Tailhook Scandal</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, April
21, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Gail O'Grady</B> (<I>NYPD Blue</I>), <B>Hal Holbrook, Rip Torn,
Robert Urich, Bess Armstrong, James Marshall, Cameron Bancroft
</B>and<B> Michael Knight </B>star in the two-hour drama based
on a true story.
<P>
In <I><B>She Stood Alone: The Tailhook Scandal</B></I>, Lieutenant
Paula Coughlin (O'Grady) is an individual committed to serving
her country.  While attending the Tailhook Convention in 1991,
she is sexually assaulted.  The incident forces her to change
her focus and &quot;to take a stand to right a wrong.&quot;
<P>
The ordeal is frustrating at best.  When Lieutenant Coughlin submits
her report of the transgression to her boss, Rear Admiral Jack
Snyder (Torn), she receives little acknowledgment of the crime.
 Next, a number of the aviators initially refuse to cooperate
with the investigation.  Then, as the Navy delays in bringing
her attackers to justice, Lieutenant Coughlin feels compelled
to go public with the scandal.
<P>
The dramatization of Lieutenant Coughlin's story is based on interviews,
court documents, official reports and other published accounts.
 A few of the names have been changed and composite characters
introduced.
<P>
<I><B>She Stood Alone: The Tailhook Scandal</B></I> airs <U>Sunday,
April 21, 1996 at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
