<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Moment of Truth: Deceived by Trust" a new drama on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 2, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I>&quot;Moment of Truth: Deceived by Trust&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>


<P>
With unwavering tenacity, a social worker crusades to ensure that
her school's principal is brought to justice for his sexual obsessions
in <I><B>Moment of Truth: Deceived By Trust</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday,
April 14, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Stepfanie Kramer, Michael Gross</B> and <B>Shannon Fill</B>
star.
<P>
In<I><B> Moment of Truth: Deceived by Trust</B></I>, a normally
quiet, reserved student, Cindy Webster, confides in the school's
social worker, Sarah Collins (Kramer), that the principal, Gordon
Powell (Gross), sexually molested her.  When Sarah begins to investigate
the allegations against Powell, she is met with reticence and
fear from teachers, school officials and even Cindy's mother,
who all support the popular and influential Powell.
<P>
Even when Sarah is demoted and transferred to another school,
she refuses to discontinue her campaign.  Putting her own career
at risk to expose Powell's deviate behaviour, she manages to obtain
a closed hearing from the Board of Education.  Sadly, the fragile
Cindy denies her original story giving way to the pressures induced
by her mother and other authority figures.
<P>
A tip then leads Sarah and her attorney friend to two more of
Powell's victims who admit to being abused by Powell, but who
refuse to testify.  In an effort to prevent Powell from being
promoted to Superintendent, Sarah next enlists the help of a newspaper
reporter and  meets a photographer of questionable character who
participated in some of the acts of abuse and, when granted a
lesser sentence in exchange for his testimony, implicates Powell.
 
<P>
Finally, one of the students summons the courage to come forward
to disclose the truth and, at last, following Cindy's attempted
suicide, Cindy's mother accepts the horrific facts.
<P>
<I><B>Moment of Truth: Deceived By Trust </B></I>airs <U>Sunday,
April 14, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
