<HEAD>

<TITLE>The 31st Annual Academy of Country Music Awards on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>April 1, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I>31ST ANNUAL &quot;ACADEMY OF COUNTRY MUSIC AWARDS&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>


<P>
<B>Brooks &amp; Dunn</B> and <B>Faith Hill</B> host the 31st annual
<I><B>Academy of Country Music Awards</B></I>, <I>live</I>, from
the Universal Amphitheatre in California <U>Wednesday, April 24,
1996, (8:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  Portions of
the special, featuring newcomer performances, will originate from
Universal Studios, Hollywood and Florida.
<P>
Awards will be presented to the Top Male Vocalist, Top Female
Vocalist, Top Vocal Duet, Top Vocal Group, Top New Male Vocalist,
Top New Female Vocalist, Top New Vocal Duet or Group, Single Record
of the Year, Song of the Year, Album of the Year, Video of the
Year and Entertainer of the Year.  An outstanding trailblazer
in the field of country music will be presented with the Academy's
Pioneer Award and an individual who attained a prominent achievement
in the field of Country Music during the preceding calendar year
will receive the Special Achievement Award.
<P>
Scheduled to perform are such Country stars as <B>Alabama, John
Anderson, Garth Brooks, Joe Diffie, Alan Jackson, Tracy Lawrence,
Martina McBride, Reba McEntire, Marty Stuart, Travis Tritt, Shania
Twain, Wade Hayes, Lonestar, Perfect Stranger </B>and<B> Bryan
White</B>.
<P>
Among the list of presenters are <B>Loni Anderson, Crystal Bernard,
John Berry, Clint Black, Blackhawk, Linda Davis, Billy Dean, Jeff
Foxworthy, Leeza Gibbons, Naomi Judd, Little Texas, Patty Loveless,
Buck Owens, Sawyer Brown, Pam Tillis, Michelle Wright, Trisha
Yearwood </B>and<B> Dwight Yoakam</B>.<B>  Johnny Cash </B>and<B>
Willie Nelson </B>will make special guest appearances.
<P>
The telecast will also include a one-time-only live performance
of the song &quot;Hope&quot; performed by many of the artists
who recorded the song as their contribution to a musical/charity
project.
<P>
The 31st annual <I><B>Academy of Country Music Awards </B></I>airs
<U>Wednesday, April 24, 1996 at 8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.


