<HEAD>

<TITLE>"My Guys" a new half-hour comedy series on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 28, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1>&quot;MY GUYS&quot;</H1>
<H3>A New Half-Hour Comedy Series</H3>
<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>
</CENTER>


<P>
A recent widower tries to run a fledgling limousine service while
coping with the uncertainties of raising two sons (aged 15 and
12) in the new comedy series, <I><B>My Guys</B></I>, premiering
<U>Wednesday, April 17, 1996, (8:30 - 9:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
The show stars <B>Michael Rispoli</B> (<I>While You were Sleeping,
To Die For, Above the Rim, Household Saints</I>; television's
<I>The Great Defender</I>), <B>Mike Damus</B> (<I>Lost In Yonkers</I>),
<B>Francis Capra</B> (<I>A Bronx Tale, Free Willy 2, Kazaam</I>)
and <B>Sherie Scott</B> (<I>The Cosby Mysteries</I>).
<P>
Set in Manhattan's not-so-stylish Upper West Side, <I><B>My Guys</B></I>
tells the story of Sonny Demarco (Rispoli), a widower in recent
times and father of two.  His eldest is 15-year-old Michael (Damus)
who has just discovered girls, in particular, the 17-year-old
beauty next door.  Then there is 12-year-old Francis (Capra),
a sagacious youth besieged with allergies to just about everything.

<P>
When bewildered by the mysteries of raising children, Sonny turns
to Dori (Scott), an aspiring actress who, between parts, waits
tables at the local diner.
<P>
<I><B>My Guys</B></I> premieres <U>Wednesday, April 17, 1996,
at 8:30 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>
<I>Please note</I>: <I>The Faculty</I> will move to the 8:00 p.m.
timeslot on Wednesdays, effective April 17, 1996 (pre-release/ABC).



