<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Deadly Web", a movie thriller on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 28, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Deadly Web&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>a movie thriller on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
A woman's Internet friend becomes her stalker, invading every
area of her life until she is finally forced to confront him in
a terrifying struggle to save her life and the life of her son
in <I><B>Deadly Web</B></I>, airing <U>Monday, April 15, 1996
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
Based on a true story, the two-hour television movie stars <B>Gigi
Rice,</B> <B>Ed Marinaro, John Wesley Shipp</B> and <B>Andrew
Lawrence</B>.
<P>
In <I><B>Deadly Web</B></I>, all seems to be going well for the
recently separated Terri Lawrence (Rice) who is trying to make
a new life for herself and her son, Spence (Lawrence).  She has
a job at a hospital library and both have made friends over the
Internet -- Spence has met &quot;CeeGee&quot; and Terri, &quot;Cybergod,&quot;
who eventually turns into a stalker, aware of every detail of
Terri's life.
<P>
The annoyance turns into terror when a doctor is killed.  Terri
becomes suspect of three of her colleagues: Barry Fox, a computer
whiz; Laura Pierson, who would like to see Terri gone; and Dr.
Todd Stanton (Shipp), whose flirtatious nature makes her feel
ill at ease.  As a result, Terri thinks she can trust no one,
not even Frank Jones (Marinaro), a former police officer, who
claims he has been following the stalker for years and knows &quot;Cybergod&quot;
has harmed others, including his former partner.
<P>
The terror accelerates when Spence's school computer is accessed
and the child's birth certificate appears on the screen revealing
the true identity of his biological father.  The act sends the
traumatized boy running out onto the street and into the path
of an oncoming car.   When Barry Fox is accidentally killed, some
of Terri's anxiety is lessened as she hoped he was &quot;Cybergod.&quot;
  The comfort, however, is short-lived as it becomes evident that
Dr. Todd Stanton is the one who has devised a complex plan that
results in Terri, Spence and Frank fighting for their lives.
<P>
A friendly computer game, <I><B>Deadly Web</B></I>, lives up to
its name in the movie by the same name airing <U>Monday, April
15, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.


