<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Face of Evil," a thriller on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 20, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Face of Evil&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>


<P>
Murder, treachery and seduction are tools used by an impenitent
young woman in order to achieve her artistic goals in, <I><B>Face
of Evil</B></I> airing <U>Tuesday, April 9, 1996, (9:00 -11:00
p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Tracey Gold</B> and <B>Perry King</B> star.
<P>
In <I><B>Face of Evil</B></I>, we meet Darcy Palmer (Gold), who,
on her wedding night, empties her new husband's bank account and
flees to New York City to pursue a career as an artist.  On her
way, she meets Brianne Dwyer, a youth just off to college, whom
she kills and then assumes her identity.
<P>
Darcy (now known as Brianne) thrives at college and flourishes
as a painter, marred only by having to blind a counselor who had
previously met the real Brianne.  Her roommate is 19-year-old
Jeanelle, the daughter of a recently widowed, wealthy gentleman,
Russel (King).  Brianne's character softens when she meets Russel
at Thanksgiving, making him realize how his destructive behaviour,
caused by alcohol, affects Jeanelle.  Consequently, he stops drinking
and revives the loving, generous nature he possessed prior to
his wife's death.  
<P>
Soon after, however, Brianne resumes her trail of evil as she:
poisons Jeanelle when Russel comes to visit the campus, making
her too ill to spend time with him -- so Brianne can; murders
her ex-fiancee who shows up at her art exhibit; lies to the real
Brianne's parents by telling them that Brianne wanted to abandon
them, and it was she who suggested Darcy take her place.  When
Darcy is expelled from school, she moves in with Russel and seduces
him.  And, finally, Darcy attempts to kill Jeanelle who has become
suspect of her.  
<P>
In the end, Darcy discloses that she may not really be Darcy,
but rather another victim's identity she has assumed.  <I><B>Face
of Evil </B></I>airs <U>Tuesday, April 9, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.     


<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
