<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Her Last Chance", the story of a troubled teen, on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 18, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Her Last Chance&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
A troubled teen, with a past history of drug and alcohol problems,
is wrongly accused of the murder of her boyfriend.  With the help
of her mother, she fights to stay straight and prove her innocence
in, <I><B>Her Last Chance</B></I>, airing <U>Monday, April 8,
1996, (9:00 -11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
Award-winning actresses<B> Kellie Martin</B> (<I>Christy</I>)
and <B>Patti LuPone</B> (<I>Life Goes On</I>) who portrayed mother
and daughter for four years in the television series <I>Life Goes
On</I>, reunite to again assume the roles of mother and daughter.
 Also starring are <B>Jonathan Brandis</B> (<I>seaQuest 2032</I>)
and <B>Tony Lucca </B>(<I>Malibu Shores</I>).
<P>
In <I><B>Her Last Chance</B></I>, Alex Saxen (Martin) is a confused
teenager who has battled drug and alcohol problems and is currently
struggling to stay straight.  Her strength is truly tested, however,
when following her second visit to a rehab facility, she is accused
of murdering her boyfriend, Preston (Brandis).
<P>
One person resolved to prove Alex innocent of the crime and keep
her from turning to old habits during the intense process is her
widowed mother, Joanna Saxen (LuPone). 
<P>
<I><B>Her Last Chance </B></I>airs <U>Monday, April 8, 1996, at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.

