<HEAD>

<TITLE>Dan McLean receives the Howard Caine Public Service Award
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 11, 1996</B></I></H2>

<CENTER>
<H1>CHCH-TV's Dan McLean Recipient of</H1>

<H2>The Howard Caine &quot;Public Service&quot; Memorial Award
</H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
CHCH-TV is proud to announce that news anchor <B>Dan McLean </B>was
this year's recipient of <B>The Howard Caine &quot;Public Service&quot;
Memorial Award</B>. The award was presented to <B>Mr. McLean </B>Friday
evening, March 8, 1996, by the <B>Ontario Association of Broadcasters</B>.
<P>
<B>The Howard Caine Award </B>is named after the President and
Founder of CHWO Radio in Oakville, and a past president of the
Central Canada Broadcasters' Association. It is presented each
year to a broadcaster in the Ontario region who has most closely
emulated the late Howard Caine by making significant contributions
to the community.
<P>
In his 23 years at CHCH-TV, <B>Dan McLean</B> has not only become
one of the most respected anchors in the southern Ontario broadcast
market, but has also gained recognition as a dynamic leader and
volunteer within the community. Among his numerous on-going commitments
outside the newsroom, Dan has served as the first Honourary Chairman
for Year of the Child, Honourary Chairman for the Hamilton-Wentworth
Kidney Foundation, Honouary Chairman for the Red Cross Side By
Side Fundraising Campaign and, most recently, the 1995 Campaign
Chairman for the United Way of Burlington, Hamilton-Wentworth.
We are pleased to report that the United Way exceeded its goal
of $6.3 million. 
<P>
We congratulate Dan McLean for the distinction he has received
from the Ontario Association of Broadcasters and his dedication
to the area's non-profit organizations.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
