<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Never Give Up: The Jimmy V Story" on CHCH-TV</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 11, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Never Give Up: The Jimmy V Story&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
Based on actual events, <I><B>Never Give Up: The Jimmy V Story</B></I>
is about coach Jim Valvano, a genial, inspirational man who left
behind a legacy in the world of basketball and who, more importantly,
touched people's lives.  It airs <U>Tuesday, April 2, 1996, (9:00
-11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Anthony LaPaglia, Ashley Crow, Lou Criscoulo, Blair Struble,
Wendy Hoopes </B>and <B>Ronny Cox </B>star.
<P>
In <I><B>Never Give Up: The Jimmy V Story</B></I>, Jim Valvano
(LaPaglia) starts out living the life he planned back in high
school when he, himself, was a star basketball player: he settles
down with his high school sweetheart, Pam Levine (Crow) and becomes
a coach.  What his plan does not include is the trouble he will
encounter in his career, his marriage and ultimately his health.
<P>
Liked by everyone, Valvano's special gift is coaching, which is
never more evident than in his locker room talks, in particular,
the speech he gives to the North Carolina State Wolfpack when
he leads them to victory during the 1983 NCAA Championships.
<P>
However, &quot;Coach V&quot; eventually starts to experience a
few problems in his life.  The strain of his absence from home
impacts on his marriage.  Following an NCAA investigation, which
finds him guilty of minor infractions, Valvano is fired.  Before
long, he is hired to be a sports commentator on ESPN only to be
diagnosed with cancer shortly thereafter.  
<P>
Determined to live life to the fullest until the end, Valvano
learns to paint, golfs and does another ESPN show.  He also forms
the V-Foundation, an organization dedicated to cancer research.
 
<P>
Shortly before his death, he is honoured by the Wolfpack Club
at the 10-year reunion of the championship team where he delivers
a speech that brings everyone to their feet.   <I><B>Never Give
Up: The Jimmy V Story</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, April 2, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
