<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Nash Bridges", a new action-drama series premiering on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../images/release1.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER>
<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT><I><B>March 6, 1996</B></I></H2> 

<CENTER>
<H1><I> &quot;Nash Bridges&quot;</I></H1>
<H1>premieres on CHCH-TV</H1>
</CENTER>


<P>
<I><B>Nash Bridges</B></I>, the new action drama series about
a San Francisco PD inspector, nonpareil in his profession, but
lacking in his personal life (e.g. two ex-wives, two sets of alimony
payments), premieres <U>Friday, March 29, 1996, (9:00 - 10:00
p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Don Johnson</B> (<I>Miami Vice</I>), <B>Cary Hiroyuki Tagawa,
Annette O'Toole, Serena Scott Thomas, Jeff Perry, Jamie Gomez
</B>and<B> Jodi Lynn O'Keefe</B> star along with <B>Cheech Marin</B>
who appears in a recurring role.
<P>
As <I><B>Nash Bridges</B></I>, Johnson is the lead member of the
elite &quot;Special Investigators Bureau&quot; with the San Francisco
Police Department.  He is one of the best, possessing singular
instincts, a good sense of humour and a certain charm.
<P>
From time to time he finds himself working along side his wisecracking
ex-partner, Joe Dominguez (Marin), who left the force for an easier
life as a private investigator.  Yet, somehow he manages to get
himself wrapped up in Nash's cases.
<P>
In his personal life, Nash does not enjoy the same &quot;top notch&quot;
reputation he relishes professionally, as he struggles with the
responsibilities of a delicate balancing act -- two ex-wives and
an inquisitive 16-year-old daughter.
<P>
Don Johnson, Carlton Cuse (<I>Adventures of Brisco County, Jr</I>.)
and John Nicolella (<I>Miami Vice</I>) are executive producers
of the series. 
<P>
<I><B>Nash Bridges </B></I>premieres <U>Friday, March 29, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, one-hour pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.


