<HEAD>

<TITLE>"My Very Best Friend" a new television movie on CHCH-TV
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: March
4, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;My Very Best Friend &quot;</I></H1>

<H2>A New Motion Picture-for-Television on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
In a tale of envy, deceit and murder, a woman reveals to a lifelong
friend how she is capable of committing a deadly act in order
maintain a certain way of life in, <I><B>My Very Best Friend</B></I>,
airing <U>Wednesday, March 27, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Jaclyn Smith, Jill Eikenberry, Mary Kay Place, Tom Irwin</B>,
and <B>Tom Mason</B> star in the two-hour production shot in Vancouver.
<P>
<I><B>My Very Best Friend</B></I> focuses on two women, friends
since the age of 13.  Dana Griffin (Smith) is a beautiful, high-fashion
model whose success has always stood in the way of  marriage and
starting a family.  On the other hand, her childhood friend, Barbara
Wilkins (Eikenberry), has enjoyed a conventional life in New Hampshire
with her husband Alex (Irwin) and their 11-year-old daughter.
<P>
When Dana announces she is marrying wealthy executive Ted Marshall
(Mason), the Wilkinses fly to San Francisco for the happy occasion.
 However, within days of the ceremony, Ted drowns after falling
off his yacht.
<P>
Following the tragedy, a grieving Dana moves in with her best
friend and family.  It is then she discloses to Barbara that she
likens herself to a predator -- a woman wont to having things
her own way and capable of murder in order to preserve her standard
of living.     
<P>
Barbara may have been fooled, but, another lifelong acquaintance
is not deceived by Dana's refined guise.  <I><B>My Very Best Friend</B></I>
airs <U>Wednesday, March 27, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>CBS</B>. 
<P>

