<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Leaving Normal" on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: March
4, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;Leaving Normal&quot;</I></H1>

<H2>A Theatrical Motion Picture on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A chance encounter between two women, completely opposite in character,
travel together to Alaska in search of a new life in, <I><B>Leaving
Normal</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, March 17, 1996, (9:00 - 11:15
p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Christine Lahti</B> (<I>Chicago Hope, Just Between Friends,
Amerika, Running on Empty, Gross Anatomy, Crazy From the Heart,
The Doctor</I>) and <B>Meg Tilly</B> (<I>The Big Chill, Psycho
II, Agnes of God</I>) star in the theatrical production. Also
appearing are<B> Lenny Von Dohlen, Maury Chaykin, Patrika Darbo,
Eve Gordon, James Eckhouse, Brett Cullen </B>and<B> James Gammon</B>.
<P>
In <I><B>Leaving Normal</B></I>, a young battered wife, Marianne
Johnson (Tilly), has just run out on her second failed marriage.
Remarkably, the experience has left her optimism intact, but with
nowhere to go in small town Normal, Wyoming.
<P>
A chance meeting hooks her up with Darly Peters (Lahti), a feisty,
cynical cocktail waitress. Subsequently, both decide to leave
Normal and head for Alaska, where each can begin a new life.
<P>
<I><B>Leaving Normal</B></I>, directed by Edward Zwick, airs <U>Sunday,
March 17, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

