<HEAD>

<TITLE>"A Mother's Instinct" a story of betrayal and triumph on CHCH-TV
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
27, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;A Mother's Instinct&quot;</I></H1>

<H2>A Story of Betrayal and Triumph on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
Two women, who discover they are married to the same man, try
to rebuild their lives while searching for the children he has
abducted in, <I><B>A Mother's Instinct</B></I>, a new television
drama based on actual facts and airing <U>Tuesday, March 12, 1996,
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Emmy Award winner <B>Lindsay Wagner </B>(<I>The Bionic Woman,
Jesse, Scruples, Nurses on the Line: The Crash of Flight 7, Fire
in the Dark, The Incredible Journey of Meg Laurel, Sins of Silence</I>)
and<B> Debrah Farentino </B>(<I>NYPD Blue, The Garry Shandling
Show, Earth 2, McBride and Groom, Equal Justice, Hooperman, Deadly
Games, Back on the Streets of San Francisco</I>) star along with
another Emmy Award winner <B>Barbara Babcock</B> (<I>Hill Street
Blues, The Law and Harry McGraw, The Four Seasons, Stranger in
the House, News at Eleven, Dr. Quinn Medicine Woman</I>).  <B>
John Terry</B> and <B>Alana Austin</B> also appear.
<P>
In <I><B>A Mother's Instinct</B></I>, Holly (Farentino), a divorced
mother who has recently married a widower with two sons, learns
that her new husband, Carl (Terry), is not the man she thought
he was.   When her suspicions grow over the many discrepancies
in his stories about his past, Carl disappears with his children.
<P>
Holly's ensuing investigation directs her to Carl's first wife,
Raeanne (Wagner), who tells Holly that Carl abducted his own sons
after losing custody of them and for the last six years, she has
been trying to find.   Furthermore, Carl is still legally married
to Raeanne.            
<P>
The two women form a strong bond and commit to finding the boys
together.  Their all-consuming search leads them to even more
shocking revelations, among them: Carl has obtained legal papers
proving he has custody of the children and he is about to settle
down with yet another woman.  However, in the final anxious moments,
Holly and Raeanne devise a plan to outwit Carl.  
<P>
<I><B>A Mother's Instinct</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, March 12, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, one day pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

