<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Race Against Time: The Search for Sarah" on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
26, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;Race Against Time: The Search for Sarah&quot;</I>
</H1>

<H2>A New Motion Picture -for-Television on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
Unyielding in their pursuit to find their missing daughter, ordinary
parents take extraordinary steps in, <I><B>Race Against Time:
The Search for Sarah</B></I>, a drama inspired by actual events
and airing <U>Tuesday, March 19, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Emmy Award winner <B>Patty Duke</B> (<I>My Sweet Charlie, The
Captains and the Kings, The Miracle Worker, Call Me Anna</I>)
and <B>Richard Crenna</B> (<I>First Blood, Rambo, Rambo III, Table
for Five, Sweet Ginger Brown</I>, and <I>Janek</I> TV film series)
reunite to star in this production after having worked together
in <I>It Takes Two</I>. 
<P>
In <I><B>Race Against Time: The Search for Sarah</B></I>, Sarah
Porter fails to show up at a special function honouring her father,
John (Crenna).   At first, her family is annoyed and wearied at
what appears to be typical behaviour for Sarah.  However, Sarah's
mother, Natalie (Duke), is convinced something is horribly wrong.
 Her instincts are right, for Sarah has been carjacked by acquaintances
and her beaten body discarded near a ravine.   
<P>
  
<P>
When the Porters first report Sarah's disappearance to the police,
they do nothing because of Sarah's past behaviour -- she has run
away from home once before.  Furthermore, when Sarah's car is
stopped, the officer wrongly assumes the woman in the back seat
is Sarah and neglects to ask for identification. 
<P>
Frustrated and fearful, the entire Porter family bands together
to find Sarah.  They distribute flyers with Sarah's photo on them
and even track down the officer who supposedly identified Sarah.
  Following a phone tip that details Sarah's fate, John, who has
subsequently suffered a mild heart attack due to the agonizing
ordeal, sneaks out of the hospital to confront the people who
have kidnapped his daughter.
<P>
Eventually, Sarah is found -- near dead and almost buried at the
bottom of a ravine.
<P>
<I><B>Race Against Time: The Search for Sarah</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday,
March 19, 1996, at 9:00 p.m. </U>on<B> CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
