<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Radiant City", a nostalgic family drama on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
20, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;Radiant City&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>A NOSTALGIC FAMILY DRAMA ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
Exasperated with living in a low-class Brooklyn housing project,
a 1950s housewife secretly finds a job so she, her husband, and
two children can enjoy a better life far away from the confines
of <I><B>Radiant City</B></I>, a new television movie airing <U>Sunday,
March 31, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Kirstie Alley</B> (<I>Cheers, Look Who's Talking</I>), <B>Clancy
Brown</B> (<I>The Shawshank Redemption</I>), <B>Tori McPetrie
</B>(<I>The Silence of Adultery</I>), <B>Adam Lamberg, Fab Filippo</B>
and <B>Gil Bellows</B> star.     
<P>
Set in 1950s Brooklyn, New York, <I><B>Radiant City</B></I> centres
around the Goodman family: Gloria (Alley), a middle-aged housewife
who yearns to move away from the Radiant City housing project;
her husband Al (Brown), a poorly paid post office worker who must
remain below a certain income level in order to stay in Radiant
City; Stewie (Lamberg) their impish 10-year-old; and Sherry (McPetrie),
their love-sick, sweet 16-year-old. 
<P>
Frustrated with contending with gossipy women, a flirtatious neighbour
named Bert (Bellows) and a policeman's harsh treatment of her
son's mischievous behaviour, Gloria decides to look for a job.
 Posing as an educated, single woman, she secures a position as
a cosmetics salesperson at Macy's department store.  Secretly,
she starts to save for a house, otherwise the family could be
ejected before Gloria has saved enough.  But, when Stewie follows
her to work one day, the word gets out.
<P>
When Al bemoans the fact he is unable to provide for a richer
life, Gloria convinces him to stop gambling on horses and gamble
instead on life.  Before the housing authority can evict the Goodman
family, they proudly announce they are buying a home in New Jersey.
<P>
In the end, Al finds a better job at the post office, Gloria keeps
hers and Sherry and Stewie regret leaving the familiarity of <I><B>Radiant
City</B></I>, a sentimental drama airing <U>Sunday, March 31,
1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

