<HEAD>

<TITLE>"In The Lake of the Woods", a compelling drama on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
19, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;In the Lake of the Woods&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>A COMPELLING NEW DRAMA ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
A senatorial candidate, suffering a devastating defeat, retreats
to a lakeside cottage with his wife.  When his wife vanishes without
a trace, suspicions arise.  It is only when the search for her
body is terminated that the horrifying truth of her death is revealed.
 <I><B>In The Lake of the Woods</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, March
5, 1996, (8:00 - 10:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
<B>Peter Strauss</B> and <B>Kathleen Quinlan</B> star in the two-hour
production.
<P>
<I><B>In The Lake of the Woods</B></I> is about John Waylan, a
senatorial candidate on the brink of achieving great things until
details of a past Vietnam tragedy are disclosed by the press.
 His political career in ruins, he and his wife, Kathy, seek refuge
at a remote lakeside cottage.
<P>
One morning, John awakens to find his wife has vanished without
a trace.  During the search for the missing woman, suspicions
are aroused as to her true fate.  Through  flashbacks, viewers
learn of John's troubled childhood, his real role in the Vietnam
war, and of the severe cracks in his marriage.
<P>
As the search proceeds over a period of weeks, various scenarios
of Kathy's fate are presented -- each one probable, and each more
puzzling than the previous.  When the search is called off and
a body not found, John is left alone with his memories.  It is
then that the truth of Kathy's death is brought to light.
<P>
<I><B>In the Lake of the Woods</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, March
5, 1996, at 8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>Fox</B>.
<P>

