<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Special Report" Journey to Mars", a special movie presentation.
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
19, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I> &quot;Special Report: Journey to Mars&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>A NEW MOTION PICTURE-FOR-TELEVISION ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
The whole world is watching as the first human attempt to land
on Mars is hours away from success.  Suddenly, sabotage causes
the spaceship's computer systems to malfunction.  With their lives
and enormous consequences for the world at stake, a brave crew
of astronauts race against time to save themselves and their mission.
 <I><B>Special Report: Journey to Mars</B></I> airs <U>Monday,
March 25, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  
<P>
<B>Judge Reinhold, Alfre Woodard, Keith Carradine, Philip Casnoff,
Rosalind Chao, Dean Jones, Diane Venora </B>and<B> Elizabeth Wilson</B>
star.
<P>
In <I><B>Special Report: Journey To Mars</B></I> over three billion
viewers have been watching a remarkable group of people who, for
the last seven months, have been travelling to Mars aboard the
spaceship Destiny.  Now, touchdown is hours away and Global News
Network anchors Tamara O'Neil (Woodard) and Jeff Van Pelt (Casnoff)
are receiving on-site coverage from astro-journalist Ryan West
(Reinhold) who is aboard Destiny.
<P>
As Destiny enters final descent there is a computer malfunction.
 The situation is further complicated when Captain Eugene Slader
(Carradine) falls victim to a mysterious illness affecting his
motor and reasoning skills.  While Dr. Lin Yo Yu fights to save
Slader's life, Lieutenant Tanya Sadavoy (Venora) takes over the
controls.  Then, GNN's satellite feed is interrupted by an anonymous
source claiming responsibility for sabotaging the mission in the
name of Native Earth Alliance, a group determined to end interplanetary
exploration.
<P>
As the world awaits the reaction of Madam President Richardson
(Wilson), whose political career depends upon the success of the
mission, an extraordinary crew of astronauts race against time
to save themselves and the Mars excursion.  
<P>
<I><B>Special Report: Journey to Mars</B></I> airs <U>Monday,
March 25, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

