<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Greatest Shows You Never Saw", a CHCH Special Presentation.
</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
19, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;The Greatest Shows You Never Saw&quot;</I></H1>

<H2>a CHCH-TV Special Presentation</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
Many well-known performers turn up in some of the most hilarious
scenes from television series that never made it to air in <I><B>The
Greatest Shows You Never Saw</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, March
3, 1996, (7:00 - 8:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Faith Ford</B> of <I>Murphy Brown</I> fame hosts the special
filled with a treasure of memorable moments.
<P>
<I><B>The Greatest Shows You Never Saw</B></I> features a selection
of off-centre, delightfully funny scenes from television pilots
that were produced, but never broadcast, as well as a host of
famous performers that appeared in them.
<P>
The popular list of stars includes <B>Danny Aiello</B> in <I>Car
Wash</I>, <B>Louis Gossett Jr.</B> in <I>Fuzz Brothers</I>, <B>Bette
Davis</B> in <B>Madame Sin</B> and <B>Leonard Nimoy</B> in <I>Baffled</I>.
Appearing in roles early in their careers are such actors as <B>Joey
Lawrence, Teri Garr, Bob Denver</B> and <B>Sarah Jessica Parker</B>.
<P>
Other pilots that never made it to the television screen include
<I>The Clumbsys</I>, a show about a clumsy family; <I>Crossroad
Avenger</I> directed by Ed Wood;<I> Shangri-La Plaza</I>, a musical
set in a strip mall. Audiences will also enjoy seeing a pilot
about crime fighting antique dealers starring <B>Vincent Price</B>
and <B>Peter Lorre</B>. 
<P>
In addition, the special showcases the first episodes of TV classics
like <I>The Flintstones</I>, originally titled <I>The Flagstones</I>;
<I>The Wonderful World of Wilbur Pope</I>, which was re-titled
<I>Mr. Ed</I>, and the colour pilot of <I>The Munsters</I>.
<P>
<I><B>The Greatest Shows You Never Saw </B></I>airs <U>Sunday,
March 3, 1996, at 7:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

