<HEAD>

<TITLE>CRTC Confirms Hearing of CHCH-TV Expansion Applications
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
16, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CRTC Confirms Hearing of CHCH-TV Ottawa</I></H2>

<H2><I>and Ontario Expansion Applications</I> </H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
The Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission
(CRTC) has confirmed today that it will hear <B>CHCH-TV</B>'s
Ottawa and Ontario expansion applications in April, 1996.  
<P>
The Ontario expansion applications filed seek amendments to <B>CHCH-TV</B>'s
broadcast license which would allow rebroadcast transmitters to
be established in nine Ontario markets: London, Kingston, Peterborough,
Muskoka, North Bay, Sudbury, Sault Ste. Marie, Timmins, and Thunder
Bay.  
<P>
The <B>CHCH</B> program schedule will provide these communities
with a significant amount of new programming options.  While <B>CHCH</B>
is available in a few of the markets on cable, on average 60%
of the programs in the <B>CHCH</B> schedule are not seen in the
nine markets the station proposes to serve.
<P>
Originally, <B>CHCH </B>filed a programming undertaking application
for Ottawa which would provide local newscasts to the city and
area.  Subsequently, the station also filed a straight rebroadcast
application.  Following the CRTC's decision to hear only one application
and responding to the Commission's concern about the Ottawa economy,
<B>CHCH</B> withdrew its original Ottawa application for a programming
undertaking.
<P>
&quot;The choice was difficult,&quot; expresses Jim Macdonald,
president and chief executive officer, <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  &quot;However,
we chose to go forward with a rebroadcast model for Ottawa as
it would be consistent with our rebroad approach in the other
nine Ontario markets.  Furthermore, we are delighted with the
Commission's quick response, and that all of our applications
will be heard concurrently.&quot; 
<P>
<B>CHCH</B> is owned by <B>WIC Western International Communications
Ltd</B>., and is a subsidiary of <B>Westcom TV Group Ltd</B>.
 <B>WIC</B> is an integrated Canadian communications, broadcast
and entertainment company with its head office in Vancouver, British
Columbia.  <B>WIC</B> is the only Canadian broadcasting company
operating in television, pay television, radio and satellite network
services.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR>
| <A HREF="../../prog/prog.htm">Return To The Programming Page</A>
| <A HREF="../../default.htm">Return To The CHCH Home Page</A>
