<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Stranger Beside Me", a thriller on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
14, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;The Stranger Beside Me&quot;</I></H1>

<H1><I>a thriller on CHCH-TV</I></H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
When a woman discovers that her husband is a rapist and that he
could potentially harm their daughter, she makes a desperate move
to prove his guilt in <I><B>The Stranger Beside Me</B></I>, airing
<U>Tuesday, February 27, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
 
<P>
<B>Tiffani-Amber Thiessen, Eric Close</B> and <B>Casey Sander</B>
star.
<P>
In <I><B>The Stranger Beside Me</B></I>, shy Jennifer Moore, a
recent transplant to Albuquerque, is swept off her feet in a whirlwind
romance by the outgoing Chris Gallagher.  Before long, they are
married and on their way to San Diego where Chris commences his
Navy career.
<P>
After the move, Chris suddenly becomes distant and passionless.
 He experiences claustrophobia, making his submarine assignment
difficult.  To cope, he starts running at night, which makes Jennifer
most uneasy as the base is plagued by a peeper.  When a woman
is actually raped, Jennifer's fears mount.  
<P>
Following Chris's arrest for voyeurism and rape, a pregnant Jennifer
wants desperately to believe in her husband's innocence.  That
belief is tested when he pleads guilty to the peeping charge,
but not the rape charge.  In the end, the latter charge is dropped
due to insufficient evidence.  Sent back to Albuquerque with a
dishonourable discharge, Chris begs Jennifer to give him another
chance.  But, before long, he starts going out at night again
and the night Jennifer goes into labour, a woman is raped.   
 
<P>
When Chris's sister reveals she was molested by her brother for
years, Jennifer calls the police who choose to protect their hometown
buddy.  After Chris threatens to harm their daughter if Jennifer
tries to leave, Jennifer takes action.   Frantic to prove her
husband's guilt, she trails him to the next victim's house.  As
he breaks in, Jennifer calls the police who arrive in time to
arrest him.  Chris is ultimately sentenced to 99 years in prison.
<P>
<I><B>The Stranger Beside Me</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, February
27, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR>
