<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH has "The Good Doctor: The Paul Fleiss Story"</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
13, 1996</B></I> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<H2><I>CHCH-TV has</I></H2>

<H1><I>The Good Doctor: The Paul Fleiss Story</I></H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
The dynamics of a family who has among its members an esteemed
pediatrician and an infamous daughter -- Hollywood Madam, Heidi
Fleiss -- are explored in <I><B>The Good Doctor: The Paul Fleiss
Story</B></I>, airing <U>Monday, February 19, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00
p.m.) </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Starring are <B>Michael Gross, Tricia Leigh Fisher, George Segal,
Lois Nettleton, Cindy Pickett, Jennifer Crystal </B>and<B> Mick
Cain.</B>
<P>
<I><B>The Good Doctor: The Paul Fleiss Story</B></I>, chronicles
the conflict between a father's (Gross) power and the integrity
of his child (Fisher). It illustrates how a sixties-based child-rearing
philosophy of love and acceptance clashes with the carnality and
baseness of the excessive eighties. 
<P>
The highly publicized results are played out in Los Angeles courtrooms
as everyone's favourite baby doctor and perfect father is sentenced
to three years probation for conspiring to hide his daughter's
call girl ring profits.
<P>
<I><B>The Good Doctor: The Paul Fleiss Story</B></I> airs <U>Monday,
February 19, 1996, at 9:00 p.m. </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

