<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Wizard of Oz on Ice", a skating special on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
12, 1996</B></I> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<H1><I>&quot;The Wizard of Oz on Ice&quot;</I></H1>

<H2>A New Skating Special on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
The classic tale of Dorothy's journey to Oz is told through the
grace and dynamism of figure skating in <I><B>The Wizard of Oz
on Ice</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday, February 27, 1996, (8:00 -
9:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. 
<P>
Olympic gold medalists <B>Oksana Baiul</B> and <B>Viktor Petrenko</B>
star in the special.  Host, Grammy Award winner <B>Bobby McFerrin</B>,
provides 53 singing and speaking voices, while new musical sensation
<B>Brandy</B>, sings &quot;Over the Rainbow.&quot;
<P>
<I><B>The Wizard of Oz on Ice</B></I>, brings to life the timeless
1939 movie <I>The Wizard of Oz</I>.  In the role of Dorothy, Baiul
sets down in the magical land of Oz where she makes new friends,
among them the Scarecrow (Petrenko), the Tinman and the Cowardly
Lion, and embarks on an extraordinary journey. 
<P>
Included in the presentation is a Jitterbug sequence, a sequence
which was created for, but never included in, the original film.
 Canadian world champion pair skaters <B>Paul Martini</B> and
<B>Barbara Underhill </B>play the Jitterbugs -- a couple of scary
pests who dance in the haunted forest.  
<P>
<I><B>The Wizard of Oz on Ice</B></I>, based on the touring production
by the same name, and currently travelling to more than 80 American
cities and 32 nations, airs <U>Tuesday, February 27, 1996, at
8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

