<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Faculty", a new comedy series on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: February
5, 1996</B></I> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<H2>CHCH-TV has</H2>

<H1><I>&quot;The Faculty&quot;</I></H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
What really goes on inside the faculty lounge of a contemporary
junior high school?  Get a witty, insightful look when the new
comedy series, <I><B>The Faculty</B></I>, premieres <U>Wednesday,
March 13, 1996, (8:30 - 9:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Meredith Baxter, Peter Michael Goetz, Constance Shulman, Peter
MacKenzie, Jenica Bergere, Nancy Lenehan</B> and <B>Kurt Fuller
</B>star.
<P>
In <I><B>The Faculty</B></I>, it is a triple toss up for assistant
vice principal Flynn Sullivan (Baxter) to determine which is more
difficult -- keeping her personal life afloat; dealing with her
malcontent, decidedly amusing teaching staff; or trying to inspire
the dispassionate students at Hamilton Middle School.
<P>
Helping Flynn face burnout, budget cuts, and discipline problems
are an off-centre group of co-workers including her best friend
Shelly (Shulman), an acerbic English teacher; Herb (Goetz), the
perpetually preoccupied principal; Herb's caustic and territorial
secretary, Daisy (Lenehan); a rookie teacher, Amanda (Bergere);
and Clark (MacKenzie), a conventional, buttoned-down history teacher
yearning to break out of his shell.   
<P>
 
<P>
There are days when Flynn Sullivan would rather turn her back
and walk away from her job, but her idealism always triumphs.
<P>
<I><B>The Faculty</B></I>, premieres <U>Wednesday, March 13, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

