<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Spanking Your Kids" generates over 50,000 calls on Jane Hawtin 
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../images/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
31, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>Show Topic <I>'SPANKING YOUR KIDS'</I> </H1>

<H2>Generates over 50,000 calls on<I> JANE HAWTIN LIVE! </I></H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
&quot;Spanking Your Kids&quot; was the topic discussed today,
January 31, 1996, on <I><B>Jane Hawtin Live!   </B></I>The controversial
theme struck a strong chord with viewers as the number of calls
generated totaled <B>50,648</B>.  Jane's guests on the show were
Kari Simpson from the Citizen's Research Institute (pro spanking)
and child psychologist Dr. David Day (against).
<P>
While this tally is the highest generated to date for a single
Jane Hawtin Live! show, the program is becoming accustomed to
generating large numbers of telephone calls.  For example, on
December 5, 1995, close to 41,000 people tried to call into Jane
Hawtin Live! to express their opinion on the topic of Legalizing
Marijuana.   Jane Hawtin Live!, which debuted August 28, 1995,
usually averages over 40,000 call attempts a week.  In less than
five months over 900,000 people have called 1-800-510-JANE. 
<P>
Show topics that have each received over 20,000 call attempts
or more include:
<UL>
<LI>Did Karla Homolka Get Away With Murder?
<LI>Capital Punishment
<LI>Lap Dancing
<LI>Abortion
<LI>Smoking -- Should Nicotine Be A Controlled Substance?
<LI>Gun Control
<LI>Quebec Referendum Day
<LI>Are Men Getting A Bad Rap
<LI>Day After Referendum -- Oui or Non
<LI>Schools Teaching About Gays and Lesbians 
</UL>

<P>

<P>
Due to the overwhelming response on the 1-800 number, <I><B>Jane
Hawtin Live! </B></I>launched a 900 Poll Line on October 30, 1995.
 The <I>Yes/No Poll(</I>conducted two - three times a week),<I>
</I>provides immediate results allowing viewers to know at the
conclusion of the show, exactly where people have positioned themselves
on a given topic.  In addition, Friday's, <I><B>Jane Hawtin Live!
</B></I>features the<I><B> </B></I>best phone calls of the week,
the best letter and the best Internet mail message.
<P>
<I><B>Jane Hawtin Live!,</B></I> a co-production of <B>Westcom
TV Group Ltd. </B>and <B>Jane Hawtin Live Productions</B>, is
seen 1:00 - 2:00 p.m. on <B>CHCH-TV</B> in the Toronto market
and is simulcast with <B>Talk 640, BCTV</B> in Vancouver, <B>ITV</B>
in Edmonton, <B>CICT</B> in Calgary and on <B>2&amp;7 CISA</B>
in Lethbridge. 
<P>

