<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Cutting Edge: The Future of Crime Fighting", on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
29, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2>&quot;Cutting Edge: The Future of Crime Fighting&quot;</H2>

<H3>A ONE-HOUR SPECIAL ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
Tools and tactics used by criminals in the 1990s have turned hi-tech.
 Police are meeting the challenge of fighting modern day crime
by using  methods and weapons that appear to be borrowed from
science fiction.  <I><B>Cutting Edge: The Future of Crime Fighting</B></I>,
airing <U>Wednesday, February 21, 1996, (8:00 - 9:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, is about crime fighters and the weapons they
use to take back the streets. 
<P>
<I><B>Cutting Edge: The Future of Crime Fighting</B></I> will
take viewers to the front lines in the war on crime.  They will
fly in a super silent helicopter that chases fugitives without
being seen or heard; ride along with police and observe the forensic
team in action; and witness the drama of their first response
to a crime scene.
<P>
This hi-tech look at crime is divided into three parts:
<P>
<B> Action/Prevention </B>which<B> </B>examines the advanced tools
police use to stop crime or apprehend suspects.
<P>
<B> Investigation</B>, a two part exercise, leads off with the
crime scene, where 21st Century forensic technology is used to
gather critical evidence for analysis.  Then, the viewer is taken
to the Crime Lab where the evidence is examined, and where computers
and other highly evolved scientific equipment are utilized to
solve the most complicated of crimes.
<P>
 The <B>Future </B>segment looks at the unbelievable world of
weaponry and technologies that are just around the corner.
<P>
<I><B>Cutting Edge: The Future of Crime Fighting</B></I> airs
<U>Wednesday, February 21, 1996, at </U><U>8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
