<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Seduced by Madness", a four hour miniseries on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
29, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>&quot;Seduced by Madness: The Diane Borchardt Story&quot;</I>
</H2>

<H3>A NEW FOUR HOUR MINI-SERIES ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
A well-liked teacher uses money and passion to manipulate three
vulnerable students into killing her husband in <I><B>Seduced
By Madness: The Diane Borchardt Story</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday,
February 25, 1996 (part one)</U>, and <U>Monday, February 26,
1996 (part two; 9:00 -11:00 p.m. both nights)</U>, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Ann-Margret, Peter Coyote </B>and <B>Christian Campbell</B>
star in the four hour mini-series based on one of the most sensational
trials in recent history.
<P>
In <I><B>Seduced By Madness: The Diane Borchardt Story</B></I>,
the whole town knew Diane Borchardt (Ann-Margret), a popular high-school
teacher, was distressed by her impending divorce.  However, no
one knew she was plotting his murder.
<P>
Diane was obsessive and possessive -- obsessed with marriage and
family; possessed by  a jealous memory of her husband's first
wife, who died before they were married.   
<P>
When her eccentric behaviour prods her husband to seek a divorce,
she looks for accomplices to help her execute her plan.  She finds
three: Douglas Vest Jr., voted the &quot;sweetest boy at Jefferson
High&quot;; Joshua Yanke, a member of the school choir; and Michael
Maldonado, Vest's cousin.
<P>
In the end, one flaw in Diane Borchardt's meticulously planned
scheme prevents her from getting away with murder in, <I><B>Seduced
By Madness: The Diane Borchardt</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, February,
25, 1996</U>, and <U>Monday, February 26, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U>,
both nights, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>

