<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Sins of Silence", a drama inspired by actual events on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
26, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;Sins of Silence&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>A DRAMA INSPIRED BY ACTUAL EVENTS </H3>

<H2>ON CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A former nun, who runs a rape crisis centre, goes to jail to protect
a young victim in, <I><B>Sins of Silence</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday,
February 20, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Emmy Award winner <B>Lindsay Wagner </B>(<I>The Bionic Woman,
Jesse, Scruples, A Message from Holly, The Incredible Journey
of Meg Laurel, Fighting For My Daughter, Passions</I>), and <B>Holly
Marie Combs</B> (<I>Picket Fences, Born on the Fourth of July,
New York Stories, Flanagan, Chain of Desire, Guiding Light, As
The World Turns</I>) star. 
<P>
Also appearing are <B>Sean McCann, Cynthia Sikes, Victor Argo</B>
and <B>Brian Kerwin</B>.
<P>
In <I><B>Sins of Silence</B></I>, former nun Molly McKinley (Wagner)
is a rape counselor who develops a strong and trusting relationship
with a vulnerable 17-year-old rape victim, Sophie (Combs). 
<P>
When the rapist's defense attorney serves Molly with a subpoena
for Sophie's records, Molly refuses to comply with the summons
and is imprisoned for contempt of court.
<P>
Now Sophie is faced with a difficult dilemma: does she come to
her friend's rescue, or does she protect her personal privacy
and reputation?
<P>
Daniel H. Blatt is the executive producer, Cynthia Sikes and Susan
Murdoch are the producers and Sam Pillsbury the director.
<P>
<I><B>Sins of Silence</B></I>, shot in Toronto, airs <U>Tuesday,
February 20, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

