<HEAD>

<TITLE>"A Case For Life", an original story on CHCH-TV.</TITLE>


</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
25, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;A Case For Life&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>AN ORIGINAL STORY ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
The abortion issue positions two, otherwise close, sisters on
opposite sides.  When the one sister risks dying if she continues
her pregnancy, the other, a lawyer, files a lawsuit against her
in, <I><B>A Case For Life</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, February
18, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Valerie Bertinelli, Mel Harris </B>and <B>Brian McNamara </B>star
in the two-hour production.
<P>
<I><B>A Case For Life</B></I> opens with the scene of an anti-abortion
demonstration at a women's clinic organized by Kelly Porter (Bertinelli).
 Meanwhile, Kelly's sister, attorney Liz Hamilton (Harris), arrives
escorting her pregnant client who has been raped and beaten by
her husband.
<P>
After an expectant Kelly collapses during the protest, it is discovered
she has congenital heart disease.  Her physician recommends she
undergo a therapeutic abortion, as the strain of the fetus could
send her into massive cardiac arrest.  Kelly and her husband Stan
(McNamara) reject the suggestion and shortly thereafter, Kelly
signs a statement voluntarily refusing treatment.
<P>
Liz pleads with Kelly to reverse her decision, arguing that a
man and children will be left without a wife and mother if she
proceeds.  Eventually, even Kelly's husband and father begin to
reconsider the abortion issue, however, Kelly stands steadfast.
<P>
Liz then files a lawsuit against Kelly, citing abandonment as
the reason.  A few days into trial, Kelly is again hospitalized,
but the trial proceeds in her absence with the judge ruling in
her favour.   
<P>
Seven months into the pregnancy, Kelly suffers cardiac arrest
with only one person able to assist her -- Liz.   Kelly loses
her baby, but survives open heart surgery.   During a painful
period, it is Liz who makes Stan love his dead child, and over
time, the sisters reconcile.   <I><B>A Case For Life</B></I> airs
<U>Sunday, February 18, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV,</B>
simulcast/<B>ABC. </B>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR>
