<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Robin Cook's Terminal", a two-hour thriller on CHCH-TV
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
22, 1996</B></I> 
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<H1><I>&quot;Robin Cook's Terminal&quot;</I></H1>

<H2>A Two-Hour Thriller on CHCH-TV</CENTER></H2>

<P>
Two medical researchers uncover a diabolical money-making plot
of a prestigious cancer centre, exposing disturbing moral issues
that impact on the medical profession in <I><B>Robin Cook's Terminal</B></I>,
airing <U>Monday, February 12, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on
<B>CHCH-TV</B>.   
<P>
<B>Doug Savant </B>(<I>Melrose Place</I>), <B>Nia Peeples</B>
(<I>Courthouse</I>) and <B>Michael Ironside</B> (<I>seaQuest 2032</I>)
star in the thriller based on the best selling novel, &quot;Terminal,&quot;
by Dr. Robin Cook (<I>Coma</I>).
<P>
In <I><B>Robin Cook's Terminal</B></I>, Sean O'Grady (Savant),
a cancer research doctor, crosses paths with his former lover,
nurse Janet Reardon (Peeples), when he begins work at the esteemed
Forbes Centre, a Seattle hospital renowned for its work on a rare
form of brain cancer and its list of wealthy patrons who have
contracted cancer, and who have been cured.
<P>
Already suspicious of the centre's extraordinary results, the
news of two mysterious murders and the strange death of a young
patient compel Sean and Janet to embark on an amateur investigation
that places their lives in peril.
<P>
Learning too much -- that patients are being given cancer in order
for the centre to cure them, thus ensuring the centre's receipt
of large monetary grants -- both are wanted, dead.
<P>
Emmy Award winner Larry Elikann (<I>A Mother's Prayer, Out of
Darkness, An Inconvenient Woman</I>) directed from a teleplay
by Nancy Isaak.  
<P>
  
<P>
<I><B>Robin Cook's Terminal</B></I> airs <U>Monday, February 12,
1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on<B> CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>
