<HEAD>

<TITLE>Michael Campbell's "Money Talks TV" premieres on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
17, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2>Michael Campbell's</H2>

<H2><I>MONEY TALKS TV </I></H2>

<H2>comes to CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
Designed for just about everyone, <B>Michael Campbell's</B> <I><B>Money
Talks TV</B></I> looks into the economy, business and investment
markets while providing practical information in a no-nonsense,
lighthearted way. Helping people make and save money, the one
hour edition of <I><B>Money Talks TV</B></I> premieres <U>Saturday,
January 27, 1996 (4:30 - 5:30 p.m.),</U> on <B>CHCH-TV, </B>with
a half-hour edition debuting <U>Saturday February 3, 1996, at
10:00 a.m.</U>, both in their regular weekly time slots. 
<P>
<B>BCTV</B>'s financial analyst,<B> Michael Campbell</B>, who
enjoys regular features on <I>Canada Tonight </I>as well as <I>BCTV
News</I>, and heard on the Western Radio Network, hosts.
<P>
<I><B>Money Talks TV</B></I>, an interactive program pre-recorded
with a studio audience, will take an enlightening, and occasionally,
humorous look at the world of money. Incorporating phone polls
and call-ins to financial experts, the show will encourage viewers
to write, fax, e-mail and call to address the show's topics. Weekly,
guests, distinguished in their respective fields, will allow viewers
an inside look at how each attained success. 
<P>
Regular show features will include such areas as:
<UL>
<LI><U><B>How to Grow a Million Dollar Company</B></U><B> </B>-
individuals who have moved a small business into a million dollar
success will share their methods with the audience.
<LI><U><B>Great Idea </B></U>- inventors will demonstrate their
great ideas.
<LI><U><B>Hot Seat</B></U> - guests will describe their business
as well as their main problems; a panel of experts will suggest
how these guests could move to the next level of success.
<LI><U><B>Hot Stocks and Mutuals</B> </U>- this will encompass
a money manager's views of where the best places are to be in
the market and which ones should be avoided.
<LI><U><B>Weird Business</B></U><B> </B>- bizarre businesses will
be sought out and the founders queried on how they came by their
ideas, and how they got started. 
</UL>

<P>
<I><B>Money Talks TV</B></I>, the business show without econo-speak,
premieres <U>Saturday, January 27, 1996, at 4:30 p.m.</U>, followed
by the debut of the half-hour edition <U>Saturday, February 3,
1996, at 10:00 a.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <I><B>Money Talks TV</B></I>
will be broadcast in all <A HREF="../wic/wic.htm">WIC</A> markets.

<P>

