<HEAD>

<TITLE>Two All-New Television Series Premiere on CHCH-TV!</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
17, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3>Two All-New Television Series</H3>

<H2>&quot;<I>WORLD'S FUNNIEST VIDEOS&quot;</I> and &quot;<I>SECOND
NOAH&quot;</I></H2>

<H3>Premiere on CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
<B>CHCH-TV</B> is pleased to announce the acquisition of <I><B>World's
Funniest Videos</B></I>, premiering <U>Thursday, February 1, 1996
(8:00- 8:30 p.m.)</U>, and <I><B>Second Noah</B></I>, debuting
<U>Monday, February 5, 1996 (8:00 - 9:00 p.m.)</U>. 
<P>
From the producers of the hit series, <I>America's Funniest Home
Videos</I>, comes the <I><B>World's Funniest Videos</B></I>, hosted
by <B>Dave Coulier</B> (<I>Full House</I>) and <B>Eva La Rue</B>
(<I>All My Children</I>).  This new television series, shot on
location at Florida's Epcot Center before a live audience at an
outdoor amphitheatre, will feature never-before-seen videos sent
from viewers from around the world.  Airing weekly, <I><B>World's
Funniest Videos </B></I>premieres <U>Thursday, February 1, 1996,
at 8:00 p.m.</U>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>
<I><B>Second Noah</B></I>, starring <B>Daniel Hugh Kelly </B>(<I>Hardcastle
and McCormick</I>),<B> Betsy Brantley</B> (<I>Tour of Duty, Havana</I>),
<B>Deidre O'Connell</B> (<I>Sirens, Leaving Normal</I>) and <B>Jimmy
Marsden</B> (<I>The Nanny, Ambush in Waco</I>), is about the extraordinary
Beckett family.   
<P>
Noah Beckett (Kelly), a famous Tampa University basketball coach
and writer, has put his life on hold to raise their six adopted
children, ranging in age from a three-year-old baby to a girl
crazy teen, and their 40 pets, which include ferrets, iguanas
and a pot-bellied pig.   Meanwhile, his wife, Jesse (Brantley),
has her hands full as the Florida Zoo's veterinarian.
<P>
However, despite their eclectic home setting, the Becketts always
seem to have room for one more, which is what a homeless 17-year-old
girl counts on when she abandons her brother at the zoo.   As
hoped, the Becketts take the boy in, and eventually, his lonesome
sister, too.
<P>
Add to the household an abrasive, gregarious, take-charge kind
of woman (O'Connell), who answers the Beckett's ad to become their
tenth housekeeper, and viewers get a new kind of loving family
who can handle almost anything.  <I><B>Second Noah </B></I>premieres
<U>Monday, February 5, 1996, at 8:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <BR>
