<HEAD>

<TITLE>"In The Line Of Duty: Smoke Jumpers" a world premiere on CHCH TV
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
15, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>&quot;In The Line of Duty: Smoke Jumpers&quot;</H1>

<H2>A World Premiere Movie on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A free-spirited, parachuting firefighter is forced to choose between
the love of a feisty woman and his addiction to the exhilaration
he experiences when taking life-threatening risks in, <I><B>In
the Line of Duty: Smoke Jumpers</B></I>, airing <U>Sunday, February
11, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Adam Baldwin, Lindsay Frost, Tim Carhart</B> and <B>Rob Youngblood</B>
star in the latest installment in the popular <I>In The Line of
Duty</I> television movies.
<P>
Inspired by a true story about firefighting, <I><B>In the Line
of Duty: Smoke Jumpers</B></I> is about the difficult choice firefighter
Don Mackey (Baldwin) must make after he begins a life with Rene
(Frost), a waitress and divorced mother.
<P>
The attraction of Don and Rene to one another is instantaneous.
Following their marriage, Rene becomes a ground firefighter and
shares in the thrill of Don's work. However, when Rene narrowly
escapes death during a raging wildfire, she decides to retire
from firefighting and concentrate on being a mother. Her experience
also leaves her disapproving of Don's smoke jumping -- a job that
takes him away from the family and places his life in serious
peril. 
<P>
Ultimately, Don is forced to choose between his family and his
obsession with his work. <I><B>In the Line of Duty: Smoke Jumpers</B></I>
airs <U>Sunday, February 11, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>,
simulcast/<B>NBC</B>.
<P>

