<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Heist", Tuesday, January 30, on CHCH TV.</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
12, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>&quot;The Heist&quot;</H1>

<H3>on CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
An ex-con, framed for a crime gone bad, plots a daring robbery
to even the score with his former racetrack partner, and to win
back his woman in, <I><B>The Heist</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday,
January 30, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Pierce Brosnan</B> (<I>Remington Steele, The Fourth Protocol,
Goldeneye</I>), <B>Tom Skerritt </B>(<I>Top Gun, Steel Magnolias,
Picket Fences</I>) and Australian actress <B>Wendy Hughes </B><I>(My
Brilliant Career; Careful, He Might Hear You</I>) star.
<P>
In<I><B> The Heist</B></I>, savvy con-man Neal Skinner (Brosnan)
was framed for an emerald smuggling deal and sent to prison. 
 Four years later, he has one week to execute a simple scheme
of revenge against Ebet Berens (Skerritt), the man who set him
up and to win back his fickle girlfriend, Sheila (Hughes), who
has since moved in with Berens. 
<P>
The plot is bold and clear -- hold up the racetrack where Berens
is the head of security and frame him as the crook.
<P>
Double talk and double dealing add to the intrigue of <I><B>The
Heist</B></I>, airing <U>Tuesday, January 30, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

