<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Canterville Ghost", January 27 at 8:30pm on CHCH-TV.  Boo!
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
9, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3><I>CHCH-TV has the engaging story</I></H3>

<H1>&quot;The Canterville Ghost&quot;</H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
A 400- year-old ghost, doomed to haunt an old castle, befriends
a young girl who travels  to the Other World to plead his case
before the Angel of Death, thus setting him free to rest in peace
in <I><B>The Canterville Ghost</B></I>, airing <U>Saturday, January
27, 1996 (9:00-11:00 p.m.),</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Patrick Stewart, Neve Campbell, Ed Wiley</B> and <B>Cherie
Lunghi</B> star in the two-hour television movie.
<P>
In <I><B>The Canterville Ghost</B></I>, Professor Otis accepts
a research grant to study in England, leaving his wife and children
ecstatic that they get the chance to live in a real English castle,
Canterville Hall.   Upon their arrival, the children, 16-year-old
Virginia Otis (Campbell) and her two younger brothers, learn that
the most remarkable feature about the residence is Sir Simon de
Canterville (Stewart), a 400-year-old ghost, visible only to them.
<P>
Proper introductions once made, the terrifying facade of Sir Simon
melts to reveal a amiable fellow who advises Virginia on her budding
romance with a young neighbour.  He even concedes to playing Hamlet
-- the role of the ghost, naturally.  Comfortable with their friendship,
Sir Simon eventually discloses his dilemma to Virginia: he is
sentenced to inhabit the castle unless he can convince a &quot;Golden
Girl&quot; to plead his case before the Angel of Death.  Virginia
immediately agrees and follows him through the fireplace.
<P>
    
<P>
The following day, just as the Otises are starting to panic, Virginia
reappears, content in the fact that Sir Simon has finally been
released to rest in peace next to his beloved wife.  Further to
this good news, Professor Otis announces his acceptance of a permanent
teaching post in England, and that the family will remain at Canterville
Hall.
<P>
<I><B>The Canterville Ghost</B></I> airs <U>Saturday, January
27, 1996, at 8:30 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

