<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Mad Dog and Glory", the theatrical hit, on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
8, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>&quot;Mad Dog and Glory&quot;</H1>

<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A remarkable friendship between a local gangster and a shy police
photographer develops when the latter saves the lawbreaker's life
in <I><B>Mad Dog and Glory</B></I> airing <U>Thursday, January
25, 1996 (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.),</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Robert De Niro, Bill Murray, Uma Thurman, David Caruso</B>
and <B>Kathy Baker</B> star in the theatrical directed by John
McNaughton.
<P>
In <I><B>Mad Dog and Glory,</B></I> a timid photographer-detective,
Mad Dog (De Niro), inadvertently saves the life of a local gangster
and loan shark, Frank Milo (Murray), when he interrupts a hold-up
in a neighbourhood grocery store.
<P>
As an act of gratitude, Milo sends his beautiful bartender, Glory
(Thurman), to stay with Mad Dog for a week.  Initially, Mad Dog
opposes the idea, however, gradually he starts to fall in love
with his charming co-habitant -- much to Milo's vexation.   What
ensues is a potentially murderous situation.
<P>
<I><B>Mad Dog and Glory</B></I> airs <U>Thursday, January 25,
1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

