<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Legend of the Ruby Silver", January 13, on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: January
3, 1996</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>&quot;Legend of the Ruby Silver&quot;</H1>

<H2>on CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A financially strapped widow and her son are drawn into a silver
mining scheme that leads to danger, greed and deceit in the adventure
television movie, <I><B>Legend of the Ruby Silver</B></I>, airing
<U>Saturday, January 13, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>John Schneider, Rebecca Jenkins</B> and <B>Jonathan Jackson</B>
star.
<P>
In <I><B>Legend of the Ruby Silver</B></I>, a mining accident
has left Kay Rainie (Jenkins) a widow. She works at the local
restaurant to support herself and her son, Matt (Jackson). However,
Kay is in a dilemma as their home is about to go into foreclosure.
 
<P>
Then, Tommy Town (Schneider) arrives on the scene.  He has come
looking for Kay's deceased husband who had previously agreed to
work for him on a mining operation on a dormant silver mine known
as the Ruby Silver.  When he discovers her husband is dead, he
finds a replacement who will do the job only if there is a cook
provided.   Town convinces Kay he can solve her financial problems
if she comes along to prepare the meals.  He also promises to
employ Matt and give everyone a share of the profits.
<P>
The four make the perilous journey to the Ruby Silver, but what
Town's workers are subjected to are greed, deceit and harsh truths,
as Town sells them out after discovering the silver.  In the end,
nevertheless, Kay and Matt are the ones richer for the misadventure
as they rebuild their lives having learned invaluable life lessons.
 
<P>
<I><B>Legend of the Ruby Silver</B></I> airs <U>Saturday, January
13, 1996, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/<B>ABC</B>.
<P>

