<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Survival in the Snow", a Movies Eleven adventure on CHCH-TV.
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">
<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: December
18, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1><I>&quot;SURVIVAL IN THE SNOW&quot;</I></H1>

<H3>A Compelling Adventure on CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
On an 1100 mile dog sled race across the storm riddled wilds of
Alaska, the primary danger for racers is usually the real possibility
of freezing to death.  However, when two top contenders are murdered,
a young woman's chances for survival become even more desperate
as she races for her life against a killer in <I><B>Survival in
the Snow</B></I>, a two-hour movie airing <U>Tuesday, January
9, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Kate Jackson</B>, (<I>Scarecrow and Mrs. King, Making Love</I>),
<B>Corbin Bernsen</B> (<I>Major League, Hello Again</I>) and <B>Michael
Damian</B> (<I>The Young and The Restless</I>) star.
<P>
In <I><B>Survival in the Snow</B></I>, Jessie Arnold is a woman
who has already raced in the Iditarod, an 1100 mile dog sled race
from Anchorage to Nome which tests the skill, stamina and courage
of all participants.  Having lost on the trail years before, and
almost dying from exposure, Jessie vowed never to race again.
 Instead, her brother, Rob, was to drive the breed of dogs that
Jessie had raised for the Iditarod.  When a tragic accident takes
his life days before the event, Jessie, in great need of the $50,000
prize money in order to maintain custody of her 12-year-old son,
pushes aside her fear to race herself.
<P>
The natural risks of the race are compounded when two of the top
drivers fall victim to questionable, fatal calamities.   Jessie,
who knew the dead victims, is certain they were killed and becomes
convinced that her brother's death was also the result of cold-blooded
murder.
<P>
As Jessie reaches the final lap in the grueling race, she finds
herself one of the three leading participants.  It is then her
instincts tell her that one of the other two top contenders is
the murderer, with his sights set on her as his next victim.
<P>
The stakes for the 1100 mile Iditarod Trail race have never been
higher as Jessie fights for  sheer <I><B>Survival in the Snow</B></I>,
a suspense-filled drama airing <U>Tuesday, January 9, 1996, at
9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/CBS.
<P>

