<HEAD>

<TITLE>Danielle Steel's "No Greater Love", on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: December
4, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>DANIELLE STEEL'S </H1>

<H1><I>&quot;NO GREATER LOVE&quot;</I></H1>

<H1>ON CHCH-TV</H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
On the maiden voyage of the Titanic, the sea claims the lives
of a young woman's parents and fianc&eacute;, leaving her to care
for her siblings and to run the family business.   Years later,
fate sees her aboard another ship where she meets a man who unlocks
her ability to love again.  <I><B>No Greater Love</B></I> airs
<U>Monday, January 1, 1996, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.) </U>on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Kelly Rutherford </B>(<I>The Adventures of Brisco County Jr.,
Generations</I>), <B>Chris Sarandon </B>(<I>The Princess Bride,
Dog Day Afternoon</I>) and <B>Simon MacCorkindale</B> (<I>Falcon
Crest, Jaws 3, Counterstrike</I>) star in the two-hour production.
<P>
<I><B>No Greater Love</B></I>, based on the novel by Danielle
Steel, centres on the life of  Edwina Winfield (Rutherford). 
In the year 1912, the Winfield family, along with Edwina's fianc&eacute;,
are enjoying life on the luxurious Titanic.  When the ship crashes
into an iceberg and slowly sinks, Edwina's parents and betrothed
are among the dead.
<P>
Returning to Boston, Edwina, the oldest, takes charge and works
arduously to save her parents' crumbling newspaper empire, and
to support her siblings.  Then, after 12 years of persevering
to keep the family together, Edwina takes an Atlantic trip, her
first since that horrific night aboard the Titanic.  To her surprise,
an affair with a handsome Englishman revives a passion she had
repressed for so many years.  Upon her return to the United States,
Edwina, finally free from the horrors of one fateful night, eventually
finds true love with another man.
<P>
<I><B>No Greater Love</B></I> airs <U>Monday, January 1, 1996,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast/NBC.
<P>

