<HEAD>

<TITLE>Holiday Programming on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: December
1, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>The Holiday Season</H1>

<H1>on CHCH-TV</H1>

</CENTER>

<P>
<B>CHCH-TV</B> welcomes the holiday season with familiar favourites
and new traditions.  Following are special Christmas holiday treats
the whole family can enjoy:
<P>
(in chronological order)
<H2>
<CENTER>
<I>HOME FOR CHRISTMAS</I> 
</CENTER>
</H2>

<P>
<I><B>Mickey Rooney</B></I> stars in this tenderhearted story.
 Amanda, a little girl of six, wishes for a grandfather for Christmas.
 In a strange and magical way, her wish is granted.  
<P>
Elmer (Rooney), a petty thief is caught breaking into a car. 
The stiff-lipped owner, Reg, who lacks any kind of sentiment,
allows Elmer to work for him doing odd jobs to compensate for
the damages.  Reg's daughter, Amanda, and Elmer are immediately
drawn to each other.  Plus Amanda thinks Santa brought her a grandfather
for Christmas.
<P>
In reality he did.  When Elmer discovers that Reg is the son he
never met, he flees in shame, not wanting the secret to be revealed.
 Distressed by Elmer's sudden departure, Amanda follows him onto
the tough city streets.  Only a miracle and perhaps a loving grandfather
will be able to find her.
<P>
<I><B>Home For Christmas </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, December 24 at
6:00 p.m. and Monday, December 25, 1995, at 3:00 p.m.</U> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>THE CHRISTMAS BOX</I></H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
<I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I>,<I><B> </B></I>a heartwarming,
ageless tale about love, family and the gift of sharing, airs
<U>Sunday, December 17, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Richard Thomas, Maureen O'Hara</B> and <B>Annette O'Toole </B>star
in the drama.
<P>
In <I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I>, the Evans family -- Keri (O'Toole),
Richard (Thomas) and their six-year-old daughter, Jenna, live
in a cramped downtown apartment.  When Keri learns about a caretaker
position in a grand old home, she convinces her over-worked husband
to accompany her on the interview.
<P>
Almost instantly, Richard is at odds with the elderly, overbearing
owner of the house, Mary Parkin (O'Hara).   Despite their unfriendly
meeting, Mary retains the couple, with the contentious relationship
between Mary and Richard persisting.   Richard even experiences
troubled dreams of angels and senses that Mary and her home hold
a sinister secret.  Keri and Jenna, on the other hand, enjoy a
warm friendship with Mary, who recognizes how much the little
girl misses her hard-working father.
<P>
However, it has been pre-determined that Mary and Richard forge
a bond of affection.  This accomplished, Richard learns surprising
secrets from Mary's past that awaken him to the true meaning of
Christmas.
<P>
<I><B>The Christmas Box</B></I> airs <U>Sunday, December 17, 1995,
(9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, simulcast<B>/CBS.</B>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CHRISTMAS ON DIVISION STREET</I></H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A youth, charmed by the wisdom and generosity of a feisty 80-year-old
homeless man, pursues a relationship with the fellow that leaves
his life enriched as his old friend relinquishes his.  The bitter-sweet
drama, <I><B>Christmas on Division Street</B></I>, airs <U>Tuesday,
December 19, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Hume Cronyn, Fred Savage, Kenneth Welsh, Cloyce Morrow, Casey
Ellison, Kahla Lichti</B> and <B>Badja Djola</B> star.  
<P>
In <I><B>Christmas On Division Street</B></I>, 14-year-old Trevor
Atwood (Savage), still suffering the loss of his grandfather,
fails to share his family's excitement about their move to Philadelphia.
 The transition is made more difficult when Derek (Ellison), the
school jokester feels it his duty to torment the &quot;new guy.&quot;
 Then, one day while in the library researching information for
a history paper, Trevor encounters Cleveland Meriwether (Cronyn),
an elderly homeless man and self-proclaimed &quot;Minister of
Education.&quot;  His personality and exhaustive knowledge of
American history win Trevor over.
<P>
As the story unfolds, Trevor pursues a complex friendship with
Cleveland, a man besieged with drinking problems after causing
the death of a boy in an auto accident years ago.   
<P>
So enamored with Cleveland is Trevor that he is unwilling to desert
him no matter the outcome.  Even after Cleveland rejects their
friendship, a lie initiated by a social worker, Trevor refuses
to stop caring for the man who would leave him with wonderful
memories and numerous examples of magnanimity: like the time Trevor
was stranded in the rain without train fare and Cleveland sold
his blood to give him the train fare; or the time Cleveland distributed
among the neighbourhood's needy, a sack of clothing Trevor had
brought for him; and so sweet was the time the two walked the
streets through the season's first snowfall when Cleveland landed
a job, temporarily.
<P>
Only after Cleveland's death, does the essence of the holiday
season take on a new and profound  meaning for Trevor and his
family.   <I><B>Christmas on Division Street</B></I>, a Westcom
Entertainment Group production, airs <U>Tuesday, December 19,
1995, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>, pre-release/<B>CBS</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>WHITE CHRISTMAS</I> </H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
Memorable Irving Berlin scores are showcased in this 1954 classic
starring <B>Bing Crosby, Danny Kaye, Rosemary Clooney</B> and
<B>Vera Ellen</B>.  The plot is simple in the delightful musical
-- two army buddies (Crosby and Kaye) develop a comedy act, then
team up with two performing sisters (Clooney and Ellen).
<P>
                        
<P>
<I><B>White Christmas </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, December 24, 1994,
(9:00 - 11:30 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CAROLS AND MIDNIGHT MASS</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Annually on this holy night, <B>CHCH</B> broadcasts Midnight Mass,
<I>live</I>, from the Cathedral of Christ The King.  His excellency
Bishop Anthony F. Tonnos will celebrate the first Mass of Christmas.
<P>
<I><B>Carols and Midnight Mass</B></I><B> </B>commence at <U>11:30
p.m.</U> on <U>Sunday, December 24, 1995</U>.   <I><B>Midnight
Mass</B></I> is repeated <U>Monday, December 25  (8:00 - 10:00
a.m.).</U>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>SOUNDS OF CHRISTMAS</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
From Crossroads Christian Communications comes a unique Christmas
card greeting.   Hosted by David Mainse and his wife, Norma-Jean,
<I><B>Sounds of Christmas</B></I> is a collection of music videos,
woven around the Christmas story.
<P>
The warm, music special airs <U>Monday, December 25 (10:00 - 10:30
a.m.).</U> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>DOFASCO CHRISTMAS</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The songs of the holiday season are performed by the talented
Dofasco Male Chorus, the Dofasco Ladies Choral Ensemble and the
Hamilton Philharmonic Youth Orchestra under the direction of Geoff
Bullivant and Glen Mallory.
<P>
<I><B>Dofasco Christmas </B></I>can be enjoyed <U>Monday, December
25, 1995 (10:30 - 11:00 a.m. and again at 5:30 p.m.)</U>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CHRISTMAS IS</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Benji and Waldo team up once again, this time in the charming,
animated tale <I><B>Christmas Is</B></I>.   In this special, the
duo search for the true meaning of Christmas.  Magically, Benji
travels back 2000 years and discovers something about himself
and Christmas today.
<P>
<I><B>Christmas Is</B></I> airs <U>Monday, December 25, 1995 (11:00
- 11:30 a.m.).</U>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>THE OTHER WISEMAN</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
<I><B>The Other Wiseman</B></I> is a timeless story of peace and
goodwill.  It is the tale of Artaban and his arduous journey to
see the newborn King.
<P>
                                                             
                                                             
   
<P>
<I><B>The Other Wiseman</B></I> airs <U>Monday, December 25, 1995,
(11:30 - 12 noon)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>THE CITY THAT FORGOT ABOUT CHRISTMAS</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
Bringing a deeper meaning to this festive time of year is the
animated special, <I><B>The City That Forgot About Christmas</B></I>.
   Benji, a little boy, and his dog, Waldo, are featured in this
tale about a town that loses its love when it loses the spirit
of Christmas.  Unexpected twists and turns result in a happy ending,
underscoring the significance of the holiday season.
<P>
<I><B>The City That Forgot About Christmas</B></I> airs <U>Monday,
December 25, 1995 (12:00 noon - </U>
<P>
<U>12:30 p.m.)</U>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>ROUGH EDGES</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
<B>Catherine Swing</B> and <B>Mary Bellows </B>star in this upbeat,
urban Christmas tale about a chance encounter between two women
from opposite sides of the tracks.
<P>
The charming, poignant drama forces the two women to look beyond
their &quot;wrappings&quot; and see where the real riches of the
Christmas spirit thrive. 
<P>
<I><B>Rough Edges, </B></I>based on a stage play by Donna Hinkle,
with screenplay by William Finlay, airs <U>Christmas Day (12:30
- 1:00 p.m.)</U>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CLARENCE</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
The angel from the 1946 classic, <I>It's A Wonderful Life</I>,
descends to earth once again in the TV movie, <I><B>Clarence</B></I>.
 Headlining in the warmhearted comedy are <B>Robert Carradine</B>
and <B>Kate Trotter</B>.
   
<P>
In <I><B>Clarence</B></I>, we discover that the angel, by the
same name, has become younger in age over the past forty-five
years and is a clock maker in heaven.  With a great lack of enthusiasm,
Clarence consents to return to earth to save the life of a fellow
angel's wife.  The woman is contemplating suicide as her company
is heading for financial ruin.
<P>
Raise your spirits with the heavenly humour of, <I><B>Clarence</B></I>,
<U>Monday, December 25, 1995 (1:00 - 3:00 p.m.).</U> 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CELEBRATION IN SONG</I></H2>
<BR>
<I><B>(Ryerson United Church Christmas Special)</B></I>
</CENTER>

<P>
The combined choirs and hand bell ringers from Ryerson United
Church pay tribute to the traditional carols of Christmas, under
the direction of Richard M. Street.  <I><B>Celebration In Song</B></I>
airs <U>December 25 (5:00 - 5:30 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>CHCH-TV/Y95 CLASSIC ROCK</I></H2>
<H2><I>NEW YEAR'S EVE SUPER PARTY</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
<B>CHCH-TV</B> and <B>Y95</B> usher in a special new year, Hamilton's
sesquicentennial (150th), with the first annual <I><B>CHCH-TV/Y95
Classic Rock New Year's Eve Super Party</B></I>,  <U>Sunday, December
31, 1995</U>, broadcast <I>live to air</I> on <B>Y95</B> <U>(9:00
p.m. - 1:00 a.m.),</U> simulcast with <B>CHCH-TV</B> (<U>11:30
p.m - 12:30 a.m.).</U>  
<P>
Hosting the super celebration at the Convention Centre in downtown
Hamilton, will be <B>Y95</B>'s <B>Scott Thompson</B> and <B>Lori
Love.</B>
<P>
The<B> <I>CHCH-TV/Y95</I> <I>Classic Rock New Year's Eve Super
Party</I></B> will<I><B> </B></I>feature over 1,500 people dancing
to the beat of classic rock's best.  Then, when <B>CHCH</B> joins
the fun in progress at 11:30 p.m., the event turns into a huge
video party, with a monitor wall displaying classic rock artists
and the party guests movin' to their music.  Add to the festivities
confetti canons and grand prizes, and you have one super party.
 
<P>
However, party-goers don't have to be at the Convention Centre
to take full advantage of all the great sounds.  The <B>CHCH-TV/Y95</B>
simulcast allows <I>everyone</I> to get up and dance <I>anywhere</I>!
  But if you still want to be there, the hotline number for tickets
is 
<P>
905-388-5281.
<P>
Say good-bye to '95 and hello to '96 at the first annual <I><B>CHCH-TV/Y95
Classic Rock New Year's Eve Super Party</B></I>, <U>Sunday, December
31, 1995</U>, broadcast <I>live to air</I> on <B>Y95 </B><U>(9:00
p.m. - 1:00 a.m.)</U>, simulcast with <B>CHCH-TV</B> <U>(11:30
p.m. - 12:30 a.m.)</U>. 
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2><I>THE JAPANESE RED AND WHITE SHOW</I></H2>
</CENTER>

<P>
For the 11th consecutive season, <B>CHCH </B>will broadcast the
<I>live</I>, musical extravaganza from Tokyo, Japan.  Traditionally,
each New Year, 22 of  the most popular male vocalists (white team)
and 22 of  the most popular female vocalists (red team) have engaged
in a fierce, but friendly rivalry in song.  This year, over 60
artists are competing in the <I><B>Japanese Red and White Show</B></I>.
<P>
During the program, millions of viewers in Japan cast their votes
for their favourite singer.  However, millions more watch this
New Year's tradition as it is broadcast around the world and seen
by fans in Korea, the United States, France, China, Canada and
more.
<P>
Start a new tradition in 1996, watch <I><B>The Japanese Red And
White Show</B></I>, <U>Monday, January 1 (11:00 a.m.- 3:30 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
