<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Ebbie", a modern-day "A Christmas Carol", on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: November
30, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H1>&quot;EBBIE&quot;</H1>

<H2>A MODERN DAY &quot;A CHRISTMAS CAROL&quot;</H2>

<H2>ON CHCH-TV</H2>

</CENTER>

<P>
A tough business woman, who has lost sight of the important things
in life, experiences a Christmas haunting which leaves her with
a renewed appreciation for love, goodness and compassion in <I><B>Ebbie
</B></I>(aka <I>Ms. Scrooge</I>), airing <U>Tuesday, December
12, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
Starring in the modern day version of Dickens' classic holiday
favourite, &quot;A Christmas Carol,&quot; are <B>Susan Lucci,
Wendy Crewson, Jeff DeMunn</B> and<B> Taran Noah Smith</B>.
<P>
In <I><B>Ebbie</B></I>, Elizabeth &quot;Ebbie&quot; Scrooge (Lucci)
is a shrewd CEO of Dobson's Department Store.  Her rise to the
top has been achieved through difficult decision-making and personal
sacrifices that have succeeded in her obtaining a powerful position,
but also in alienating her from her inner, gentle self and the
important people in her life.  
<P>
Then, on one Christmas Eve, Ebbie is visited by a colourful cast
of midnight visitors who take her on an emotional journey through
her past, present and future.   Reliving her former heartaches
and glimpsing into a lonely, unhappy future, Ebbie realizes the
outcome of her selfish choices and awakens Christmas morning with
a new, hopeful perspective.
<P>
<I><B>Ebbie</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday, December 12, 1995, at 9:00
p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
