<HEAD>

<TITLE>Danielle Steel's "Mixed Blessings" on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: November
21, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H2>DANIELLE STEEL'S MIXED BLESSINGS</H2>

<H3>A WORLD PREMIERE MOVIE ON CHCH-TV</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
All aspects of motherhood are explored: the elation, the heartbreak,
the allure and the pain, when three very distinct married couples
face parenthood for the first time in <B>Danielle Steel's <I>Mixed
Blessings</I></B> airing <U>Sunday, December 10, 1995, (9:00 -
11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Gabrielle Carteris</B> (<I>Beverly Hills 90210</I>), <B>Bess
Armstrong</B> (<I>My-So-Called Life</I>), <B>James Naughton</B>
(<I>The Glass Menagerie</I>), <B>Bruce Greenwood</B> (<I>St. Elsewhere</I>),
<B>Scott Baio</B> (<I>Diagnosis Murder</I>), <B>Julie Condra Douglas</B>
(<I>Eerie, Indiana</I>), and <B>Alexandra Paul</B> (<I>Baywatch</I>)
star.
<P>
Based on a best-selling novel by <B>Danielle Steel</B>, <I><B>Mixed
Blessings </B></I>centres on three married couples whose relationships
are challenged when they have to face such serious issues as infertility,
infidelity, adoption, high-risk pregnancy and unresolved personal
problems.
<P>
One couple, for example, are childless because the husband is
impotent -- a secret hidden from his wife, who is pregnant.  Another
couple are incapable of having children and risk seeing their
marriage destroyed because of the wife's depression.  Adoption
may be their only hope.   The third pair of partners desperately
want children, but postpone having a baby due to an interfering
mother who insists her daughter's career take priority.
<P>
Douglas S. Cramer (<I>Danielle Steel's Kaleidoscope, Danielle
Steel's Vanished</I>) is executive producer.
<P>
   
<P>
Relationships are saved while others are destroyed in <B>Danielle
Steel's</B> emotional drama <I><B>Mixed Blessings</B></I> airing <U>Sunday, December 10, 1995,
at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B> 
<P>
(pre-release/<B>NBC</B>).
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
