<HEAD>

<TITLE>Skating Specials This Fall on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I><B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: November
8, 1995</B></I>
<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3>CHCH-TV GLIDES INTO NOVEMBER AND DECEMBER </H3>

<H3>WITH A FULL SCHEDULE OF SKATING SPECIALS</H3>

</CENTER>

<P>
In addition to the two-hour special, <I><B>Ice Wars: The U.S.A.
Vs. The World</B></I>, airing <U>Friday, November 10, 1995 at
9:00 p.m</U>., <B>CHCH-TV</B> has put together an entire schedule
of exciting figure skating specials:
<P>
<B>Title:</B> <I><B>The Riders Ladies Skating Championships I</B></I>
<P>
<B>Venue:</B> Mankato Civic Centre, Mankato Minnesota
<P>
<B>Air Dates:</B> <U>Sunday, November 12 and Sunday, November
19, 1995 (2:00 - 3:30 p.m., post-release/CBS)</U>
<P>
<B>Description:</B> The world's top professional ladies and pairs
skaters  perform in this preliminary competition. The top four
ladies in each preliminary will meet in a final competition, airing
December 17 and 24, 1995, on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.  Pairs will also
compete, but will not advance to the final.  Scheduled competitors
include <B>Oksana Baiul,  Elizabeth Manley, Yuka Sato, </B>and
<B>Roslyn Sumners</B> along with <B>Calla Urbanski</B> and <B>Rocky
Marval</B>.  Providing commentary will be Verne Lundquist, Scott
Hamilton and Tracy Wilson.
<P>
<B>Title:</B> <I><B>Men's Outdoor Skating Challenge at Sun Valley</B></I>
<P>
<B>Venue:</B> Sun Valley Resort, Sun Valley, Idaho
<P>
<B>Air Dates</B>: <U>Sunday, November 26 and Sunday, December
3, 1995 (2:00 - 3:30 p.m., post-release/CBS)</U>
<P>
<B>Description: </B>The top U.S. and international amateurs compete
in several disciplines.  Competitors include <B>Brian Boitano,
Paul Wylie, Viktor Petrenko, Scott Williams, Alexander Fadeyev,
Gary Beacom, Petr Barna </B>and<B> Brian Orser. </B>
<P>
<B>Title:</B> <I><B>The Riders Ladies Skating Championships II</B></I>
<P>
<B>Venue: </B>Rosemont Horizon, Chicago Illinois
<P>
<B>Air Dates:</B> <U>Saturday, December 9 (3:00 - 4:00 p.m.) and
Sunday, December 10, 1995 (2:00 - 3:30 p.m., post-release/CBS)</U>
<P>
<B>Description:</B> The second-round competition among women professional
skaters in an elimination event will determine the finalists for
the tour crown.   Pairs will also compete, but will not advance
to a final.  Potential ladies competitors include <B>Nancy Kerrigan,
Caryn Kadavy, Katarina Witt, Denise Biellman, Rory Flack-Burghart
</B>and<B> Yvonne Gomez.</B>
<P>
<B>Title:</B> <I><B>The Riders Ladies Skating Championships III</B></I>
<P>
<B>Venue:</B> Matthews Arena, Northeastern University, Boston,
Massachusetts
<P>
<B>Air Dates:</B> <U>Sunday, December 17 and Sunday, December
24, 1995 (2:00 - 3:30 p.m., post- release/CBS)</U>
<P>
<B>Description: </B>Winners of the first two previous competitions
go toe-to-toe for the tour championship.   Potential ladies competitors
include <B>Nancy Kerrigan, Oksana Baiul, Katarina Witt, Yuka Sato,
Elaine Zayak, Elizabeth Manley, Caryn Kadavy </B>and<B> Denise
Biellman</B>.
<P>

