<HEAD>

<TITLE>CHCH-TV presents "Flight For Justice: The Nancy Conn Story"
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: September
20, 1995</I><HR>

<H3><CENTER><B> CHCH-TV HAS THE CHILLING DRAMA</B> </CENTER></H3>

<H4><CENTER><I><B> FIGHT FOR JUSTICE: THE NANCY CONN STORY</B></I>
</CENTER></H4>

<P>
A woman who survives a brutal attack by a serial killer tirelessly
crusades for legislation to keep her assailant behind bars when
he is paroled and once again threatens her life. <I><B>Fight For
Justice: The Nancy Conn Story</B></I>, airs <U>Tuesday, October
3, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Marilu Henner</B> (<I>Evening Shade, Taxi, Marilu</I>), <B>Peri
Gilpin</B> (<I>Frasier</I>), <B>Doug Savant</B> (<I>Melrose Place</I>),
and <B>Don Franklin</B> (<I>seaQuest 2032</I>) star in the production
along with <B>Sean McCann</B>,<B> Andrew Keegan</B>, and <B>Lisa
Jacob</B>.
<P>
<I><B>Fight For Justice: The Nancy Conn Story</B></I>, based on
a true story, is about Nancy Conn (Henner), a hard working, single
mother of two teens (Keegan and Jakub) who, despite her hectic
schedule, still manages to take several classes at the local university.
On one such occasion, while hurrying across campus, a man -- Richard
Ellard -- collides with her. Never does she anticipate that this
random encounter would result in a terrifying nightmare.
<P>
While out with her cousin (Gilpin) one evening, Nancy again runs
into Ellard, only this time he is wild-eyed and brandishing a
knife. Forcing the two women into his car, he drives to a remote
area, assaults them, then leaves them for dead. Nancy, however,
lives to identify Ellard who is subsequently arrested and convicted.
When he is later paroled and seeks retaliation against Nancy,
she relentlessly campaigns to keep Ellard off the streets.
<P>
<I><B>Fight For Justice: The Nancy Conn Story</B></I> airs <U>Tuesday,
October 3, 1995, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <HR>

<P>
