<HEAD>

<TITLE>"In The Line Of Duty: Hunt For Justice," A special drama on CHCH
</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: September
19, 1995</I><HR>

<H2><CENTER> IN THE LINE OF DUTY: HUNT FOR JUSTICE </CENTER></H2>

<H2><CENTER>ON CHCH-TV</CENTER> </H2>

<P>
A police detective and FBI agent join forces to pinpoint a group
of terrorists after two of them murder a state trooper <I><B>In
the Line of Duty: Hunt for Justice</B></I>, a new made-for-television
movie airing <U>Sunday, October 1, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Nicholas Turturro </B>(<I>NYPD Blue</I>), <B>Adam Arkin</B>
(<I>Chicago Hope</I>), <B>Miguel Ferrer </B>(<I>The Return of
Hunter</I>), <B>Dan Lauria </B>(<I>The Wonder Years</I>), and
<B>Melissa Leo</B> (<I>Homicide: Life on the Street</I>) star.
<P>
In the two hour drama, <I><B>In the Line of Duty: Hunt for Justice</B></I>,
a state trooper (Lauria) pulls over a suspicious-looking van on
the highway and is shot down in cold blood. His close friend,
detective Mike Garrett (Turturro), leads the hunt to track down
the murderers. He quickly learns that the two (Ferrer and Leo)
are leaders of a liberal underground terrorist group, the United
Freedom Front, an organization wanted in several states for numerous
anti-capitalist criminal activities -- dating back to the Vietnam
War era. He also learns that the group is being tracked by a relentless
FBI investigator, Damian Valentino (Arkin), who has invested seven
years in the search of the group's members.
<P>
After a somewhat antagonistic start to their partnership, Detective
Garrett and FBI agent Valentino finally succeed in tracking down
the terrorists.
<P>
<I><B>In the Line of Duty: Hunt for Justice</B></I> airs <U>Sunday,
October 1, 1995, at 9:00 p.m</U>. on <B>CHCH-TV</B> (simulcast/NBC).
<HR>

<P>
