<HEAD>

<TITLE>"Divas," An original emsemble drama on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: September
13, 1995</I><HR>

<H1><CENTER>DIVAS</CENTER></H1>

<H4><CENTER>AN ORIGINAL ENSEMBLE DRAMA ON CHCH-TV</CENTER> </H4>

<P>
The members of a young, all-female, African-American singing group
share an intense commitment to a dream. Their triumphs and tragedies
are chronicled in the original television movie, <I><B>Divas</B></I>,
airing <U>Tuesday, September 19, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Nicole Ari Parker </B>(<I>The Incredibly True Adventures of
Two Girls in Love</I>), <B>Tammy Townsend </B>(<I>Days of Our
Lives</I>), <B>Fatima Lowe, Lisa Carson, Mark Gomes </B>and <B>Khalil
Kain </B>star in the drama.
<P>
<I><B>Divas</B></I> focuses on an aspiring group's victories and
pain -- personally and professionally -- while the members learn
about the music business and each other.
<P>
The founder and manager of &quot;Divas&quot; is a slick, would-be
entrepreneur, Monte (Kain), who is driven by the need to prove
himself to his family. The group's co-founder is the opinionated
Tanya (Lowe). Jewel (Carson) is a working single mom who ends
up nurturing the group. Struggling to find a balance between her
demanding career and boyfriend is the seductive Lynette (Townsend).
Then, there is the pre-med student, Stephanie (Parker), who auditions
on impulse and earns a place in the group as well as Monte's heart.
<P>
Acclaimed producer/director <B>Thomas Carter</B> (<I>Equal Justice,
Under One Roof</I>) served as executive producer of the movie.
<P>
<I><B>Divas</B></I>, an ensemble drama, airs <U>Tuesday, September
19, 1995, at 9:00 p.m.</U> on <B>CHCH-TV </B>(one hour post/Fox).
<HR>

<P>
