<HEAD>

<TITLE>"The Great Mom Swap," a lighthearted drama on CHCH-TV</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../gifs/bkgd.jpg">

<P>
<IMG SRC="../../gifs/11s.gif"> <I>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: September
13, 1995</I><HR>

<H4><CENTER><B>CHCH HAS THE LIGHT-HEARTED DRAMA</CENTER> </B>
</H4>

<H1><CENTER><I><B>THE GREAT MOM SWAP</CENTER></B></I></H1>

<P>
Two teenage girls with nothing in common, except for the contempt
they share for each other's lifestyle, learn a lesson in tolerance,
respect and friendship in<I><B> The Great Mom Swap,</B></I> airing
<U>Sunday, September 24, 1995, (9:00 - 11:00 p.m.)</U> on <B>CHCH-TV</B>.
<P>
<B>Shelly Fabares</B> (<I>Coach</I>), <B>Valerie Harper </B>(<I>Rhoda</I>),
and the legendary<B> Sid Caesar</B> star in the two-hour movie
along with<B> Hillary Tuck </B>(<I>Camp Nowhere</I>) and <B>Mary
Kate Schellhardt </B>(<I>Apollo 13, Free Willy II</I>).
<P>
In <I><B>The Great Mom Swap</B></I>, Terry Benessi and Karen Ridgeway
are two young girls with a strong dislike for each other.  Terry
is the bookish, bright, unpopular girl from &quot;the wrong side
of town.&quot;  Karen, by contrast, lacks academic prowess, is
popular and comes from an affluent family.
<P>
When their mutual animosity results in the potential burning down
of the school, they are given a choice: expulsion and a month
at a work camp, or 50 hours of community service while trading
families for a month.  The pair opt for the latter.
<P>
Karen is humiliated to be seen in Terry's neighbourhood, and quicker
than she feared, her so-called friends desert her.  Having to
relinquish a loving household for a sterile mansion, Terry discovers
that Karen's life is not exactly a fairy tale.  And, when the
two are forced to work together as a team for their community
service assignment, their reaction is one of more antagonism.
<P>
Filled with poignant humour and lessons in pride and regard for
others, <I><B>The Great Mom Swap</B></I> is a delightful, contemporary
<I>&quot;Prince and the Pauper&quot; </I>frolic.  <I><B>The Great
Mom Swap </B></I>airs <U>Sunday, September 24, 1995, at 9:00 p.m.</U>
on <B>CHCH-TV</B>. <HR>

<P>
