<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Nanny: Madeline Zima Biography</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY background="../../images/bkgd.jpg">

<P>

<CENTER>
<U>MADELINE ZIMA</U>
<P>
<B>Biography</B>
</CENTER>

<P>
Madeline Zima co-stars as Grace Sheffield, a very serious, analytical
six-year-old, in TriStar Television's half-hour comedy series
<I><B>The Nanny</B></I>.
<P>
Madeline, born on September 16 in New Haven, Connecticut, began
her career in show business at the young age of 22 months starring
in a Downey commercial. She went on to appear in dozens of national
commercials in New York before being cast in the daytime serial
&quot;Guiding Light.&quot;
<P>
She co-stars in the feature film &quot;Mr. Nanny&quot; with Hulk
Hogan, and has appeared in &quot;Last Supper&quot; and &quot;The
Hand That Rocks the Cradle.&quot; Madeline also guest starred
on the TV drama &quot;Law &amp; Order.&quot;
<P>
When not acting in Hollywood, Madeline lives in Easton, Pennsylvania.
Her favorite subject in school is art and she enjoys playing with
Barbie dolls, camping, panning for gold and roller skating with
her sister.

<P>
