<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 12/20/95</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
</CENTER>
</H1>


<H2>
<CENTER>
Wednesday, December 20, 1995
<IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
</H2>


<UL>
<LI>China Suspect Arrest 
<LI>Prostitute Prof 
<LI>Harris - Tax Cut 
<LI>McLeod-Omnibus 
<LI>McLeod-Omnibus Tag 
<LI>Handover Wrap 
<LI>Unpaid Work 
<LI>Garbage Dump
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>China Suspect Arrest</H3>

<P>
A Toronto man has been charged with one count of first-degree
murder and two counts of attempted murder in connection with a
shooting outside a Toronto Chinese restaurant early last Sunday
morning in which a man was shot to death. 
<P>
Police raided a residence in Toronto's Jane-Finch area and took
several suspects into custody. 
<P>
Charged is 20-year-old Tien Dung Duang. He'll appear in court
tomorrow morning for a bail hearing.
<HR>

<H3>Prostitute Prof </H3>

<P>
Ryerson University says it found no evidence that part time journalism
instructor Gerald Hannon breached the limits of academic expression
in the classroom by espousing views supporting pedophilia. 
<P>
Hannon has been reinstated and will resume his duties next month.
He was also investigated by the University over comments about
his work as a prostitute. 
<P>
Ryerson says an investigation showed Hannon breached the collective
agreement and will be given a letter of discipline. 
<HR>

<H3>Harris - Tax Cut </H3>

<P>
It would seem that Premier Mike Harris is backing off somewhat
on his promise of a 30-percent provincial income tax cut to Ontarians.
Harris is now saying the wealthy will not get the tax break. 
<HR>

<H3>McLeod-Omnibus</H3>

<P>
Liberal Leader Lyn McLeod has called for an extension of public
hearings on Bill 26,called the &quot;omnibus bill.&quot; 
<P>
But Premier Mike Harris says &quot;no&quot;. The hearings are
being held all this week at Queens Park, and then will take to
the road for two weeks in January before being passed into law
January 29th. 
<P>
The hearings have become so popular that Liberal Leader Lyn McLeod
has written to Premier Harris, asking him to extend the hearings.
But Harris says no. 
<HR>

<H3>McLeod-Omnibus Tag</H3>

<P>
The deal the opposition parties agreed to, actually provide for
60 hours less hearing time than the government originally planned.

<HR>

<H3>Handover Wrap</H3>

<P>
NATO troops are quickly taking up their positions in Bosnia now
that their official mission has begun. 
<P>
The United Nations handed over the peacekeeping mission to allied
forces today. 
<HR>

<H3>Unpaid Work</H3>

<P>
Imagine getting paid for all the chores you do. Collecting a cheque
for things like washing the dishes or taking out the garbage.
Well, Statistics Canada has released a report that puts a dollar
amount to the 25-billion hours of unpaid work Canadians have put
in. 
<P>
Reporter Marci Ien brings us the facts and figures. 
<P>
<I>It's women who do most of the shopping, cleaning and other
chores ...in fact Stats- Can puts the number at 65 per-cent. But
research also shows more women are entering the paid labour market.
And that means families have more income.</I>
<P>
<I>Many use the extra cash to help out with the chores...and with
the children. In fact, spending on child care outside the home
increased to 2.8 billion in 1992. ...and that makes daycare one
of the fastest growing items of household expenditure. </I>
<P>
<I>But for those who put in double duty at home and at work...health
can be an issue. </I>
<P>
<I>In Hamilton, Marci Ien, Channel 11 News. </I>
<HR>

<H3>Garbage Dump</H3>

<P>
Two committees of metro Toronto council have rejected a proposal
to buy the Adams Mine site near Kirkland Lake to store Toronto's
garbage. 
<P>
The committees will recommend council seek a private sector solution
to its garbage woes. The proposal was considered too expensive
for the municipality. 
<P>
Mine owner Gordon McGuinty says the decision surprised him because
some metro officials recommended keeping all options open. 
<P>


<P>
<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

