<HEAD>

<TITLE>The Evening News: 11/30/95</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="../../../images/evening.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
On-Line Archive
<H2>Thursday, November 30, 1995 <IMG SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</H2>

</CENTER>
</H1>

<UL>
<LI>QP Follow 
<LI>Ontario Cuts 
<LI>Agriculture Cuts 
<LI>Hydro Secrets 
<LI>Veto Bill 
<LI>Exorcism Sentence 
<LI>Caveat
</UL>

<HR>

<H3>QP Follow </H3>

<P>
A number of Liberal MPP's stormed out of the legislature in a
rage today, accusing the Harris government of being sneaky and
dictatorial, in how it introduced an omnibus bill that could change
dozens of laws affecting everything from hospital closures to
the environment. 
<HR>

<H3>Ontario Cuts</H3>

<P>
In Ottawa today, Federal Finance Minister Paul Martin was non-committal
when asked for his reaction to yesterday's Ontario mini- budget,
saying only that times are tough and governments have to cut back.

<HR>

<H3>Agriculture Cuts</H3>

<P>
The Ministry of Agriculture has wasted no time in announcing how
it will shoulder its share of yesterday's announced spending cuts.

<P>
Several field offices, including the one in Cayuga, are to be
shut down. Also among the cuts... funding for the Ontario Agricultural
Museum in Milton will end. 
<HR>

<H3>Hydro Secrets </H3>

<P>
Secret safety reviews Ontario Hydro conducted of its nuclear plants
give the utility failing grades for safety and operating performance
at its two Bruce plants on Lake Huron and at its Darlington Nuclear
Station east of Toronto. And safety at Hydro's Pickering Nuclear
Plant has come under fire in a letter from the atomic energy control
board. 
<P>
The letter stated safety concerns at the plant were being overridden
by &quot;other corporate priorities.&quot; Broadcast News obtained
copies of the reports that Hydro had said would alarm the public
unnecessarily and undermine its economic interests. 
<HR>

<H3>Veto Bill </H3>

<P>
Hamilton's Sheila Copps injected emotion into Parliament's post
referendum unity debate today. 
<P>
The Deputy Prime Minister was close to tears as she pleaded with
the Bloc Quebecois and Reform Party to support her government's
unity proposals. The focus in the latest round of bickering was
on the constitutional vetoes being offered to Quebec, Ontario,
Atlantic Canada and the west. 
<HR>

<H3>Exorcism Sentence </H3>

<P>
A Cambridge woman believes she was possessed by Satan... and it's
the devil who killed her granddaughter. 
<P>
Anna- Maria Canhotto has pleaded guilty to manslaughter in the
death... and she was to be sentenced today... but that won't happen
until after a psychiatric examination. 
<HR>

<H3>Caveat </H3>

<P>
The mother of one of Paul Bernardo's murder victims is urging
the federal government to deny killers the right to apply for
early parole. 
<P>
Donna French joined one of 8 CAVEAT news conferences across the
country today to publicly support a private members bill that
would take away the right of murderers to apply for parole after
they serve 15 years of a life sentence. 
<P>
The private members bill to repeal section 745 of the criminal
code was introduced by Toronto Liberal John Nunziata last year.
It has little chance of passing into law because Justice Minister
Alan Rock opposes it. 
<P>
<I> </I>
<P>

<CENTER><IMG WIDTH=585 HEIGHT=30 SRC="../../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>

